{"product_id": "15100", "page": 3, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-02-05", "text": "I jumped into this franchise late and played AC4 first and loved the story and gameplay, so I wanted to start from the begining to get the full experience.   I expected AC 1 to be a bit more primitive when I got it, but wasn't ready for just how bad it was.  The story isn't quite as good, but that's forgivable.  The problem lies in the fact that what little story there is, is drowned out by monotonous tasks that don't give that \"assassin\" feel.  There's very little sneaking around and assassinating of a target.   Instead, most \"missions\" turn into a slugfest where you're fighting half the city guards.  There's no feeling of immersion, rather just grinding through battle after battle to get to the cutscenes to try and glean some kind of storyline.  I finished it, deleted it, and vowed to never wasted time on it again.  Had I played this first, I wouldn't have been drawn to the Assassin's Creed franchise in the first place.  Here's to hoping 2 and 3 are better.", "hours": 25.0, "user_id": "76561198039042219", "username": "imthepopedammit", "products": 45, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 3, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-02-04", "text": "Terrible controls (both with joypad & keyboard).\nBad graphics.\nRepetitive. Repetitive. Repetitive.\nUninstalled as fast as I could.", "hours": 2.2, "username": "Kamgusta", "products": 2279, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 3, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2018-02-03", "text": "Assassin's Creed I was very good storywise and it gives you proper knowledge which is needed to connect all things together in later AC games what concerns the story Ubisoft wants to tell you. If you are kind of player as I am, which means that you began playing AC from Brotherhood or simply not with the first part, I strongly recommend you to buy and play this game. If you are the person who does not want the story but pure gameplay experience, you do not need to touch this game.\n/ PROS\n- overall quality at the release date\n- the story\n- idea\n/ CONS\n- monotony gameplay (too much repetition or similarity of missions and actions you take throughout the game)\n- movement is not as good as you may expect but we need to consider the fact that it was released in 2008", "hours": 12.0, "username": "SAMPITTKO", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
