{"product_id": "15100", "page": 8, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-30", "text": "Great game so far. Bit repetitive but I keep coming back for more anyway!\nWorks with wireless PS4 controller with a bit of adapting the settings in the game.", "hours": 35.3, "username": "nicolleelizabethevans", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 8, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-29", "text": "This game is a really interesting game. I love the idea that people can live the lives of their ancestors, who happen to be badass assassins. The gameplay is linear, and Altair may have a severe case of monotone, but I think it still is pretty cool to uncover a conspiracy, redeem yourself after killing a ton of friends, etc. It consists of running around Acre, Jerusalem, and Damascus killing each target, dramatically. You kill about 3 targets in each area, then you kill another target, and then the game is done. Throughout the adventure, you can collect a ton of flags from each place, and can be annoying to find all of them.\nTL;DR This game is for people who want to run around a lot stabbing people who are evil.", "hours": 28.3, "username": "PinkandBlue", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
