{"product_id": "15100", "page": 10, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-12-18", "text": "Game has a simple story. But ofcourse not true history. I saw Turk\u0131sh flag in game. Turkish flag discover in 1389 battle of Kosova. So is not Eyyubi flag. I was very suprised when saw the flag. Gameplay is enough sometimes you get crazy. Altair jumping wrong way or mouse not doing what you did. Finally is not worth the price. But if you want learn the story buy it in discount season. And Hasan-i Sabbah is just junkie but not use the needle.", "hours": 28.8, "username": "Comolokko", "products": 55, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 10, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-18", "text": "Another great example of games before they became unfinished, microtransaction-riddled nonsense.\nA cheaper history course than the ones you could take at your local community college/10", "hours": 1.7, "user_id": "76561198132164162", "username": "_ALuX_", "products": 31, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 10, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-17", "text": "A great game, and childhood favorite of mine, AC1 delivers on most fronts. My only real issue is around 4 crashes through out my 30 hour playthrough, several graphical glitches, and several mechanics glitches. No game breaking bugs were found in my playthrough. 360 version is less glitchy, and never crashed, however doesn't run as good/load as fast (obviously). My other complaint is needing to play around a bit to get my gamepad to work correctly, but once it is all said and done the experience is quite nice.\nCompared to games nowadays I would say the experience is pretty bare overall. A few mission types, repetitive actions throughout the game, simple revenge story, (that DOES however thicken) etc. However, I would definitely recommend playing through this game to get a grasp of the world, setting, backstory, and characters, if you plan on playing through the series. I wouldn't skip this point in the AC timeline simply because it IS enjoyable even in its bare state, and it isn't a long game. (30 hours: Main story+Side Missions *Did not get all collectibles*) AC2, Brotherhood, and Black Flag are better games in my opinion, but It wouldn't be fair to judge the game based on its newer releases.\nTLDR: Good game, port is a little buggy, controller issues may occur during setup.", "hours": 32.2, "username": "State", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 10, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-12", "text": "You jump around, kill a lot of people and the visuals are beautiful. It gets kind of repetitive but is a great experience, conveyed through a strong story-telling. 10/10, one of my favourite games, Altair is quite a dull character, but is the original assassin, so I let it slid. This gem is 10 years old and still fantastic, definitely recommend it. I'm gonna play all the other games, including Unity now, it is so much fun. Gets you started to what is to come in the franchise, a must play overall", "hours": 41.9, "user_id": "76561198112564270", "username": "DILDO BAGGINS", "products": 43, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 10, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-10", "text": "Very repetitive but incredible for its age. Sets the story for many games to come. Recommend a quick playthrough of this one.", "hours": 18.4, "username": "Piyapon", "products": 541, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 10, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-12-10", "text": "The climbing mechanics are cool, the counters during combat are cool, and the story is pretty interesting. However, it's very boring. Same missions each area, and they are all done the same way. The assassination missions are worth it, but everything else is lame filler. I'd recommend going through the main missions only. Pretty short game, worth it if its on sale.", "hours": 18.3, "user_id": "76561198224562468", "username": "arlendp6555", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
