{"product_id": "15100", "page": 12, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-29", "text": "I came back to this game with thoughts of nostalgia and love of the series before it got turned into a series milking the consumers every year. But honestly this game is such a drag. You run around saving millions of civilians, doing the same 4-5 quests to learn about your targets and then go kill your target. Then rinse and repeat 9 times. The actual assassination missions are fun. But you only spend 1% of your time doing them. And don't get me started on the 500 collectables. Anyone who actually goes for all of them is insane.", "hours": 9.3, "user_id": "76561198045102105", "username": "Schwegg", "products": 281, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
