{"product_id": "15100", "page": 15, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-22", "text": "I bought this for my new PC, just to play the series from the start. It seems fine when you are just running around. But, when you get into any action scenes. Like when youare fighting. It is so glitchy, that it is unplayable. I would seriously not recommend this to anyone", "hours": 11.5, "user_id": "76561198286137238", "username": "Soulspinner", "products": 66, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 15, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-11-21", "text": "Gave it a chance, but it just didn't work out. The story seems interesting, but the controls are just painful! I wouldn't be surprised if this was ported from console.\nPros:\n+ Story seems interesting\n+ Good graphics for it's time\nCons:\n- Absolutely horrible controls\n- Walking simulator 2.0, it takes half of real life to go to the next town\n- Clunky camera, probably console port legacy\n- Map is garbage", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Xel'Naga", "products": 192, "early_access": false}
