{"product_id": "15100", "page": 15, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-19", "text": "Still holds up remarkably well.\nInnovative in it's time.\nA fun setting. With some interesting moral ambiguity.\nCombat is superficial but fun.\nThe story is quite interesting and has some fun though not persay unexpected twists and turns.\nThe main character turned out more likeable than I expected. Far more likeable.\nThe only 2 true downsides to the game are:\n1) Repetitive sidequest. More varied sidequests would have been great. And especially some subplots linked to them.\n2) Meaningful sidequests. Linked to point 1. True rewards and unlocks linked to the sidequests.\nAll in all though...\nPretty awesome and cool.\nA recommended game!", "hours": 26.3, "username": "Darthvegeta800", "products": 312, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 15, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-11-19", "text": "Compared to its sequels, the original\nis a very limited open world game with repetitive missions that still feels quite polished and full of promise - promise that later games in the franchise would elaborate on, for better or worse.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "TemplarHedgehog", "products": 206, "early_access": false}
