{"product_id": "15100", "page": 19, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-10-25", "text": "This is a hard review to write. I like the Assassin's Creed series. WIthout a doubt, the franchise couldn't have evolved into what it is today without this game. What I like about it is that it kept me busy for 20 hours. I like the whole \"apple\" thing. I like the freerunning/parkour integration. What I can't [under]stand is that riding a horse (peacefully) is a crime that is punishable by death.... There are no cars, helicopters, bicycles, etc. Only horses. And if you ride one between towns, which is mandatory in the beginning, you WILL get attacked. That is the dumbest thing I have ever seen in my life. Incomprehensibly stupid. I love the other games though lol.", "hours": 20.0, "username": "RotoGamer2826", "products": 694, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
