{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-17", "text": "This is the game that started it all. Assassin's Creed has had influence on many items, from movies to other games (let alone the series it spawned). This game is slightly clunky, but as it is the first in the series, one can forgive any little flaws, the same way some artist's early works are not as refined as their later efforts. It is fun, and has an immersive story (which is somewhat literal in respects).\nAs the only of the series I have played at this point (though I have bought a few), I am unsure how the series goes through anything other than hearsay, but those rumors indicate that this is still one of the best. Also, I do wonder if the Arkham games took a few of this game's ideas as basis for their own success...", "hours": 10.4, "user_id": "76561198069159152", "username": "wrb41977", "products": 745, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-08-14", "text": "Works really \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing bad with xbox one controller!", "hours": 0.6, "username": "PurpleMercurius", "products": 370, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-14", "text": "Great game that set up grounds for future gigantic franchise, extremely innovative and graphically impressive for 2007, though with few flaws unfortunatelly in form of repetitive gameplay. Still one of my favorite instalment of a largely exploited and milked assassin's series.\nVerdict: 7/10", "hours": 12.1, "username": "Zest Riddler", "products": 1247, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-08-14", "text": "When I started playing Assassin's Creed I was amazed at the detail of the world and people that Ubisoft had put into the game and at first i had a blast sneaking about the rooftops and taking out targets from up high. But as the game ran on it started to get very repetitive with the set up missions and side missions being all the same with no difference in how they were played the only enjoyment to be had being the assasinations themselves. If you are starting the assassins creed series the story will be the only reason you will need to play this.", "hours": 19.7, "user_id": "76561198037259791", "username": "xeno", "products": 415, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-11", "text": "Perfect. Just like all the Assassins Creed games. Already finished playing this one, ac 2, brotherhood, revelations, 3, tyranny of washington and now I started playing 4", "hours": 22.0, "username": "P0TAT0 FR0G", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
