{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-08-10", "text": "This is arguably the worst game I own on steam. The mechanics at times are fun, but overall the game is just a heaping mess and not worth the time or effort.", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561197991220883", "username": "Cerebral Paulsy", "products": 202, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-09", "text": "I love to play this game. Graphicaly this game was in the past and still is somehow a masterpiece. It's been quite a lot since this game had been released but I recommend this game very much.\nPS. Freaking Hollywood has made a movie (Blin!)... don't watch it. Instead play this game.", "hours": 308.9, "user_id": "76561198391158518", "username": "wasp8118", "products": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-05", "text": "As the first Assassin's Creed I ever played, I have to say I enjoyed it a lot. The story was pretty good overall. In each act the player gets to choose where to go for their next target between what targets are available and how much information they want to have before the assassination (even if there is a minimum), which I like since it doesn't restrict the player's actions too much. The mechanics are pretty well designed for the game, but are a slighly difficult to get used to in my opinion. The only thing about the game I didn't really like was the last assassination since it didn't feel completely fulfilling the way it carried out. The ending on the other hand was pretty good and got me wanting to play the next game in the series.\nI would definitely recomend this game for people looking to get into the series or people who want to try out a game like this.", "hours": 52.9, "username": "OconkerC", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 27, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-05", "text": "Not well optimized for Windows 10. Plenty of CTDs, glitches.\nA bit boring, considering the other games. Ending is terrible.\nBut still recommended because of the Ezio storyline that it spawned.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "CryingSpock", "products": 121, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 28, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-04", "text": "This game is a perfect example of an Assassin's Creed game. Your character has tons of trouble climbing things, runs off ledges all the time, misses lots of his attacks, and in general is kind of a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 However, what this game lacks that the others have is a subtitle.\nI still \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665in love these games, though. <3", "hours": 16.1, "username": "Captain J. Ryno", "products": 185, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 28, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-04", "text": "I like this game so much. The starting point of a fantastic franchise. The gameplay is superb and the story, one you manage to decipher it, is pretty interesting. The whole world building gets better with every new chapter. Everything began with this tittle. Altair is an amazing character and the Assassin's Brotherhood a concept to behold. The story arc is exciting, while the missions let you know and enjoy every city. The recreation of history is convincing. The enviroments are unique. Masterpiece 10/10", "hours": 97.4, "username": "Tecnocrat", "products": 287, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 28, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-08-01", "text": "The best initiative by Ubisoft after prince of persia franchise.\nIn the beginning (back in 2007) when this game was released and played I heard may of my friends praising this game more than any other game. They kept saying to me, dude you should play assassin's creed. When I asked why? A strange yet stupid reply stating that its similar to prince of persia and you can make the character climb any building. (What's the big deal) That message was stuck in my head until I tried with first time on my PC (pirated version - because games costed huge amount) after trying it for few missions I Fell In LOVE with this game. I uninstalled the pirated and deleted my gamesaves. Sold my pc and bought a new high end gaming machine costing \u20b91.28 Lakhs ($2000 Approx) then I purchased first 3 instalments of Assassin's Creed except 3 (ubisoft gave AC 3 for free on their 30th anniversary)\nStarted a new game in ultra settings and damn It was worth of my money. The story, the cutscenes, the idea itself was unique. Loved the gameplay and completed in no time. But still there are few thing yet to collect. This game has major musical auro for the ears. For once i really felt that i am living in 11th century. Love everything about this game.", "hours": 22.3, "username": "Amjad Hussain", "products": 118, "early_access": false}
