{"product_id": "15100", "page": 30, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-12", "text": "While it may not hold up as well as the others, this was the seminal game that gave us the franchise that Ubisoft would soon start to hold over us as they slowly milked it to death. AC2, ACB AC4, ACR, and ACS are the only other ones worth getting.", "hours": 31.1, "username": "Rudbeard", "products": 490, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 30, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-11", "text": "For me, still the best game in the whole franchise. Because it shows the real Assassin's. on their own time. And it's the only game who makes sense to wear a Assassin costume. My eyes hurt to see Ezio running all over Italy with a Assassin suit and nobody giving a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665for that. On AC I it's normal, because the Assassin's were an active order. And it's the most difficult game, but just because has limited gameplay. Doesn't have parkour, wich is good, because as i know, parkour was not invented in ancient Egipt like AC Origins is showing to us. AC I is by far the most original game in the franchise.", "hours": 10.9, "username": "John Winchester", "products": 311, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 30, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-10", "text": "Assassin's Creed brought an original idea to gaming in 2007. Although some gameplay elements can seem unrefined, and the story can drag sometimes, this game was the start of something very interesting. It's fun while it lasts, but it's rarely worth a replay.", "hours": 18.8, "username": "IronicRobot", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
