{"product_id": "15100", "page": 30, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "Score: 8/10\nAs the first game in the series, its content clearly wasn't as developed as in its sequels. I still enjoyed the streamlined story, as they do a great job of building to the climax. Some of the approaches to the target assassinations were also very creative and enjoyable. If you have a decent PC set up, this game can look pretty great for its age.", "hours": 17.6, "username": "Paratus", "products": 439, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-08", "text": "It's a special game of course cause it's the first opus of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665Creed, so it's always a pleasure when u play it. Only the quests are a bit repetitives, and it becomes tedious to get informations for your murder target (even though the result was worth it). But the game dates back to 2007, so good game.", "hours": 28.1, "user_id": "76561198179946005", "username": "\u2666\u2663\u2660\u2665", "products": 12, "early_access": false}
