{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-06", "text": "I remember enjoying the game despite it becoming repetitive. It brings new elements to the open world genre, like the parkour mechanic. And the story is quite captivating, not just the good vs evil \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "bob loblaw", "products": 551, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-06", "text": "Okay, so after roughly 26 hours I finally finished the game in 100%.\nPros:\n+ Fantastic story\n+ Very immersive world\n+ Good gameplay\n+ Lots of extra stuff to do (read the cons)\n+ Pretty fun challenges\nCons:\n- Very repetitive, almost all extra stuff was to either save a citizen, find flags, kill a templar or complete a certain challenge\n- Minor bugs while doing parkour around the city (climbing wrong walls, jumping in a wrong direction, which was especially annoying above water)\n- Often music and background noise was too loud, which made dialogues hard to understand\n- Madmen constantly pushing you for no reason, which often leads to exposure. There are far too many of them and you can't really do anything about them. If they block your way, they constantly push you and you can't push them back because guards will instantly expose you.\nOverall, I'd recommend this game for everyone starting the journey with Assasin's Creed genre as this is the beginning of the story and a golden classic, which led to creation of so many good games afterwards.", "hours": 25.9, "user_id": "76561198047202073", "username": "JCVader", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-06", "text": "Not a single AC game sucks. So amazing.", "hours": 19.9, "username": "link1987", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-05", "text": "Great game from start to finish for what/when it was. Repetitive but a great showcase of gameplay/interactive world at the time. amazing franchise.", "hours": 20.4, "user_id": "76561198347419480", "username": "dubiousd0m", "products": 30, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "Big fan of this game, with time missions get repetetive, but the story makes it, best way to start game series from here.", "hours": 29.0, "user_id": "76561197965258147", "username": "Velnias", "products": 60, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "The game potrays the story fo Desmond Miles, where through a machine called the \"Animus\" is able to relive the life of his ancestor, Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad who was an assassin during the time of the Third Crusade. This game requires players to use the environment to their advantage, quite similar to another Ubisoft game franchise, The Prince of Persia. One of the main difference between this game and The Prince of Persia games is having an open world gameplay as players may choose the approach on how to fulfill the objective.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Hybrid_Dragon", "products": 93, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "Assassin's Creed I is a great game and I really enjoyed playing it. The first time I picked this gem up was a few years ago and I was blown away. This is the second time I've beaten the game and I can't wait to play other Assassin's Creed games, that's how much I liked it.\nAnd don't let my game play time fool you, I played it in offline mode so 1.3 hours is not how much I played it.\nTbh, I beat the game pretty quickly, a few hours a day in the past week or so, but it was still awesome.\n10/10 overall experience :D", "hours": 1.3, "username": "anniberi", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 31, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "This PC controls for this game are awkward, but not too awkward that it doesn't ruin the experience. There is a good amount of content for the price it's at, and the world your in is pretty to look at.", "hours": 21.4, "username": "Ivory Fox Boy", "products": 313, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-04", "text": "Not that great you finish the game very fast no currency no achievements and very easy objective.", "hours": 18.3, "username": "Tommasteragent | \u2622 | KYS", "products": 200, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "1: do some side quests\n2: kill a guy\n3: rinse and repeat\n4:...?\n5: profit", "hours": 54.4, "username": "USBChicken101", "products": 36, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "This game is a perfect example of whether graphics or gameplay makes a game good.\nGraphically, the game looks beautiful. The visuals are incredibly stunning and the world looks beautiful. Graphics and visuals I give a 10/10\nHowever, the game is simply just not fun to play. It gets boring, repetitive, and you spend most of the game either A) climbing walls or B) fighting or trying to get away from guards. That's the majority of the game. Pretty much had to force myself to grind it out the last few levels just to beat it, and now I can uninstall it. You can revisit all the levels again after beating the game, to get the parts you missed, or to find flags, but really..... Why would you want to? Just about anything you do will attract the guards and fighitng them is a chore, not anything close to fun.\nAlso, the story failed to draw me in, but it seems to have drawn in some others. Hard to say if you will like the story or not.\nIf you want a game just for great graphics, then go for it. If you want a game that's fun to play, look elsewhere. Ask yourself what's more important between graphics and gameplay.", "hours": 15.3, "username": "Brispir", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "- stay your blade from the flesh of an innocent\n- hide in plain sight\n- never compromise the Brotherhood\n- and jump into as many haystacks as possible", "hours": 18.3, "user_id": "76561198049565291", "username": "hapber", "products": 445, "found_funny": 19, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "I personally really enjoyed Assassin's Creed as a whole. Below I have detailed just what made this game worth playing, as well as what I found frustrating or undesireable throughout my playthrough.", "hours": 49.3, "username": "UselessAssassin", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "I'm amazed that this game got such positive reviews upon release. While I applaude the mix of made up story with actual historical characters and events it's intervened by some very drab gameplay elements which become awfully reptitive very quickly: Evesdrop on people, pickpocket stuff, get permission for the kill on a high value target, make the kill, explore the city by climbing eagle towers, rinse and repeat over and over again.\nAlso, there is a suprisingly small amount of actual stealth/sneaking for a game revolving around assassins. Most missions eventually will end up you being dragged in some fights involving very poor swordfighting mechanics (multiple guys will stand around you and each in turn allow themselves to be butchered).\nI played about halfway through the game and gave up due to the sheer repetition of it all. As far as I'm concerned Ubisoft gets a 10 for the ideas but a mere 5 for the actual execution of the ideas that made it into the final game.", "hours": 27.6, "user_id": "76561197960703887", "username": "Chief", "products": 103, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-02", "text": "Assasins Creed. I find the lore of this series really good especially the start which is this game. Yes the gameplay is VERY repetitive but its the story that made this game successful. I would reccommend this if you are going to play through all of the Assasins Creed games. If not but want a AC game? get 2, Brotherhood, and Revalations", "hours": 15.4, "username": "Infinite CJ", "products": 149, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-07-01", "text": "+ Amazing scope, absolutely massive game-world\n+ Incredibly well-crafted story with excellent voice-acting\n+ Climb absolutely anything and jump off from the highest points into a stack of hay. Awesome!\n- AI and city life less dynamic than it should have been\n- Gameplay can become a bit repetitive\n- Some miner tech issues in the face of such a magnificient game engine\nAll in all Assassin's Creed is a good game and worth a buy.", "hours": 17.0, "user_id": "76561198046992905", "username": "Damna", "products": 470, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-30", "text": "Guards are as cancerous as fidget spinners, 8/10", "hours": 102.2, "username": "anewest", "products": 280, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 32, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-30", "text": "It's fun to play this game to see where it all started, but it turns generic quick. 7.5/10.", "hours": 14.2, "username": "gamernes9", "products": 257, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 33, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-30", "text": "After 14.1 hours of this game I must say it gets really repetative so keep that in mind before buying this product.\nAssassin's Creed was a really fun game, if you've played any of the other games you know the basics, run around, climb, assassinate the templars, etc. This game started what is now a great series, and one that will remain in my mind forever, and if not that a very long time. The game's story is (in my opinion) deep, and at times relatable. The free run system could use some work (it has gotten work in later games) and the climbing was somewhat stable however you could not climb ledges that you would be able to in later games. Overall I recommend this game to fans of the series, but if you're new to it, I would start with Assassin's Creed II (Italy) or III (Boston) (You don't have to play them in order)", "hours": 14.8, "username": "MalwarebytesMan", "products": 125, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 33, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-28", "text": "A little buggy here and there, but nothing to spoil the experience or game breaking. A must have for those who are a fan of the franchise", "hours": 20.5, "username": "JonnyonTorry", "products": 270, "early_access": false}
