{"product_id": "15100", "page": 33, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-27", "text": "Not really the gem among the AC series, but any fan of the franchise should give this a go.\nNone the less I liked the story and after getting accustomed to the controls I quite enjoyed spending time with Altair.", "hours": 25.4, "user_id": "76561198139903364", "username": "taz96", "products": 202, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 33, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-27", "text": ":D exelent game", "hours": 65.6, "user_id": "76561198051529724", "username": "R.", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 33, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-26", "text": "This game is extremely repetitive and boring. I tried to play this game all the way through and I ended up quitting at the ending because it was too hard with the garbage combat in this game. The guards start chasing you if you walk by them and it takes 5 minutes to ditch them because when you try to turn somewhere or jump there is a stupid wall that the game makes you run into, a beggar, or a special needs guy that punches you. I do not reccomend playing this unless you really want to. AC2 is 10x more amazing.", "hours": 29.1, "username": "Farmboybello", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-26", "text": "Ah, the ship that launched a hundred sequals, and the highly trained super-assassin who can't swim. A great game for it's time that opened up the modern open-world genre. Well worth a play and a must if you want to have all the details of the story. As will all Ubi games, it has major pc optimization issues, especially if you run a system with more than 4 cores. Before you even try to play it, set your compatibility mode and limit core affinity to 2 cores. Also, never got the dx10 version to work, always had missing world elements; ie. objects were there, but no walls, floors, roofs, ect. Great game, poor pc port.", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198031121733", "username": "deathscythe808", "products": 398, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-26", "text": "10/10 game. This game is the birthstone for what Assassins's Creed has become. I have beat the game 4 times I believe now, and it doesn't get old. Crazy to see how different the original is from the newer AC games.\nA lot of people however, do say it gets repetitive, which in a sense I can agree on. Your mission for killing the templars is the same. Visit the city district, talk to the bureau leader, do viewpoints, save citizens, and 6 missions that are of the same relation. Once done, you go kill the templar, and eventually make your way to the next city and repeat it all. Although it's the same, it does not take away from the fact that doing all this is FUN. It still has an awesome story line and is very relaxing to play.\nIf you want to get into the AC series, definitely start from the beginning with this one. It's also crucial to the Desmond Miles story.", "hours": 94.5, "username": "GameNut", "products": 118, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-26", "text": "Never played AC and i bought all the games in the steam summer sale thinking now is the time to play them all in order before origins comes out.\nAssassin's Creed seems to have aged well. Graphics still look nice.\nGameplay is okay but the quests are very repetitive, same goes for the combat.\nAll you seem to do is counter - break grab - repeat.\nIt's still fun to play but after about 15hours it was getting a bit frustrating and i was starting to rush so i could move on to ACII", "hours": 18.4, "username": "\u2623Valtorde\u2623", "products": 491, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-26", "text": "On my deathbed I'll probably ask to play this game one last time.\nBut in all seriousness, I played it more times than any other game (physical copy mostly). It got me into gaming and is truly a classic. Its success was the reason why the other games happened, some people really forget that, including Ubisoft, unfortunately.\nThe gameplay gets repetitive, yes, a lot of people often point that out. Besides that, the game has aged really well, has great visuals, great story and characters. Not to mention it is the base for the entire fanchise.\n10/10, fight me.", "hours": 12.6, "user_id": "76561198126957161", "username": "TheNemophilist", "products": 54, "found_funny": 7, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-25", "text": "The cut scenes and combat can be a bit boring (don't know if this applies to the later game) and the parkour system can be a bit stiff if you don't know what you're doing, but it's an Assassin's Creed -game. :)", "hours": 3.0, "username": "Asam1", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-25", "text": "The first Assassin`s Creed game is a good start to a huge franchise and for the year of its release a remarkably well programmed game.Like every game it has got its \"Ups and Downs\" , but it is worth noting that it gave video games a totally new meaning. It also allows people with a less beefy computer (e.g me) to play a part of this franchise.", "hours": 31.0, "user_id": "76561198305989576", "username": "TheBritishBoy", "products": 26, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-24", "text": "An old classic, definitely recommended. It started a huge behemoth of mixed-quality games, but this one always stood out to me. It was time well invested--though definitely not worth the time (to me) of collecting all of the collectables in-game.", "hours": 10.0, "username": "Godon", "products": 979, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-24", "text": "\"Nothing is true, everything is permitted\"...even if you do the same all the time...\n7/10", "hours": 6.9, "username": "Jeffrey Goines", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-22", "text": "11/10 A must have!!", "hours": 26.5, "username": "{FP}Camouflage", "products": 11027, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 34, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-20", "text": "Ya know....  there are just better Assassins Creed games out there now.  This one is notorious for being EXTREMLY repetitive.\nIts got some appealing features to it but in the end, its kinda boring, reduntant, hollow.  Id just read the story synopsis somewhere and skip it.  Oh and theres the small minor issue of the game freezing on you every 5 minutes.", "hours": 8.2, "user_id": "76561197972406557", "username": "SpaceMonkey907", "products": 452, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-18", "text": "The game is old but for the time it was made its a pretty big leap. Some of the missions are really repeitive like listen to this guy or beat up this guy, but in all the game is pretty simple and fun for the start of the Assassin's Creed games. I would recomend to try it.", "hours": 19.7, "user_id": "76561198073952047", "username": "ARC RC 1136", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-18", "text": "The price of the game went up to twice it's price in Mexico. And now it's even the most expensive place to buy the game, which is just plain ridiculous.", "hours": 4.5, "username": "DrBeckett", "products": 2382, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-17", "text": "If you want to play the series in order, this game almost makes it not worth it.", "hours": 22.9, "user_id": "76561198018642305", "username": "\u24c8\u24c9\u24b9 vupe", "products": 369, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-17", "text": "Do I recommend this game? As you can see from my rating, no.\nDo I think you should still play it though? I suppose so. I, for one, do not like to play a sequel without having a chance at the original title that came before it.\nThis game is very well done overall for its time. The gameplay was unique and the features were different. The combat mechanics were different than anything I had ever seen before but lead to a very slow moving game in the long run. It is the moving mechanics that frustrates me the most. It is difficult, at least with a keyboard, to navigate the narrow alleyways while running at top speed. The character occasionally bumps into a wall and tries to climb it. When you are being chased by enemies this can be extremely infuriating.\nThe beauty of this game though is the story that it brings. While it isn't particularly the best story I have seen, it is very unique and leads directly into the sequel which is why I think you should still play this one in order to understand the sequel or at least watch a gameplay walkthrough so you can understand what is going on.\nI played this on Windows 10 and found it to be very buggy and crashed on occasion. This game is DX10 I believe which was one of the worst APIs Microsoft ever built. Coincidentally making its debut on Vista, one of the worst OSs they built. I tried running this game in Vista compatibility mode but the crashes never went away. I had to play through the ending 3 times just to defeat the final boss and watch the final cutscenes without crashing.\nI am glad I forced my way through it so I could experience the story and move on to the sequel but I didn't enjoy it overall and was more relieved when I finished it just because I didn't have to play it ever again.", "hours": 16.5, "username": "acdcdave1387", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-16", "text": "This is where it all began.\nThe game has definitley aged a lot, and you can see that. The graphics are sub-par for this day and age. The quests are very repetitive. The mechanics are very clunky. But, when this game was released, it was cutting edge. It helped define RPG games that came after it.\nIf you can look past that this is an old game, I highly recommend it. Or, if you haven't played an Assassin's Creed game before, you need to play this one. This is where the series started.", "hours": 19.6, "username": "TheForFeeF", "products": 122, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-16", "text": "The game that made Ubisoft.\nGame of the Year Awards (1962-present):", "hours": 3.1, "username": "CULT|icycalm", "products": 849, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-15", "text": "Only downside: lack of a true open world.", "hours": 3.6, "username": "Gun Squared", "products": 361, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-13", "text": "A must play for the ones who wants to follow the story.\nIf your only looking for a game to play without having the franchise in mind, i would not recommend it. Its outdated.\nI recommend playing it only to be Immersed with the story.\n5/10 for gameplay\n9/10 for immersion with the Assassins creed franchise", "hours": 25.7, "username": "Balos", "products": 305, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-06-11", "text": "I was stuck on the last boss for so long. He oneshot me every time. Then i realised i had to throw a knife at him to get my life back. Anyway this game is great, it challanges your timing in attacks and blocks. 9/10", "hours": 40.0, "username": "\u2655 El Hugo \u2655", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 35, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-06-09", "text": "I love the Assassin's Creed games but the first one was deathly boring to me. The plot/script feels very rushed and the gameplay is totally barebones compared to any of the sequels. If you're new to the Assassin's Creed games, I'd reccomend starting with AC II and then learning about Altair's story by playing AC: Revelations.", "hours": 12.7, "username": "THE SCREW OF DAMNATION", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
