{"product_id": "15100", "page": 42, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-04-01", "text": "For me I did not enjoy this game that much. This game has an okay story but it is so repetitive. \"Go to that city, assassinate the guy there, good now go back to master and tell him.\" The combat is plain awful and I did not say it was hard it was the fact that you just do everything in a repetitive way that you get so bored of it. I mean you can not expect that much from a 2007 game overall a 5/10", "hours": 16.1, "user_id": "76561198138156912", "username": "ButterMelon", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 42, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-31", "text": "Many regard this as a \"beta\" to what AC would become. It's partly true, but don't believe this is unfinished in any way.\nAC1 is short and straight to the point. It's going to upset you a little sometimes due to the repetition and a little grind, but on average it's a very entertaining experience, dark and gritty in a way that no other AC matched to this day.\n8 out of 10/ 4 out of 5. If you are a fan of the series, buy it already. If not, try it - the general taste should be enough to let you decide whether the rest is worth it,", "hours": 4.1, "user_id": "76561198039040311", "username": "Enriador", "products": 86, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 42, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-31", "text": "Awesome. one of the best assassin's creed games (after number 2).", "hours": 17.0, "user_id": "76561198273645312", "username": "BenMin0", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 42, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-31", "text": "Great game. Honestly though, I wouldn't recommend buying it at full price. Wait until it's on sale. It does connect with AC2 but if you skip this game and go straight to 2, you're honestly not missing much. You might be a little confused with the story but as you progress you'll get the gist. If you like to feel immersed in the story as I do, I recommend buying it but buy it on sale. If you're just looking to purchase an Assassin's Creed game, I'd say go with AC2 or Black Flag.\nThe character does not move fluidly. You'll find yourself jumping to the wrong thing, trying to run up a wall where you should've grabbed the ledge, not climbing onto the roof where you should be able to, getting out of a hiding spot only to find yourself climbing onto the edge of the hiding spot, sometimes you'll refuse to climb onto a viewpoint. The missions are repetitive. You do the same thing in every city in every chapter while the cities mostly look the same. The main characters voice is absolutely terrible. Comming from the Holy Land, you would think a dude named Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad would have a middle eastern accent as ezio has an italian accent. NOPE, you're a white dude.\nIf you don't care about feeling immersed, read the wiki on ac then skip to ac2 and go from there.", "hours": 6.4, "username": "stink", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 42, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-03-31", "text": "It keeps crashing. Whenever it crashes, you should restart the game and replay from far checkpoint.\nAlso it has no subtitle. Seriously?", "hours": 12.6, "username": "Yukirin", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 42, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-30", "text": "A exciting and compelling game that retells history through the eyes of the developers. Assassins Creed tells a story of a young assasisn trying to redeem himself, and learn to be a true assassin while trying to stop the templars from world domination. The game even after a decade still stands to the test of time, and the graphics have aged well, and pushes the newest laptops to their limits.\nAs a assassin you are able to run rooftop to rooftop using freeruning skills.\nPRO:\n1. Good Story\n2. Plenty to do\n3. Aged Well\nCON:\n1. Graphics are difficult to run\n2. No subtitiles\n3. Repetitive and very long", "hours": 13.0, "user_id": "76561198036333438", "username": "jgray13", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 42, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-30", "text": "Note: First time ever playing assassin's creed, so my views will be based around that.\nThe game as a whole was great. It wasn't incredibly easy, but not very hard either. The parkour was fun but frustrating occasionally due to clunkiness that ended up costing me a life or two.\nThe controls and combat in the game are very unique and different from most other games, which I liked. I felt like an assassin and I definitely had to think about each move I was making or I could end up regretting it.\nThe story was fantastic, and I could definitely understand Al-Tair's feelings. Him, as a person, changed throughout and became a completely different person at the end.\nOverall, I would give this title a 7/10. It was incredibly fun, but it was repetitive in the long run and had a clunky parkour system. Thankfully, the game is short so it doesn't drag on for long.", "hours": 26.8, "username": "[ Scarlet Red ]", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
