{"product_id": "15100", "page": 44, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-03", "text": "I have a few gray hairs from all the time I put into trying to find all the flags.  I couldn't even find all the Masyaf flags, and there are only a couple dozen of them.  Seriously, what kind of self respecting Knight Hospitaller leaves a flag in the middle of a plank that connects the roofs of two buildings?\nOverall, I love this game, the community is awesome (one of the best communities I know that's centred around a video game) and the graphics are really good (considering that it's about 10 years old at this point).", "hours": 109.1, "username": "Jeanne de Clisson", "products": 46, "found_funny": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 45, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-03-01", "text": "A very difficult recommendation because the game is falling apart at it's seams on newer hardware, but it's still a recommendation none the less.  It's a very fun game, it has a decent story, Altiar seems very bland from his monotoned voice and you don't really see his face much under the hood, but he has extremely good dialogue and character development.  It hasn't aged well, it was extremely innovative for it's time, however, we've seen these innovations recycled ever since and done better making the game's world just feel extremely dated.  Also, while the futuristic parts of the game can be quite interesting, they're kinda shoehorned in the game worst than any other entry in the series, or at least before ACIV, especially with the ending.", "hours": 19.7, "username": "FreelanceXD", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
