{"product_id": "15100", "page": 45, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-02-24", "text": "So, I started the series with the second part, after people told me it was much better and I loved the second part. So I couldn't resist getting the first one in a sale. But I honestly cannot recommend it. It's the most repetitive game in existence.", "hours": 7.3, "user_id": "76561198016960112", "username": "ln(t)", "products": 24, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 46, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-20", "text": "Never having experienced the historical adventures of Assassin's Creed, and desperate to fill my Prince of Persia void, I plunged into Assassin's Creed: Black Flag a few years ago, and was instantly enamoured. Even the first title in the series, while not as streamlined graphically, still gives such a great feeling of freedom and action, and goes one step further with its detailed exploration of various organisations like the Templar. Great game. Captures the spirit of action-adventure perfectly.", "hours": 5.2, "username": "ShovelKnight49", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 46, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-02-18", "text": "Total Score:  65/100, C+ (Stabby McStabmuffin)\nGraphics and Art:  9\nSound and Music:  8\nStory and Plot:  7\nControls:  5\nCreativity and Uniqueness:  7\nMood and Immersion:  7\nLength, Content, and Replayability:  7\nFunctionality:  7\nCharacter Choice and Customization:  3\nChallenge:  5\nHave you ever had that dream where you're being chased by someone?  Well, now you can play that dream!  This is a game about running, climbing, jumping, being chased, hiding, and then finally you realize the truth - it's just way faster to stop and kill everyone chasing you than it is to run away in the first place.  I'm not exactly sure if this is what the creaters intended, but it's cathartic all the same.  All the same, this is a fun little game with a pretty-good plot (you won't really care about any of the characters, and the main character is only kinda interesting...his artificial arc definitely isn't going to leave you on the edge of your seat...so just get back to the stabbing).  As a \"stealth\" game, it comes a little short because it really isn't that except for the fact that you do kinda surprise people by suddenly stabbing them, then walking away (spoiler alert!).  (I mean, that would be surprising unless you live in like New York or Chicago or Detroit or LA where you kinda expect random people to do this.)  As a console port, the controlls are hillariously wonky to the point of comedy, when your character alternates being being a master acrobat to being the most clumsy creature in the world, seemingly at random.  The fighting is pretty much the same.  This game does have some silly camera tricks, though it (generally) sometimes avoids annoying angles, unless you are fighting.  It has automatic checkpoints, but the saving isn't really a big deal, and it tends to save every time you need it to.  This isn't a difficult game, at all, but I think it's supposed to be all about the ride.  It CTDs very rarely, but it's nothing to worry about.  Overall, it's a better than average ride, all things considered.  Oh, yeah, I got all the flags and templars, which takes like a million hours, and do you know you get exactly NOTHING for so doing.  Oh, yeah, ignore the flags and templars, unless you hate yourself :|", "hours": 59.3, "username": "apophis13", "products": 556, "early_access": false}
