{"product_id": "15100", "page": 50, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-01-16", "text": "Assassin's Creed Review:\n11 hrs completion time\n5/10\nWith a weak and predictable storyline mediocre graphics, repetetive side objectives and repetition of missions it was a bland experience that I struggled to get through. Coupled with the problems in the fighting system such as not being able to block properly as the game chooses when it wants to block plus \"free run\" mechanics randomly choosing also where to jump randomly I have jumped straight through buildings into a haystack instead of climbing.\nWith no real variations in cities apart from cultures shifting from Arabic to European the objectives and citizens stayed all the same with only changes to clothing but voice work remained the same.", "hours": 15.3, "username": "Matex600", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 50, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-15", "text": "I believe this game is fun overall, there are buts thow. The free running and combat can be slow and becoming very boring and annoying. The side-activities become slightly repetive but enjoyable all the same. The main story is excellent, being able to play as an assassin during the crusades is awesome and also a bit educational. This game may have its ups and downs but i highly recommend you play or at least give it a try.", "hours": 21.2, "user_id": "76561198353581870", "username": "TheIronGambit", "products": 19, "early_access": false}
