{"product_id": "15100", "page": 53, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-02", "text": "Here's what I think about th game :\nGood story (Like other assassin's creed games)\nFine fighting mechanics (\"Fine\" because I cannot counter enemies' attacks sometimes for whatever reason)\nSure there's no ships to ride like assassin's creed 3, 4, rogue, syndicate and no shops to buy equipment but the cool thing is that you get equipments, upgrades, and abilities (such as dodge, break defense, counter attacks) as the story progresses on.\nWell, the only con I could think about is that you can't skip cutscenes but the cutcenes are kind of interesting to see. (probably for the people who loves history anyway)\nWell to the conclusion of playing this game for almost 14 hours now, the thing that I can conclude is that this game is good and it's worth it.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "Yer Kurua | \u272a NJ", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 53, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2017-01-02", "text": "Assassin's Creed. A decent first entry to a great franchise. This game is a solid 6/10 for me\nPros:\n-Great story.\n-Good characters.\n-Good graphics (for its time)\n-Great combat and parkour\nCons:\n-The gameplay gets VERY repetetive after a few missions. Basically doing the same stuff over and over again with minor changes.\n-There is little to no replay value due to its repetetivity and the fact that there are FAR superior entries to this franchise\n-No subtitles\nOVERALL:\nThis game isn't a must-have, not even for fans of the franchise, but it's cheap, so it's worth it", "hours": 13.9, "username": "\u00d8rjan", "products": 176, "early_access": false}
