{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-07", "text": "*Friend* How is the studying to exam going??\n*Me* I'm about to kill the leader of the assassins who are actually a Templar!\nAnyway, for those of you who are wondering if i failed the exam, no i did not. i saved my progress and hope to continue next year. (;_;)\nThis game is the first in the Assassin's creed series and that shows with weird controls and repetetive gameplay and no proper cutscenes. However, that doesn't mean it's bad. No, i actually enjoyed every second of it. the story is very slow at first and you have to play an hour or so to understand why you have gone back in time to play as your great great great x100 great grandfather Alta\u00efr. who would much rather do a triple backflip on to a house that's 10 miles away and turn into a warewolf every third Thursday at full moon when Jupiter is right behind the sun's core and listen to Kanye SouthWest's new album than do leap of faith.\nthis was my first time playing a assassin's creed game and i absolutely fell in love with this series. the ai have funny dialogs and i can easily spend an hour listening to them. there are so many different people that do different things. it makes this world seem real like this is what people did in those times when your parents were young and did not have phones or PCs\nBUT!!! if i meet one of those women who wants money one more time, i swear i will..... ohhhh!!! yeah i \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing hate them.\nThe story, OMG. one of the main reasons i bought every single assassin's creed game there is. the story makes it 10 times more fun to play. i played blackflag for 20 min before i played this game and i didn't know why i went back in time or what they said about templars and assassins\ni would recommened this game to anyone who's new to assassin's creed games, for those of you who have played the newer ones it might be hard to get used to the controls but i would still recommened it for the story.\nPS: i know this review is a mess. first time trying to do a proper review, give me some mosquito spray please!!", "hours": 15.6, "user_id": "76561198058641860", "username": "Taco Bell", "products": 257, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-07", "text": "A truly new and fresh game back in the days, where parkour meets pseudo - historic fights with evil templars.\nThat game was a really nice distraction from most of the stuff released back then. But what it has to offer now?\nFirst of all this is really part of trilogy (pentalogy?) depicts a story of one guy, named Desmond Miles, snatched by some organization, locked in a room and forced to relive past lives of his ancestors in search for... Well that would be a spoiler, so I let You to find out.\nGame take place in two different places, one being today reality and second in middle ages Holy Land. While present offers some background story of Desmond and his story, the Animus part is where the fun really happens. You're an Assassin named Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad, sent by Your order to kill cartoonishly evil templars in attempt to free Holy Land from their grasp. Alta\u00efr also slowly reveals their true purpose there and his job became one of finding something hidden through generations... Overall story is pretty good and makes almost no effort in captivating player.\nNow little about gameplay - it is a third person perspective, where You're allowed to climb almost every building in game. Unfortunately the climbing itself is a little clunky, but if You can grind Your teeth a little, You will get satisfaction quickly. Apart from this there is some horse riding, running on rooftops and many fights. Alta\u00efr slowly gets better weapons and means to fight more enemies at once, without dying. Fights themselves are pretty spectacular, with many different finishers and moves, depending on weapons used. They are also pretty intuitive, if one learn their moves.\nMain quests are done very good, but side quests are really boring and repetetive, and that is very unfortunate, as they do very little to expand the story, and they can be just ignored.\nWhile game aged a little, some vistas still are magnificent. Animations of fights are done very good too. You will notice that many building looks the same, but that can't be avoided in a game that big and somewhat complex. Overall graphics are pretty good.\nDo I have to tell You that the preferred way to do that is by playing with a controller? No, I think not.\nP. S. Remember - water is Your most deadly enemy, and You can't counter it;)", "hours": 22.4, "username": "Paul von Nod", "products": 836, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-06", "text": "Being an assassin sounded cool, but in practice I thought this game was drab and dull. Almost nothing about the story made any sense at all, and was an incoherent mess. You can only climb to the top of a building and jump off into a pile of hay so many times before you begin to lose interest. For me, that took about 8.7 hours.", "hours": 8.7, "username": "Bod", "products": 243, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-06", "text": "Great start of one of the greatest (in my opinion) series of all time.", "hours": 16.7, "username": "S P A G H E T", "products": 188, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-05", "text": "Its a cool concept, but the game is just a borefest.  You keep doing the same things over and over and over.  I remember playing this on PS3 upon release and I didn't like it then either.  Thought I would try again at a friend's insistence and well, it still sucks.  Plus I hate the controls.", "hours": 7.2, "user_id": "76561198093363183", "username": "Smackm0nk3y", "products": 464, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-04", "text": "One of the more boring Assassin's Creed for me, but it was still a blast.", "hours": 49.7, "username": "Elijah", "products": 83, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-04", "text": "If you're even a little limited on time & patience and you just want to play this to get a complete story experince from AC series. I suggest to go on youtube and watch a clip which gets the story in 5-60 mins. If you have time and are determined to complete the whole series storyline this is fine. Just don't pay the full price for it.\nFor a game made 2007 graphics, enviroment and sounds are suprisingly good, of course there is issues with e.g. drawing distance but they couldn't think that someone really plays this with a 2016 high-end machine. Main storyline is fine.\nPC gameplay is awful and the game gets easily pretty boring. Bad contrallability, clumsy combat, no quicktravel, tens of repeating and similiar mini-quests before you get to the real main quest and and such a stupid AI.\nI don't recommend this unless you are obsessed to get all the games in the series finished (or if you're unemployed)\nPros:\n+Graphics (2007)\n+Story\n+Sounds\nCons:\n-Graphics (2007)\n-Gameplay (horrible character & camera controllability, clumsy repeating combat, etc.)\n-Repeating repeating repeating", "hours": 7.0, "user_id": "76561198101191956", "username": "Reddy", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 60, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-04", "text": "Best game in the franchise!!!", "hours": 17.0, "username": "The Iron Son", "products": 682, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-03", "text": "An absolutely fantastic, one of a kind, unique game... if you play it with HUD turned off. I explain it in detail here:\nBut the short gist of it, AC1 was clearly designed to be played without a HUD (except some of the missions that were added in the PC version, they didn't take HUD-less design into account), and it provides a whole different experience. As an example, you're not going to an eavesdrop icon to listen to a minute of conversation and that's it, mission done. You're going to the Jewish Quarter because that's where the Rafiq told you there might be information, and you find the Jewish Quarter by seeing in the distance the Star of David on a gateway, while you're on the rooftop, and then you explore and use your Eagle Vision to see who knows something.\nAs soon as the HUD is introduced, a lot of this is lost, and the cyclic nature of the game is seen (which is why a lot of people call the game repetitive, because HUD makes the cyclic nature obvious, but without it you NEED it to learn patterns and to investigate what's out of the pattern).\nEven if you've played and like the game already, but have never played it with HUD fully off... do it. It won't be a perfect HUD-less experience on PC (mainly because, as I mentioned, new PC missions don't take HUD-less design into account, but you can ignore those because not every mission is required for game completion), but it will still be great and unique.", "hours": 46.4, "user_id": "76561198049790538", "username": "Farlander", "products": 563, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-02", "text": "Absolutely fantastic game. Pick it up when it's on sale. You won't regret it. (Make sure you have a controller, though. Trying to play this thing with a keyboard is ridiculous)", "hours": 15.0, "user_id": "76561198051625850", "username": "markhaskell95", "products": 22, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-02", "text": "no subtitle.\nAs non-english speaker it's very helpful if there are subtitle especially when character have certain accent.\ngraphic is better than first release.", "hours": 23.7, "username": "aczeir", "products": 18, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-12-02", "text": "Nice gameplay, it's actually fun, but:\n- after a while you realize you're always doing the same things over and over\n- the game is not perfectly optimized for pc. You lose the full screen mode if you switch to another app and come back\n- the controller is not completely integrated.\n- there are no subtitles\n- the camera works often very bad, going behind walls or plants.\n- there are no achievements like on Xbox or PS3, which means taking all the flags or killing all the templars is completely useless", "hours": 32.5, "username": "Giant Lizard", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-12-02", "text": "Its really nice but i dont like these Beggar and Psychopaths there just annoying -.-.", "hours": 16.7, "username": "Butterzwerg", "products": 343, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-30", "text": "This is where it all started.  The first game in the amazing series that we now know would have it's ups and downs.  This game plays very differently than the other games.  At first it appears that you are just a grunt in the faction of Assassins.  We would later find out in a future game that you are not just a regular person in this game.  You are perhaps the most important assassin present.  The gameplay still holds up as the core mechanics of the game haven't really changed much.  If you're looking to play through the series and you want to know if you should skip this game, you should not.  It's a great game that will make you want to play more.", "hours": 26.2, "user_id": "76561198047868578", "username": "jcbvickers", "products": 219, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-30", "text": "A very old game with fun gameplay and very difficult controls. The missions and the environment are interesting, i found myself staring at cities and landscapes quite often. The two interchanging stories Desmund and Altiar add to the game and gives a bit of the complex lore too.\nThe combat is challenging, taking some practise and control tinkering to get used to, the two 'stances' make things difficul wich later games don't configure wich means you have to get used to it.\nOne bad thing, once you complete a memory block, you cannot continue playing then choose to go to the next, it forces you to so you can't complete secondary objectives if you missed any wich i found quite annoying when i realised it.", "hours": 3.3, "username": "Zed", "products": 107, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-30", "text": "I would rate this game 7.5/10, because the storyline is very fun overall, but there are some issues. The campaign can be boring or slow at times, as it gets repetitive, but it's never a huge issue. My main problem with this game is that the PC port is terrible! I haven't had any issues with crashes but there are constant glitches through the game, such as death during the leap of faith jumps, or enemies flying all over the place/off the screen when hit. My character has also experienced these glitches, flying all over the place when knocked down or othewise hit. I've had to play through the final boss battle 3 times because of these issues. Also, the controls are a bit stupid, and don't always work as they should, with the wrong moves being carried out, enemy blocks missed, etc. Overall it's a fun game but be prepared for some stupidity.", "hours": 29.9, "user_id": "76561198143351053", "username": "Juicy_Jay", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-29", "text": "one of the best story lines i have ever seen in a game series", "hours": 16.7, "username": "SneakyFatMan", "products": 304, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 61, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-29", "text": "I'm only writing a review for the steam awards. I loved this franchise but for real it's had too many sequels. Let it die.", "hours": 14.1, "username": "iDracarys", "products": 61, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 62, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-11-28", "text": "Assassin's Creed\nUbisoft's most interesting project gone successful.\nIf you want to Play Assassin's Creed games start with this one. Its way better and Confusionless.\nThe Graphics are great, the Background Music is awesome during combat.\nClose Quarter combat system is awesome and the most important thing Free Running is great, not awesome but great.\n100% Recommended.", "hours": 13.2, "username": "Izhaaq996", "products": 233, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
