{"product_id": "15100", "page": 65, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-11-20", "text": "This, right here, is an example of a bad port. It plays great on the X360, even if the controls take a little getting used to. But on the PC? It's just plain unintuitive. Half the time I played it with a remote, I had to use my mouse and controller anyway because the program decided \"Not today.\"\nAlso, I got Shadow of Mordor after playing this\nAssassin's Creed 4: Black Flag. Shadow of Mordor is a far superior game to both in my mind. The combat feels better, the atmosphere is more clear in where it wants to be, and the story feels like more of an assassin game. Assassin's Creed feels more like \"Pride's Blunder: Climb Back Up the Ranks\"\nUpdate: Does not work with XB1 remotes.", "hours": 27.1, "username": "Tenthadorn", "products": 134, "early_access": false}
