{"product_id": "15100", "page": 68, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-02", "text": "Just as good as the first time back in '08. Gameplay is repetitive with only 3 main cities (Damascus, Acre, Jerusalem) and your home base (Masyaf), but the story's what drives the experience.\nThe gameplay itself can be (very) glitchy at moments, especially when free running; your weapon arsenal isn't as extensive as the other games, but it does the job wonderfully; there're no negative drawbacks to not being stealthy, so be as crazy as you want. These things don't detract from the enjoyment of the game, but can be frustrating when you have to escape after assassinating your target. This is a series in its infancy, we all know where it goes from here with the numerous added enhancements and features.\nGraphics-wise it's held up quite well; the environments still look gorgeous and the attention to detail for both the cities and history still fascinates me to this day. The audio, on the other hand, is alright for the main characters and targets, but is recycled for the NPC townsfolk and you can hear the compression in some of the dialog. This is a port, so it's understandable.\nDespite the minor glitches and audio complaints, I still highly recommend this game to veterans of the series and those who have never played the series before. Experience the ongoing, generational struggle of the Assassins against the Templars. Become one with the Brotherhood. Live the Creed.", "hours": 20.2, "username": "Paradoxicles", "products": 546, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 68, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-02", "text": "Files not Saved on SteamCloud/UbiCloud!", "hours": 5.4, "username": "DDay Judgement!!!", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 68, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-10-01", "text": "The best setting of the AC series IMO.  Still I can't really recommend buying this one unless you want to play through all the AC series or just want to look at ancient middle eastern cities from on high.  The original game is monotonous, even though it is pretty short, and the ending is rather confusing because you aren't really sure if you are actually done.  But don't judge the entire series based on this game as the rest of them have much better gameplay.", "hours": 34.1, "username": "TJTaylor", "products": 414, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 68, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-10-01", "text": "Kind of like the first Mass Effect, it's not the best in the series, and it has aged, but still a solid game. Story is rough in certain parts. Even so, the gameplay is so fun it's a testament to its power as a series.", "hours": 1.6, "username": "bluecuban", "products": 336, "early_access": false}
