{"product_id": "15100", "page": 69, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-09-18", "text": "It's interesting that back in the middle ages not a single person knew how to swim. Seriously though...why was it so hard to implement a swimming function in AC1?", "hours": 34.6, "user_id": "76561198156238225", "username": "Rexhiboy", "products": 10, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 69, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-09-17", "text": "I will start with pre-game.\nU cant even play it through steam it crushes all the time.\nDynamics are really bad it made me sick sometimes.\nAfterall, this is the first game of a legend serie.\nSo, it worth buying when its on sale. Otherwise, dont buy it.\nGood story, no subtitle hard to understand if u r not really fluent in English.", "hours": 5.1, "username": "mSt", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 69, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-16", "text": "This is the first installment of the series I've played and it's a good introduction so far. The game is well-made for PC and runs very well. The controls are a bit meh, only because they made it with consoles in mind first. It still plays well, it's just that they're console-y. Hopefully the issues with Unity are resolved, as I plan on buying the rest of the games and playing them in order.", "hours": 21.5, "username": "[Ratchet Miles]", "products": 345, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 69, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-11", "text": "A great start to the franchise. It gets repetitive, but it has a great story.\n8/10", "hours": 30.0, "username": "Paco91", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 69, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-11", "text": "Where it all began. Honestly it's a very good, genre-defining game, if a bit repetitive. The gameplay can get quite tiresome towards the middle stages of the game but it's not THAT monotonous as some make it out to be. The storyline is, in my opinion, among the most interesting from any AC game and it served as the basis for many of the games that were to come. I would not say it's a mandatory title in the franchise, but a strongly recommended one. After all these years, it's aged more than well.", "hours": 27.8, "username": "\u0418\u0432\u0430\u043d", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 69, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-11", "text": "The Classic, completed it ages ago 100% finding all that could have been found with my wife! However if you wish to play the best AC game, get AC II :)", "hours": 41.6, "username": "Shaman", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 69, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-10", "text": "11/10 one of the best games Assassins Creed games.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "\u272a Moop", "products": 66, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-09", "text": "I've about finished the game, the story that is, and i enjoyed the main story even though it did get a bit repetative but anyway this is what I thought of it:\nPros - Good Main story line\n- Gameplay was fun enough to ignore the graphics which were a bit outdated but not unplayable\n- The characters were more interesting than other assassin's creed games\n- Good ending\nCons - The side quests can be a bit laborious\n- It can get repetitive towards the end because your basically doing the same thing 9 times\n- The options are a bit lackluster as there isn't even a fullscreen setting you have to press ALT+ENTER to go back into fullscreen after tabbing out\nAll in all I think its a good game and is worth buying just put aside the the small problems.\n8.2/10", "hours": 12.6, "username": "Roke", "products": 111, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-06", "text": "It's another Assasins Creed game, this time, something.", "hours": 2.8, "user_id": "76561197970701643", "username": "Liam Neeson Punching Wolves", "products": 1160, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-05", "text": "This is where everything with assassin's creed began. Is definielty my favorit one. Comparing to others assassin's creed you have less different stuff you can do but the place where it is played is well done. Especially masyaf, I was climbing to the highest point and looking around the mountains. It's stunning and wouldn't have move for awhile just enjoying the view but the game progress won't do itself.", "hours": 100.6, "user_id": "76561198151225506", "username": "Apocalypto_ch", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-02", "text": "The worst exit game navigation in history.\n6/10", "hours": 1.6, "username": "RangerX3X", "products": 234, "found_funny": 9, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-09-01", "text": "Finally got around to play Assassin's Creed! Even though it's from 2008 the graphics still hold up quite well, however the side quests can make the game a little bit monotonous. I didn't really cared about them (I'm not a completionist) so I just played the main missions, with the narrative keeping me wanting to play the game so I guess it didn't suck that bad?\nBetter to play in short periods of time (~1h-2h) so you don't get tired of it and give up.\n\u27a1\ufe0f\ufe0fFinal Rating: 7/10", "hours": 13.9, "username": "Godciaz", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-09-01", "text": "So recently I decided to marathon all the Assassin's Creed games available on PC and 100% complete them. This one I didn't 100% complete but I did do the story and some side stuff. Here are my honest thoughts on just the game itself, if you were to buy it now.\nPros:\n-Interesting story line in and out of the Animus.\n-Combat can be quite satisfactory and challenging.\n-Is not too easy.\n-The locations are quite cool and interesting.\n-Desmond.\nCons:\n-Graphics are very outdated which is unsurprising seeing as how old it is.\n-Gameplay is very repetitive (do some spying then kill your target). 9 times.\n-Freerunning is quite slow and clunky, but not too bad.\n-Cutscenes are very dull, boring and overwinded.\n-Voice acting isn't great especially from Altair.\n-Altair is quite a boring character with no spirit.\n-Being stealthy is very dull, pointless and sometimes very hard.\nOverall, if you want to have some fun with a one off game then DO NOT BUY THIS, unless maybe it's on sale. There are much funner games for \u00a310. If, however, you want to start the AC games from the beginning and understand it all like me then buy it, but do know IT IS NOT NEEDED! You can easily start from AC 2 and not really miss much as that is a much better game!", "hours": 14.9, "username": "Tim the Enchanter", "products": 50, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-30", "text": "For an almost 10 year old game it still holds up to this day and is definitely worth picking up if you've never played an Assassin's Creed game before.\nThe game tells a story of Desmond Miles - a descendant of Assassins - a secret organisation fighting with Templars. While Assassins strive to preserve freedom - Templars seek to control people. Desmond who lives in modern times is put by Templars into Animus with which he can access genetic memories of his ancestors and re-lives the events happening in the third crusade times.\nThe game is very atmospheric. The cities you visit during the game are big and extremely atmospheric. It really does feel like a crusader movie. The movement - ability to climb any building, run on the rooftops is very well done. The whole scope of the game does look impress. For the times this was released it is very impressive. Even today it still looks very good and holds its own.\nDuring the game you will kill a number of templars. And while all the tools seem to be present the game feels a bit repetitive. Each mission follows pretty much the same schematic - follow someone and eavesdrop on conversation to learn something, beat someone up, pickpocket someone else. In the end it does not affect the main mission much though. With additional Ubisoft dis tractors - climbing towers to reveal map and so on it's a completionist nightmare. Even more so that the side missions are even more repetitive than the core plot. The main missions at least vary from each other and are really fun to do.\nThe strength of this game lies within stealth. Blending with the crowd, picking routes to avoid detection to deal the final blow. When executed properly it's really satisfying. The combat is a bit too easy. All you have to do is wait for a queue to counter and you can fight off a hundred men.\nThe only problem I had was with an XBox controller which for some reason does not work well with the PC version of the game. And some keys are bound in a strange way without ability to re-bind them. Even using community fixes I couldn't get it to work exactly as it should.\nThe whole story of Desmond Miles is a bit weak - and personally I would prefer for it to be strictly about Altair.\nOverall the game still holds up - worth picking up and playing through.", "hours": 19.3, "user_id": "76561197997045080", "username": "agurczuk", "products": 921, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-30", "text": "Assassin's Creed before Ubisoft decided to recycle it for 300 years", "hours": 1.1, "username": "Suk Mike Hok", "products": 165, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-27", "text": "I never thought I'd like this series...My son bought me this game recently, I've just finished it today....Well now I have all the Assassin's Creed games that are available on Steam on my Wishlist. I can't wait until I get them all and try them out. Why didn't I try them out sooner.", "hours": 28.5, "user_id": "76561198126784295", "username": "mynamewastakenmore", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 70, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed is simply brilliant! The beginning of a fantastic series! Sure, it's pretty much the same\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665you do all the time, but i still find it very entertaining! The story is great, and Alta\u00efr is awesome.\nThe only problem is a \"Leap of Faith Glitch\" that i've encountered multiple times. You basically do the jumps as usual, but when you hit the haystack, you just simply die, which is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing annoying.\nBesides that, 10/10\n-EppeyX", "hours": 13.8, "user_id": "76561198171825706", "username": "Giuliana \"Bitconnect\" Dave", "products": 144, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-24", "text": "I started off by playing Assassin's Creed 2, staring Ezio Auditore. Safe to say when I went back to play the original Assassin's Creed, while I was impressed with the story line I was anything but with the actual game play. Objectives weren't clear, game controls were signifcantly different to the subsequent AC games, and certain aspects of the game simply didn't make sense like why the guards were constantly on high alert even though they have no idea what you look like and so have to shift around the game slowly while in the prescence of guards.\nSomething which also annoyed me was that our little protagonist can drown.... A (soon to be) Master Assassin can drown. Kind of takes away the magic.\nI found myself getting bored within 3 hours of game play and I have no drive to complete this game whatsoever. I regret buying this on the summer sale 2016, and I instead wish I had purchased Assassin's Creed Revelations so I could at least finish Ezio's story.\nJust avoid it.", "hours": 3.5, "username": "FireThief", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-23", "text": "-If landing in hay bales kills you enable vsync-\nEach game is like a story expansion of the one before it, with some extra new bits that sometimes are fun, but other times just get in the way. I'm glad they're taking a year off. They need it.\nThat said, this is one of my favorite series. Its like medieval GTA. The writing and story ideas I enjoy a lot. The first game will seem pretty bland if you've played anything newer. But I liked this era the most and Altair is my favorite.\nI'd say pick it up on a deal if you're iffy about something a little aged with some repeated aspects throughout the whole game. 20 is kinda steep. If you didn't play it way back when, it might be a tough fit. But I can't really bring myself not to recommend just out of enjoying the philosophy of it.", "hours": 74.6, "username": "Thrival Pariahtal", "products": 479, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-20", "text": "I write reviews only after I've defeated the game.\n10/10\nRich atmosphere.  Xbox controller support.  Amazing story.\n100% recommend.", "hours": 24.6, "user_id": "76561198089432204", "username": "McDuck", "products": 263, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-20", "text": "Best game! The original of the Assassin Creeds! I wonder if they will base the movie off this game? Or merge other games into the movie? Or just mess up the whole thing and make a whole new story for the movie?\nWell, in the meantime, you can enjoy playing the original Assassin's Creed!", "hours": 22.0, "username": "ResidentBilly", "products": 347, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-19", "text": "Best of the best", "hours": 12.9, "username": "Sanches1611", "products": 43, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-15", "text": "Great game, wish it had captions- but the rest of the AC games do so it doesn't matter, it's just one game. Definitely start with this game before playing the other games. It's really hard to go back and play this game when you've started on any of the others. It's an older game, and the AC series has improved A LOT since this game. You simply can't compare it to the other games, because it is the first one. Don't skip out on Altair's story. I love the character and the story. Just because it's an early game, there's not much to the open world. There's the basic storyline and that's it. Compare it to AC II, that has a massive open world and side quests. The first AC has no side quests really. That being said, I still don't think people should skip this game. It's a good start to an awesome series.", "hours": 32.0, "username": "heartofscylla", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-14", "text": "So 9 years after release, I finally played my first Assassin's Creed game ever.\nI never knew what was it all about, except that there is an assassin that kills stuff. I was very pleasently surprised by the story and plot - something new for me that I didn't expect.\nOne thing that I didn't like from start was how the character is controlled (I don't think it is very suitable for keyboard, ofc I can imagine this game was primarily made for consoles), but I got used to it after some time and had no further problem.\nStyle of gameplay was something completely new for me as well, I loved the roof action and how the cities were designed - there had to be a ton of work in just designing the environment. After some time I think I became pretty good at moving on the roofs and it was very enjoyable. Even interaction with crowd was very well done except 2 things that kept\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665me off for the whole game:\n1) the annoying begging women who at one point completely blocked you from moving and you had to push them - which caused me many many troubles considering there were alerted soldiers all around and these little \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665es just kept ruining my missions.\n2) the drunken dudes that were attacking and pushing you everytime you came close - one in time would be ok, but there were just too many of them.\nSome reviews criticize the monotony of game and that they got bored very fast - that was not my case. I was playing it continuously in the evenings for 1-2h/day max and I never got  bored. I enjoyed the continously increasing difficulty of combats, but to be honest I wasn't enjoying increasing difficulty of investigation missions - some of them were just ridiculous at the end.\nOverall I liked the game, the story and the gameplay mechanics and I will definitely continue with playing successors, but it's not the type of game I would play twice. Also I have met some bugs, but nothing game breaking.", "hours": 20.4, "username": "ThreeDots", "products": 106, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-13", "text": "For it's time, a groundbreaking game.  I really enjoyed it and have played through it 3 times now.  The last time modded out with updated graphics.\nThe storyline was the best part.  Some of the busy work isn't that bad since it was the first game in the series but they should have learned that gathering flags and feathers is a waste of time.  The following games improve on the story line but sadly they also continue the busy work side quests.  For people with OCD like me, this can be a nightmare because we want to complete the game in it's entirety.  If you can complete the mission without them, just ignore the side quests and go for story line.  It will be much more enjoyable.", "hours": 3.0, "username": "BadHello", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-13", "text": "I've started playing through all the \"old\" AC games again for nostalgic reasons I guess, and I can honestly say that you might as well skip this one unless it's on sale and you're a really big AC fan. A couple of issues with this game; The controls can feel very slow and clunky at times, especially when you're climbing towers (which you will be doing A LOT), the missions can get really repetitive pretty fast, walking through the streets and hearing people saying the same lines over and over again can get pretty annoying, same goes for the music when you get in a fight with a couple of guards, the vigilante missions where you help civilians feel like a chore and I got to the point where I just stopped giving a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665about them because there's absolutely no fun in doing them.\nI had to change and replace some of the game's files because the native controller support is worthless (AC2 has the same issue). It didn't take too long to fix it but it's something they could've easily patched in if they actually gave a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\nI also noticed at certain points the framerate seems to drop for no reason at all and there's nothing I could do about it.\nI liked the story and (most of) the actual main assassinations were pretty cool, but for 9,99 I would definitely skip this game. It was a great game for it's time but it hasn't aged as well as I had hoped. Again; if you're like me and you're trying to play through all the old AC games again, you might as well skip this one and start at AC2", "hours": 13.0, "username": "Yung Kromosome", "products": 291, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 71, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-13", "text": "It was a revolutionary game nowdays it is quite boring...", "hours": 16.1, "username": "\u00a1Light", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-12", "text": "It's been so long since I last played this game and remembered it like it was yesterday. Game is amazing which I would recommend if you want to understand the whole Assassin's Creed lineup.", "hours": 18.3, "user_id": "76561198148934658", "username": ".\u25cf.\u263bPORK\u263b.\u25cf", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-12", "text": "And here it is: the start of it all. This game is a great game. Not as good as most of the AC games that come after, but I recommend playing this one first!", "hours": 17.0, "username": "\u2720 The Italian Spaniard \u269c", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-11", "text": "it did not load at all for me", "hours": 0.3, "username": "You Have Failed This CIty", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-11", "text": "Quite interesting at first play. It is good for fans of this series.\nPros:\n- Free movement\n- Acrobatics/ parkour\n- Target kills\nCons:\n- No subtitles\n- After some time highly repetitive", "hours": 7.8, "user_id": "76561198018523777", "username": "Dorreah", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-08-10", "text": "The first thing you will notice are the vastly outdated graphics, which just hurt your eyes and are nothing like the trailers and the screenshots. Everything is downgraded as usual. However, this is not the biggest of surprises in the game industry these days, so in my generosity, it can be forgiven.\nWhat I and many others fail to understand is the concept of the game, for it simply isnt very well thought out before put into use. This is very obvious when you really start to understand the gameplay and try to execute the things you observe the game showing you, which eventually feels clunky, outdated and sometimes, unfortunately, even flat-out depressing.\nGameplay-wise, the game holds your hand almost all the time and it becomes really annoying, when you start to notice you have no real difference in the course of action. There are moments where you just feel completely lost and get annoyed at how everything doesnt quite fit together.\nThe controls dont feel fluid at all, and occasionally you feel like you're either stuck in the mud or glue, or the game intentionally was made hard and frustrating to control. Why would anyone want to offer the players of their game an experience like this?\nAnd what's really frustrating are the sounds. It's like someone literally wanted to hire one of the worst composers, voice actors and the sound designers for this kind of a game! Could it be simply a bad decision from the lead of this project or very, very dark humor from the entire team of the game developers? You decide!\nAnd dont even get me started on the AI. It's rather non-existent. Some games are famous for their silly bot-AI that keeps doing mistakes and failing at the only thing it was designed to do. The only difference between those games and this is that the AI here isn't even funny. It just wants to make you shout at it's actions in utter rage.\nThe performance of the game tends to be lackluster. Ive seen it perform badly on many different specs and machines, which cannot garner much respect, but at this point it doesn't really surprise, either.\nAll this could be fixed with at least a long, interesting story that would give content for your money and/or time, but it doesn't really offer either.\nWhen you thought it couldn't get any worse, the game has more bugs here and there, hindering your already non-existent progressing and sucking the last drops of joy out of the experience\nOn top of all of this, the game is insanely difficult to progress in. Everything has been made non-intuitive for the average gamer, to the point even hardcore difficulty masochists will find it unpleasant to experience.\nIt all makes you think: Where is the gaming industry heading these days?", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Basic Hoovy", "products": 37, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-09", "text": "Ilike That story", "hours": 12.1, "username": "Bike123", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-08", "text": "The game that started the AC franchise O_O.\nAwesome game, and it will always have a legendary place in all of the AC gamers out there, it is however not without flaws, and though i probably gave this a 9 when i first played it ages ago, it simply is not a 9 when i replayed not that long ago on my AC maraton.\nSo i guess it's a 8.5 if that exists.\nIt is however a MUST own and must play for those that are even slightly into Assassins Creed.", "hours": 13.7, "username": "MiniDude", "products": 477, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-07", "text": "This is where it all started. It's quite rough on the edges and after a while it starts being repetitive. You can almost feel like this was just a proof of concept. When AC first released, it sure was innovative, but it hasn't aged very well. If you don't really care about the story that much, you can safely just skip right to AC II.", "hours": 22.0, "username": "ELBuAR7o", "products": 310, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-07", "text": "Yeah this game is a modern classic but you're better off buying AC2 instead.", "hours": 40.4, "username": "f\u044f0z\u0454\u0418^G", "products": 425, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 72, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-08-06", "text": "If you are new to the franchise I'd recommend starting with AC2, however if you are already a fan, this is definitely worth picking up during a sale. This is the root of the franchise and has repetitive missions and flaws, but I really enjoyed seeing the completely different setting and it also is the most realistic AC to date imo and the assassins are really ruthless which was neat to see for once.", "hours": 59.6, "user_id": "76561198131313860", "username": "C01001010", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
