{"product_id": "15100", "page": 76, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "- good gameplay in 2007\n- good mission\n- good combat system\n- good assassination skill\n- i'm only\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665to\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and fight and I didn't play like the title of the game\n- they f^cked all\n- I f^cked them\n- yeah very simple game\n- just go out and kiss their\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665br>Tip: don't steath, just rambo", "hours": 15.1, "username": "\u0e56\u06e3\u06dc\u06e9Active!!!", "products": 190, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 77, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "Assassin's Creed does deserve to be acclaimed for its contributions to the stealth genre. From it's innovative exploration of environments, including the addition of parkour and tiered levels, to the simplicity and immediacy of it's control system (even if Altair sometimes runs into the wall rather than UP them!)\nNot only this but it's excellent for it's explorations of philosophy (albeit rather simply) and conflict of religion, by chosing the era of the Crusades, something it handled rather one sidedly (Christian's were very obviously evil, but did at least question the morality of the Assassin's and the protagonist himself).\nIn fact Altair is still one of the most memorable of the characters from the series, progressing from self-confident, narcissistic fool to more mature and conscientious assassin.\nUnfortunately the game did interrupt this progression with the annoying sci-fi sequences inbetween where we encounter Desmond, however I suppose he does form a viable narrative link to Ezio in the future games, so this annoyance can be somewhat overlooked...\nIt's still a good, easy game to play even now, with a narrative that will remain as timeless as a Dan Brown novel.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "Deisophia", "products": 631, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 77, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-06-30", "text": "The storyline really isn't that interesting compared to the Ezio trilogy or 3 or 4. The gameplay controls are super weird and don't make sense and the gameplay is very reptitive. First AC game I'vee not liked... would not recommend.", "hours": 4.5, "username": "dwhite", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 77, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-29", "text": "Have only heard others rave about this game and decided to get it during the steam sale.  It plays fine, the cities are a little redundent and the controls can be frustrating, but it's an older game so it's fine.\nThe issue I've been having is that it crashes every few hours, and after googling it this seems to be a common problem on newer PCs with win 8.  While normally I'd be okay with a slightly buggy game, when it crashes the game tends to set me back to the beginning of the memory block.  This is very frustrating because after getting through half of memory block 4, it crashed and sent me back to the first city.  I don't know if I want to finish the game now, only because the crashing tends to wipe my save.\nSo overall, a decent game, but it just doesn't work on my system very well.", "hours": 14.8, "user_id": "76561198017381769", "username": "Helvetica Black", "products": 44, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 77, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-27", "text": "playing this game will show how much AC games have gone far. though i'll admit this game shows that assassin creed wasn't very much a stealth game and was very combat based i enjoyed it. if you want an assassin creed game that can get challenging sometimes (should learn from this AC3) its highly recommended.", "hours": 24.6, "user_id": "76561198204568491", "username": "Erumbitarbo", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
