{"product_id": "15100", "page": 78, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-12", "text": "I started playing this game in 2016 after I completed AC2-ACRG and I feel like this is the best of the whole series. Of course the controls are classic and decent, but the main attraction is that Altair, of all main characters, presents the true faith of the Assassin's Brotherhood since he didn't started his path from some sort of passive tragedy or pressure of living. Altair and Shay are the characters whom I pay the most respect to.\nHighly recommended, even if simply for this belief.\nNothing is true, everything is permitted. Sometimes you win, sometimes you learn.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "twitch.tv/ami326", "products": 43, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 78, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-12", "text": "awesome <3", "hours": 7.8, "username": "Neem | Pudina \u2122", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 78, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-12", "text": "Good game overall even by today standarts\n+Graphics stil look good even nowadays\n+Music, Art , Setting\n+City varation - guards language , city style , beggars ,etc\n-Climbing bugs somehow got me raging like never before\n-Action repeating over and over again\n-Merely half\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665long to AC2\n-Character depth and magic is missing , even the main targets feel liked scraped noones\n-Well I\u00b4ve got to love the way you loose all your gear at the start of a new assassin game , apart from ac3 , there you play half of the game without it", "hours": 19.5, "username": "Senjougahara", "products": 458, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-11", "text": "\"Nothing is true; everything is permitted\"", "hours": 40.3, "user_id": "76561197983468005", "username": "GamerWolfOps", "products": 671, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-06-05", "text": "I tried to like it, but I'm constantly wrestling with controls, camera, and missing features modern games have (like fast travel, for example).\nControls are idiotic. You have to hold three damn keys just to sprint. Climbing things isn't too fun either, because the guy is really slow doing it and often he can't reach to climb and it takes you a second to realize that, because of his slowness. When you run to an edge of something, you just \"stare\" down instead of jumping or doing anything sensible. You have to press \"other hand\" control.\nThe reason for the mess with the controls is 'cause you have \"low profile\" and \"high profile\" modes. The low-profile mode is annoying as hell, however, because you move around like a snail. Same goes for some places like the Abstergo lab or some buildings: you can't sprint, you can only \"walk\" which takes forever.\nSpeaking of profiles, you have to actually use a horse to move around cities. I searched around whether there's a fast travel mode, and apparently there is, but not in all the places and you have to get to the edge of the map or something. Annoying. This means if you want to move at any appreciable speed, you have to \"gallop\" in high profile mode which, for some reason, makes every random dude with a sword want to kill you.\nNow, you may think me being on a horse and the dudes being on foot... I can just run away! What's the problem then? Well, the problem is one of the more annoying features of the game: the detection meter. Whoever thought it was an awesome idea for it to loudly beep should be fired. So, it beeps if you're in an area where you might get attacked. If you get detected, it starts to beep even louder. And if you run away? Hell, that thing will beep forever! You actually have to find a bush somewhere and jump into the bush and sit there for a minute just to shut that stupid beeper off\u2014no other reason; there's no one chasing you any more!\nSo for the last three hours, I feel like I've done nothing but wrestle with controls and get annoyed with the damned beeper.\nAs for the story, well, it may be a good one, but I already dislike the guy I'm playing as. He's a rebel in one sentence and submissive in another. He's all over the place and I don't want to be him.\nI don't recommend this outdated game.", "hours": 4.3, "username": "Zoffix Znet", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-06-04", "text": "The gameplay is clumsy and repetitive. The story is good in general but nothing extraordinary.", "hours": 20.7, "username": "BMNascimento", "products": 72, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-06-01", "text": "I came really really late to Assassins Creed. After hearing lots about it, I finally decided to give it a shot. I was actually pleasantly surprised. It wasn't anything groundbreaking, due to its age I guess, but it was an enjoyable way to pass the time. The menu system annoyed me a bit though, too many steps to exit the game for example.\n6/10", "hours": 19.3, "user_id": "76561197996314601", "username": "simonbrowne404", "products": 417, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-29", "text": "The original classic. Would highly recommend.", "hours": 7.3, "username": "Dyrenex", "products": 473, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-05-28", "text": "A very disappointing game.\nThis is the 3rd game I bought on Steam many years ago (2009) and had technical difficulties on my old PC so I left it on the backburner since.\nI finally got to play it past the tutorial and it was okay.\nThen I went for the second prey and it was the same. Then the 3rd prey...still the same.\nFinally the 4th prey...still no change.\nIt's always go there and climb all towers to get the map, do at least 1 activity then report to the bureau for some useless idle talk and finally hunt the target.\nControls are not great, characters not particularly interesting and the present time scenes are barely useful, especially considering how slow it all is.\nIn the end, interesting concept with a really nice presentation of its historical setting (a period / place not scene often in games) but terribly repetitive with no real incentive to wander around.", "hours": 7.7, "username": "Troll", "products": 2017, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-27", "text": "So here it is. The first, the one that started it all...and it's ongoing yearly (Or so) sequels and add ons.\nShort at sweet....for me one of the most overrated games EVER!....BUT, I will say that its actually quite fun and has a damn lot of atmosphere. It's the Batman Arkham assylum before there was one. Unfortunately, there's this huge open world which goes to waste, for the most part you go looking for flags and stuff....to what ends? Just to collect things with no reward?\nThis is why the sequels did so much better.\nRegardless, the story  is great, graphics are rather nice, even for an 8 year old game and sets the stage for the sequel, which in my opinion was a much better use of open world.\nI'll still recommend this though.", "hours": 14.4, "username": "Squatingtiger", "products": 415, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-24", "text": "Love this game", "hours": 5.1, "user_id": "76561198109669131", "username": "Gogi", "products": 524, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-23", "text": "Late review:\n7/10\nBesides the repetitive story and missions, the first Assassin's Creed is true to its story, you're playing as an Assassin after all during the year 1191? I forgot.. Theres no happy moments no friends to hang out with, Altair was a born and breed Assassin soon to be Master, your mission is to kill 12 targets your master has given you to redeem yourself.\nIts simple:\n- Gather intel\n- Plan\n- Assassinate your target\n- Get in.. Get out\nAssassins Creed 1 is True to its objective, theres a brotherhood and a Master something the rest of the sequels fail to understand. It's not an adventure game where the main protagainst goes on adventures its about the life of an Assassin.\nThe real reason why Assassin's Creed game story fails everytime is because of the \"Animus\", the game is nothing without the animus of course, but you don't get to see how the character lives you're constantly skipping through time, You don't know what your favourite Assasins food is? what his favoruite colour is? what his favourite weapon to use throwing knives? Sword? their opinion of the hidden blade.\nUbisoft releases a book of their game with more in-depth story and details, why can't they make the story of the book into their games...", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198061766308", "username": "Monkey King IlI", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 79, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-05-23", "text": "This game constantly freezes and im at a good 80 fps, it just randomly stops working and its bugging me\nIntel Duo Q6660\nR7 250\nNforce 680i LT\nThermal Take Armor Series Case w/ 250mm side fan\nKingwin 1000 watt fully modual power supply\n1TB Hard Drive Western Digital Blue Edition", "hours": 1.0, "username": "CraZy_Bed", "products": 21, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 80, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-23", "text": "Recommended for the story if you are into AC games.\nOpen world gameplay is quite repetitive.", "hours": 16.6, "username": "Ykcin", "products": 2802, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 80, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-23", "text": "despite the issues with repetitive gameplay, lack of subtitles and some bugs, Assassin\u2019s Creed I is the stepping stone, a necessary evil, for players to get hooked into a very deep narrative, which on its own turns this mediocre title into a worthwhile experience for most players that endured through its repetitiveness.", "hours": 11.1, "username": "Borba", "products": 3226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 80, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-23", "text": "Visually, Assassin's Creed was way ahead of its time.\nHowever, despite its great potential and the revolutionary combat system, the game suffers from VERY repetitive gameplay and missions, which are basically the same all the way through, only in different locations. The story is thrilling and delivers an acceptable beginning to the franchise.\nWorth a Playthrough! 08/10", "hours": 35.4, "username": "mk2305", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 80, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-22", "text": "The first in one of my favourite game series. Not so great in itself, but sets the scene for the games that follow it. Gameplay is a little repetitive, but I'd still say it's worth playing if you want to get the background for the series.", "hours": 27.6, "username": "Ishvii", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
