{"product_id": "15100", "page": 82, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-05-04", "text": "Tried for several hours over many attempts to get into this game. The gameplay is just tedious and the story isn't rewarding yet. No reason for me to keep slugging through it. The concept of recreating historical ancient cities is amazing. Just poorly implimented here. I've heard future games in the series make incrimental improvements, but i was never able to get excited about this franchise because this game was a bummer.", "hours": 7.9, "username": "MarkT", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 82, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-05-01", "text": "The first Assassin\u2019s Creed was a good game for its time but it definitely has not aged well. The good things about it is that it's a great addition for a die hard AC fan. You get to play as Altier and know his backstory before the other ancestors in the franchise.When this game was released, the environment was quite rich in innovative and the NPCs acted and reacted to your character realistically. For it\u2019s time, it was quite an achievement. However, the later games definitely are better than this one.\nI will list the cons.\n- Repetitive\n- Always have to select the Xbox controller setting every time you start the game.\n- Crashing\n- You have to use a mod to have your Xbox controller configured correctly.\n- There is no in game reward for collecting flags and killing templars except for bragging rights.\nI would definitely recommend playing this game after playing the later AC games just to see the back story and how the whole franchise started. The storyline is actually very good with twists and turns. However, if you aren't a big AC fan then you can go ahead and skip this one.", "hours": 41.2, "username": "Claritiel", "products": 491, "early_access": false}
