{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-24", "text": "Aweome game, would totally reccomend", "hours": 127.6, "username": "c\u00e2y c\u1ed9t xo\u1eafn", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-03-21", "text": "Assassin's Creed, The successor to Ubisoft's The Prince of Persia reboot series. Days have been better.\nLet me first start off with a few thoughts.\nDecent gameplay with a few issues here and there in regards to story pace and developement.\nThe story for the first game in the series was interesting but now its very......its a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing a mess.\nAnd the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 PC port, When I first played and beat this game, I was playing a on a rather \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 laptop but it got the job done. when I finally got me a nice desktop (that I would later upgraded with a some decent cost-effeint parts)\nThe specs towered over the receommended specs and yet I cannot replay this game can max seetings without crashing almost everything goddamn time.\nI tried several things (inlcuding the Direct X file trick but that didn't get me anywhere)\nThe sad thing is that this is the only mainline game in the series that does not force Uplay on you and yet I still cannot receommend this game because the crappy port. If it wasn't for that I would recommend this game easily. With that I say sadly No.  (Note if anyone has very other receommnedations to help me with my crashes issues I would very much like to hear them please and thank you.)", "hours": 36.0, "user_id": "76561198038996953", "username": "Agent X G3", "products": 254, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-21", "text": "/!\\ WARNING - THIS IS MORE OF A \"MEH\" RATING RATHER THAN A FULL APPROVAL /!\\\nAt the time, I found Assassin's Creed to be a somehow cool game. At first I felt immersed in the game's world, and I liked the parkour-type of gameplay.\nBut the issue is that the game gets very repetitive, very fast: find a tower, climb it, explore the city, do some unvaried missions, kill your target, repeat.\nOverall, I found the game to be more boring than entertaining, and I'm not afraid to say I played it mostly for the story rather than the gameplay itself.\nRating: 5.5/10 - A good idea with an interesting scenario, but not varied enough to be played again. The sequel is better in every way and form.", "hours": 5.2, "username": "Sagittarius", "products": 2099, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-03-21", "text": "Meh, pretty boring. I prefer the memories in the Assassin's creed revelations, they were far more interesting.", "hours": 3.3, "username": "Justinian I", "products": 73, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-20", "text": "Back in the day when this was released it was a wonderful exciting breath of fresh air that kept me coming back for more. a trait that eludes most games these days - it deserves a 9 out of 10 for being ahead of it's time and creating the birth of something special , untill AC 3 that is.", "hours": 8.3, "user_id": "76561198036004266", "username": "Acid-Man", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-19", "text": "The one that started all this Assassin Creed madness. Bad things first: side quests get repetitive and boring very soon, there is no variability there and it might actually make you think: that s all there is to it? But the overall story is decent, especially missions with killing your 9 targets are always different in interesting new places to look for assassination techniques. Plus the 3 big cities, Damascus, Jerusalem and Acre are nice fresh air to New York (in which 90% games are situated). Historical period of crusades is really something that is not seen so often.", "hours": 18.4, "user_id": "76561198012833532", "username": "Awesomo 2000", "products": 435, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-19", "text": "I will always love the first Assassin's Creed, my only hiccup is sometimes Altair's pathing is a little rough but otherwise super solid game, highly recommend.", "hours": 46.3, "user_id": "76561198085340778", "username": "Sihara", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 85, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-03-19", "text": "I have never head the word infidel before in a game.(at least so many times...)\nThe game was pretty small, considering it is an Assassin's Creed game.\nCombat is easy and can be dull after some time since you will be fighting 10+ enemies at the same time.\nI believe that the gameplay can be considered obsoleted since it has been surpassed by other games in the franchise.\nI can only recommend this game if you have a lot of patience (you will lose a lot of missions due to a stupid reason and you have to start over) and you find this game on a sale.", "hours": 9.5, "user_id": "76561198140372716", "username": "ArisZou", "products": 47, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 86, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-12", "text": "This is a recommendation with a caveat.\nAssassin's creed gave the feeling of King's Quest, Prince of Persia, and Thief mixed in with an interesting storyline and compelling gameplay.\nThe caveat is that the game has three parts that are essentially straight up repeats of the previous, just with more story progression. Each city is the same round of tasks after the first.\nThat said, the story is decently written and gameplay fun enough that playing through the game is worthwhile.\nIt's also a great start for the even better sequel.", "hours": 9.7, "username": "CYB.tachyon", "products": 530, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 86, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-03-11", "text": "I really don't understand why this game is so popular. The controls are just awkward. The game is virtually unplayable on a keyboard. Why do I have to sign into a game to exit this piece of junk? Frustrating all the way through.\n3/10", "hours": 3.1, "username": "mur666", "products": 421, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 86, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-03-10", "text": "Started it up with Xbox one controller pluged up. It wouldnt recognize any inputs (including mouse/kb). Worked when I unplugged the controller. Applied a fan made patch that was supposed to fix the problem, it failed to do so. Asking for refund, not interested \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 pc ports.", "hours": 27.7, "user_id": "76561198134527067", "username": "nothing", "products": 40, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 86, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-09", "text": "I believe that this game is one of the timeless classics. It's the beginning of one of the most popular game series of all time, and it shows why this game spawned such a cash cow. It's still very playable to this day, and although it doesn't have near as much content compared to modern games, it still really is just a good game despite that. I probably wouldn't pay full price for it, but I would definitely grab it at a reduced price.", "hours": 10.6, "username": "MisleadingBanana", "products": 264, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 86, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-09", "text": "Where it all began!", "hours": 10.6, "user_id": "76561198216196104", "username": "Karttunen", "products": 12, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 86, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-03-08", "text": "Pros\n+ Interesting plot\n+ Great parcour mechanics\nCons\n- Terrible controls\n- Unfinished port from consoles without some options (subs, windowed/fullscreen mode  switch and more, overall pure options).\n- Strange combat mechanic.\n- Repetitive quests and missions. Its cool first few hours, but further all that stuff is so boring. Its like some grind MMO, but not interesting single player game.", "hours": 8.4, "user_id": "76561198069050434", "username": "daermol", "products": 140, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 86, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-03-07", "text": "I recommend it as an Assassin's Creed fan I played through all of them on console (Xbox 360) The story from the games I played was good as I just rebought all of them (Exept Rogue) I thought I would start of with where it all began BUT as I'm a windows 7 user I keep crashing on cutscenes which as you can understand\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665me of but toying with the compatibility might help you out\nRegardless 9/10", "hours": 5.1, "username": "Sir Cat Ina Hat", "products": 168, "early_access": false}
