{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "Allahu Akbar, this game is great xD xD kind of tedious though and uhhhh a bit lacking in the variety department but uh yee it set's the stage for the series well which is good, however the cliffhanger at the ending was like dafuq? you could've made the cliffhanger like a billion times better but yknow 2007 and what not so uh yee.", "hours": 18.5, "user_id": "76561198057162362", "username": "Sir Cucksalot", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "old but gold", "hours": 10.3, "username": "JimisPerfectS", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "All Assassin's Creed titles, good story but not great -- linear with only one way through.  Really REALLY idiotic missions and  terrible lack of control.   Not worth the effort to load and register with Ubi, not worth the money to sit hour after after waiting for the next scene to load.", "hours": 1.4, "user_id": "76561197996096137", "username": "Dragon", "products": 384, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "To start this review off, let me say that I am a huge fan of the Assassin's Creed franchise. Even considering some missteps, concerning the latest direction the games have taken, I will still look at AC games through rose-coloured glasses. Except the first game of the franchise, that is.\nIt is the game that introduces us to the overarching plot of Templars versus Assassins. This is all very interesting and Desmond seems kind of cool. The way of how this story is told is also innovative and cool. Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad, however, who is the 'real' protagonist of the game, is bland to say the least. The way he is written, does not allow the player to easily identify with him and thus makes him a bit annoying.\nGameplay-wise the game suffers from some very annoying problems as well. The jumping and climbing, which has become a trademark for the AC franchise, is not that polished in the first game. Very often jumps do not work out as planned and the stealth can sometimes be hindered by exactly those quirks. Furthermore, the missions are extremely repetetive and the travel-system in this game is god-awful.\nFor anyone, who wants to get into the AC series: Do yourself a favour and skip this one. There are tons of videos that give you a summary of the story, so that you can get into the second game, without having missed anything from Desmond's story. Keep your hands off this one, jump into the next one and fall in love.", "hours": 7.0, "username": "Tegernseher", "products": 530, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "For a 2007 game I was pleasantly suprised, the storyline was great! Game mechanics were limited but tbh I wasn't really expecting too much from the game when I bought it. Late to the party but I really hope the stories of the next few games are just as good.", "hours": 20.0, "user_id": "76561198120565077", "username": "N1NJ4", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "Amazing Game,\nIll love it so much, Graphic is impossible, Very addictive to play.\nTry it Lads.", "hours": 22.0, "user_id": "76561198212178135", "username": "Izzo_Alsalloum", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-28", "text": "Its ok", "hours": 20.2, "user_id": "76561198022658933", "username": "Gamingman", "products": 1113, "early_access": false}
