{"product_id": "15100", "page": 87, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-26", "text": "The game is good...But the controls are just so friggin useless.....", "hours": 3.6, "username": "EllendigeTullip J\u00e4germeister", "products": 77, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-25", "text": "If you want a game that succeeds very well at being mediocre, play any other in this series.\nIf you want a game that's an interesting failure, willing to serve its own vision before pandering to the widest playerbase, play this one.\nIs it tedious at times? Yes, certainly. Will you feel confusion, even dismay, at some of the choices the designers made? Probably.\nBetter, though, to have flaws in something interesting, than a perfectly crafted empty spectacle.", "hours": 17.3, "username": "Golden Neckbeard", "products": 404, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-24", "text": "Basically, it's a cool game.\nHowever two things are very annoying. 1) You need to climb a tower every 2 minutes to unlock \"quests\", so to speak. Super annoying. 2) When you want to exit the game, you exit the in-game game, and then you're back in the game that's inside the game. Then exit that and you have to loud your profile and then exit out of that to finally exit the game.\nOther than that, good old-school game.", "hours": 15.6, "username": "Mouth", "products": 154, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-22", "text": "It's like eating through a pile of dog\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665just to get one Snickers bar. Not worth it.", "hours": 12.9, "username": "pEpinko", "products": 232, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-02-20", "text": "\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665game", "hours": 13.0, "user_id": "76561197987031616", "username": "lil homie", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-20", "text": "The amount of research and effort put into this game is stunning. Each city is constructed as it used to be in the 12th century, all 9 assassination targets where actuall people who either died or disappeared in that time.\nThe game itself is very atmospheric with an interesting and deeper than expected storyline. Controlls may take you a while to get used to but feel natural after that. The main plus of the game is the free roaming and climbing, the transitions while climbing feel natural and flawless.", "hours": 32.1, "user_id": "76561198252991802", "username": "lepton", "products": 16, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-20", "text": "Yes, only for the story. Forgot collecting/doing anything extra. Just load up, focus on the main quests and nut this thing out in a few hours so you can move on to the fun games that follow.\nYou need to think of this as simply a tech demo for whats to come.", "hours": 12.0, "username": "Godfrey", "products": 1324, "early_access": false}
