{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-16", "text": "Very good game, with the hability of connecthing (real life) history fans to videogame enthusiasts.\nAlthough in late game the mecanics may seem a little repetitive, the background allows you to live in a part of history not portrait in many videogames and to do a little \"tour\" from a different perspective around the places you hear in history class.", "hours": 23.7, "user_id": "76561198008454470", "username": "joao_palotas", "products": 51, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 88, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-02-16", "text": "An absolute MUST for assassins creed fans.\nPros:\n-Maxing it out gives better graphics than xbox one and ps4 will ever give you (I mean like, wtf, it's a very old game but maxing it out beats the consoles of this generation? it's a plus for me.)\n-Good gameplay-sometimes a bit choppy in the fighting part\n-Overall a pretty good story.\nCons:\n-Halfway through completion you understand how repetitive it is.\n-Voice acting is kinda cheap... Every person I save from any town says the same crap. They cheaped out on it, just like pc builders and their Power Supplies.\n-If you play anything else first, the combat will disappoint you in this one. (No air assassinations etc)\n-What the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 IS WRONG WITH THE ENDING?!\nWorth it, if you're a fan and you got time to kill!", "hours": 21.1, "user_id": "76561198026044658", "username": "Pingou3", "products": 56, "early_access": false}
