{"product_id": "15100", "page": 94, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2016-01-01", "text": "Here are my notes while playing the game if you don't have time to read them DON'T WASTE YOUR TIME AND MONEY! IT'S NOT WORTH IT.\nPro's\n- Premise of the story has a lot of potential\n- Very easy to run. GPU usage is 20-30% (GTX 970), CPU usage is 10% (i7 3820)\n- Running and climbing is a good idea let down by poor implementation\nNegatives\n- tutorial is buggy and repetitious\n- intro was intriguing yet boring at the same time. Go figure!\n- buggy fighting mechanics\n- it was very hard to control your character\n- game has a lot of hand holding\n- confusing messages in the UI\n- mission consists of 1. Travel for ten minutes to city 2. Gather information twice 3. Plan attack 4. Attack never goes as planned\n- the fact that you have time to interrogate the target before he dies means it must be a stealth kill for privacy but never happens\n- alerts only go off when in hiding places even if you have not been found for 10 mins\n- story is Altiar is arrogant and foolish, gets demoted despite still being sent on missions to kill key targets. Assassinations are clumsy but they are planned that way for story, if this is true there is no need of planning attacks if it always boils down to a fight.\n- Desmond parts could at least let you run making exploration less time consuming and annoying.\n- the introduction from every assassination is boring and long\n- story gets interesting midway but the bad mechanics still hinder experience\n- menu won't start with controller activated\n- you can't swim FFS\n- BUG! I attempt a mission to kill kill 3 soldiers, I killed two out of 3 failing the mission but when restarting mission dead bodies are still on floor alerting guards to my presence. Pathetic!\n- these NPCs that are deranged pushing you every time you walk past are annoying and unnecessary\n- boss fights are really bad. Chase till he stops then fight 20 guys, keep hitting boss till your player assassinates him automatically.", "hours": 15.3, "username": "KingSmug", "products": 218, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 94, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2016-01-01", "text": "Im not sure how I like this game to be honest.\nThe story itself is awesome and a good preparation for the 2nd game (which is my fav. ac game by far)\nBut the game play is just a variety of different mission which basically are the same - only the assassination target differs - every time you need to prepare for the assassasination by finding out information about the target and then kill your him. That's the whole game, sadly.\nBut like I said earlier - the story is great and you really need to play this game in order to play the others thats why I give it a thumbs up!", "hours": 24.9, "user_id": "76561198177383381", "username": "davy_grolton", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 94, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "Cool with me.\nKill or be killed!!!!!\nAt least I can kill & get away with it along with pick pocketing & other things.\nPeople like these type of games then they would enjoy games like \"Kingdom of Amular\", \"Elder Scrolls: Skyrim\", etc.\nI think it's cool,\nespecially when I think the enimieys are my wife's friends, lmao!!!!!!", "hours": 45.0, "username": "father_dragon_barragan2008", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 94, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "If this is the first and only Assassin's creed game you've played, please don't judge the entire saga based on this game--in my opinion this is the worst one in the entire series; the game play is very repetitive.  To be fair, this was the first game that needed to be set to launch the entire saga.  The game had some very creative concepts like jumping off 30 story buildings, secretively assassinating with a hidden blade.  The story line is pretty cool too, I won't spoil too much but it has a matrix like story-line.  Overall it's a very good play and a must if you like platforming and sneakily killing people type games.  It is also a must play first if you intend on getting into the assassin's creed story lines.", "hours": 65.7, "user_id": "76561198114776608", "username": "buckman333", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 94, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "Holy ****. Is this the kind of game that consoles provide? No wonder I never got into them.\nBuy this if you like;\nSimplistic game play\nStatic worlds where you can slaughter 50 people in a city and nothing changes..even if you do it right in front of people\nWalking really slowly by guards over and over and over because you don't feel like killing 10 guards\nDoing the same thing over and over and over\nSuper simple combat", "hours": 11.7, "user_id": "76561198001737061", "username": "Newbie Z", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 95, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-31", "text": "It's an old, but a very good game.\nThe story is one that captivates you, making you live in the main character skin.\nThe game play it's easy to understand and the movement and combo can be easily reproduced.\nI recommend this game to any person that likes history, a good story and the assassinations.", "hours": 0.2, "username": "Ragnar\u00f6k", "products": 294, "early_access": false}
