{"product_id": "15100", "page": 96, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-20", "text": "I'm a huge fan of the series but I gotta say that playing this game has been painful to say the least. Storywise it's interesting especially in the modern day section but parkour, fighting and guard AI are awful. You should buy/watch it on youtube only for the story if you are a fan of the series.\n+ Goodlooking for an fairly old game\n+ Altair\n+ Interesting setting\n- God awful game mechanics\n- Repetitive missions", "hours": 6.2, "user_id": "76561198140656191", "username": "Rainbow Goddess", "products": 59, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 96, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-19", "text": "The first of the Assassin's Creed series happens to be my favorite (I haven't played all the Assassin's Creed so my review may change later.) Why is it my favorite? The gameplay is outstanding as is the story. You begin as a high ranking assassin name Alta\u00efr. You and two other assassin's are looking for the \"apple\" in a cave along the way you break the three simple rules that defines the creed, I won't go too much into the details. Once you get back to your master you are get underattacked by the templars, the Brotherhood's enemies. After you scare off the templars you get hold on trail for breaking the three simple rules of the Creed. You get stabbed in the body and left to die, or you thought. You are reborn and as a noivce so you must work your way up the rankings once again. That's the simple starting of the game. The second best part about this game is that you don't need Uplay to play it. Now remember \"Nothing is true and everything is permitted.\"", "hours": 1.6, "username": "Nasus", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 96, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-18", "text": "This game was fun. . . a lot of fun. . .now I want it again. . .;-;. I want it so badly. . .I accidently sold it. . .;-;. I've got a good PC for this game. I ran a lot of Assassin's Creed games on my laptop. The one that's a ROG laptop. It's an amazing laptop PC.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "Do U No Da Wae?", "products": 233, "early_access": false}
