{"product_id": "15100", "page": 99, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-28", "text": "Incredible story and graphics. Gameplay is good but not optimal. I do not like how the camera works but I got used to it. This game is just amazing. The plot is very well written and strategies are needed to pass some parts. Sometimes you need to be pacient enough to repeat some parts until you get it done. I suggest to look around a lot before deciding where to go. Totally recommend this game.", "hours": 33.4, "user_id": "76561198097590064", "username": "twitch.tv/tukdream", "products": 68, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 99, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-28", "text": "Assassin's Creed 1 is a mediocre start to the Assassin's Creed series.\nGameplay is simple.  Go to city, do quests, do assassination, and get kicked out of animus.\nDo that a few times and the twist ending and you have the game.\nGameplay 6/10\nSound 7/10\nStory 8/10\nOverall the game is alright.  Rush straight through the game to get to Assassin's Creed 2.\nBTW no window mode", "hours": 11.2, "username": "MPkNight", "products": 623, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 99, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-28", "text": "While more combat oriented than the other games in the franchise, the original Assassin's Creed is still a fine gaming experience. Albeit more repetitve than future sequels. With solid graphics and a large world to explore, this semi-linear experience is well worth the money if the action/adventure genre appeals to you.\nJust be warned that the Assassin's Creed franchise contains numerous jump puzzles that may give problems to certain gamers. Particularly those using a keyboard and mouse.\n7.5/10", "hours": 52.0, "user_id": "76561197971943763", "username": "Grimhotep", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
