{"product_id": "15100", "page": 101, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-21", "text": "This was rough. It wasn't hard, but the controls make this type of game more difficult than it needs to be. Terrible combat makes any fight something to run from, but when the last hour and a half is made up of mob battles, I just wanted it to end. The free running is fun at first, but it's to grabby to be great. Also, there are no skippable cutscenes. So even if you cared about the story (I did not), if you fail a mission, be prepared to rewatch it over and over again.\nThis games got so annoying in the end, I'm not sure if I'll ever pick up the second titles, even though I hear it's a better game. Better than Assassin's Creed? Not hard and maybe not for me.", "hours": 18.6, "username": "duskvstweak", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 101, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-20", "text": "ep1k n1ce", "hours": 18.2, "username": "Patriots SB 51 Champs", "products": 53, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 101, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-11-20", "text": "I played this game years after it was released because it was part of a package deal.  For that reason it's hard to give a bad review because it was so cheap, but I didn't like this game.  Assassins' Creed 2 is a different story, however.\nAnyway, the game is very repetitive and quite short.  There is not even much in the way of achievements unless you want to collect flags but the game pretty much implies that this is a worthless endeavor.\nThe game had good graphics for its time.  Perhaps that's what made it so popular, and also you can climb on just about everything.  This is the good part.\nThe problem is that you are always doing the same thing.  It's always about assassinating certain people and it's almost always done in the same way. Yeah, you have to maybe pickpocket, interrogate or eavesdrop on people before you get to the target but in the end you have to keep repeating these activities over and over again.\nThis game could make you hate poor people since the beggars will swarm around you like flies until you want to murder them even though that's evil and the guards will make your life miserable if you keep doing that.  This is one of the funnier aspects of the game but after awhile it gets annoying.\nIn the end, I felt that I was just doing the same thing over and over and over again just for slight progression in the main character's (Desmond's) story, and the game doesn't answer all the questions (hence the many, many sequels) so you don't necessarily get a good resolution.\nI have played other stealth games.  I enjoyed Tenchu 1 and 2 though they aren't super hardcore about stealth, and I've always thought that the Metal Gear Solid games did stealth well.  I especially loved how difficult Siren was with its stealth gameplay, but this game got too tiresome.  The stealth isn't particulary hard, like some of the games I played above, so I wouldn't even say it's a challenging stealth game.  I do like the parkour elements but I just wish there had been more variety to the missions you have to perform.\nI didn't like this game, but then I played Assassin's Creed 2 which is better in every possible way, so unless you want to be a completionist and play all the games I recommend skipping this one.", "hours": 24.8, "user_id": "76561197999045600", "username": "totalgarbage", "products": 333, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 101, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-20", "text": "...", "hours": 15.8, "user_id": "76561198168019150", "username": "Merchant", "products": 98, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 101, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-19", "text": "Disclaimer: I'm writing this Review 3 Years after I played it.\nYou start with a simple Tutorial teaching you the Basic's of the Game: Fighting/Movement/Assassination\nAfter this you get a sort of Mission telling you where an who to assassinate.\nThe Game allows you to do this in whatever way you want.\nThis repeats mutliple Times without feeling repetetive due to new Areas/Situation/Guards.\n7/10", "hours": 16.5, "username": "psyConAim", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 101, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-19", "text": "An amazing game. No sequel is better! Loved the story and easy to use controls. It has a lot of play time if you do all the side quests as well as the main campaign.", "hours": 23.7, "username": "A Ghost Of Onyx", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 101, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-11-19", "text": "Boy, I bet this was really something when it was first released. I played this after AC2 and it's clear that AC2 improves upon absolutely everything introduced here. But there was a lot this game brought to the table originally and I still found myself having fun playing it. I'd recommend this game if you thirst for more backstory to the Assassin's Creed series or if you can get it cheap because it's barely worth half of what AC2 costs.", "hours": 15.1, "username": "UltimateXero", "products": 242, "early_access": false}
