{"product_id": "15100", "page": 105, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-23", "text": "Assassins Creed 1 was the first Assassins Creed game I played, and I left this game on between the end of 2014 and the start of 2015.. Random fact for the review.\nThe game after 8 or so years, still feels so fresh, simple and clean (except for that blood stain from that templar...)\nAlot of games these days don't feel the same.. And that's a shame.\n11/10 Altair is underrated", "hours": 9.4, "username": "\u03bbctionwill65", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 105, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-23", "text": "Hated those crazy lunatics pushing me around every second, in the most important moments when I was trying to blend in like a real Assassin. Like I was invading their personal crazy ppl space.\nLoved the game though.", "hours": 12.5, "user_id": "76561198163986777", "username": "wasffa", "products": 124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 105, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-10-21", "text": "Just finished replaying through this game as I have not played it since it was released back in the day on Xbox 360.\n*****If you have never played Assassin's creed before, this game is a must play. Ignore everything below, as that is written from the POV of someone who has played and completed nearly every game in the entire series, and went back and played this one now on PC. The series was one of the best and most revolutionary ones there were. I wish I could experience them for the first time again.*****\nAs someone who has played every single Assasin's Creed from start to finish, going back and playing this game was painful in terms of the mechanics, camera angles, repetitiveness.\nThe main story-line is still good although repeptitive, and I did enjoy the nostalgia seeing how the series got started in terms of the pieces of eden, abstergo, and desmond.\nHowever you are assigned to assassinate a total of 9 people, and before you can kill one of them, you must complete at least 2-3 mini tasks.\nThere are only 3 different mini tasks in the entire game: Pickpocket a random citizen for info, talk to an informant and complete his task, and beat up a random preacher/well-know citizen to get info from them. You do this NINE times. You literally pickpocket, escort/run through city, and fist fight a citizen a total of 25-27 times, and then assasinate a target. (9 main kills, 2-3 mini tasks before each one).\nOnce again want to emphasize if you've never played the series, please get this and play it through, as you're starting one of the best and most successful game franchises of all time.\nFirst time played: 9/10\nGoing back years later after playing the whole series: 7/10", "hours": 7.8, "username": "WatchaGunnaDooo", "products": 167, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 105, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-21", "text": "Assassin's Creed is all about spending ages gathering information on your targets, using it to devise a plan to get in, make the kill and get out, then see it all go horribly wrong in a split second and end up winging it anyway. But that just makes it all the sweeter when you do execute a plan perfectly.\nBasically Metal Gear Solid with free running during the Crusades. It can drag a bit going through all of the information gathering challenges, but the assassinations just about make up for it.", "hours": 34.1, "user_id": "76561197974172829", "username": "Andy Pants", "products": 196, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 106, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-20", "text": "Recommend this game if you love stabbing people and parkour, this game is so fun.\nA must play game if you want to play Assassin's Creed II 'cause the controls and gameplay is much likely the same, and you'll go crazy if you start playing Assassin's Creed II w/o playing this game. For the timeline of AC, this game covers the story where it all begans about Desmond Miles, and his ancestors, that he has a blood of an assassin.", "hours": 62.1, "username": "aRTiPee", "products": 32, "early_access": false}
