{"product_id": "15100", "page": 108, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-10", "text": "This game is great, if you have played the other AC games, this one is much more different.\nThe game has 9 or 10 levels if I can remember correctly and side missions.\nAlso the game is open world, which may seem bad, or good for some people..\nHere are some reasons what I think are good and bad about this game:\nPros:\nGood Story\nGood fun (in my opinion)\nAn assassins creed game that involves crowds (unlike all the other AC games, am I right?)]\nEasy to play\nYou can ride horses\nCons:\nQuite afew glitches\nClimbing seems harder\nNot as smooth parkour or assassinations as AC 3 and up\nNot much freedom at the end of the game\nAnyway, these are some reasons why I find this game good, I would really suggest buying it, it's worth it, in my opinion.", "hours": 28.3, "username": "you big gay", "products": 30, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 108, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-08", "text": "Assassin's Creed- games are love or hate kind of games much like Battlefield or Call of Duty. I myself as a history buff have enjoyed each and everyone of the game in the franchise. Each game feels different and is made to be different unlike COD. The reason why I like this one is because of the setting (Middle ages) and how beautiful the game looks. Also the Desmond trilogy (AC 1-3) has the strongest storyline. I liked Black Flag, Rogue and Unity aswell and I'm waiting for Syndicate, because each game changes the gameplay and the feeling to it.\nBUT the first part in AC is repetitive because of the game's mechanic. I honestly prefer AC II over I because of the variety of missions and activities. This game will remain a classic for me but it's not the best in the series unlike most games are.\nOh and it's the only AC game that doesn't require Uplay, even tough I have nothing against Ubisoft. Some people on Steam complain it on a daily basis which I don't get. I agree that you can have opinion but whining about Uplay or Ubisoft isn't good for your health.\nBut verdict, it's an 8/10 game.", "hours": 10.1, "username": "Farka\u0161", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 108, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-10-08", "text": "Extremely boring ... only 3 thing to do: run around, climb stuff, kill stuff.\nVery linear game just follow direction.\nLooks good", "hours": 31.2, "user_id": "76561198122721461", "username": "alexandre.belinge", "products": 66, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 108, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-06", "text": "This is the game that started my assassin\u2019s obsession. Even though I bought it recently on Steam, it has my ~10 full walkthroughs (5 of them with flags, templars, citizens and viewpoints accomplished), a lot of memory block replays.\nI played it first within a week of its release (not knowing it), and up until now, the game fascinated me several times:\nSo, I recommend the game despite its sometimes repetitive gameplay (please name the game where gameplay isn\u2019t the same throughout the game).", "hours": 23.7, "username": "Hlelia", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
