{"product_id": "15100", "page": 113, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-06", "text": "windows 10 review This game seems to run ok on most settings providing your pc's specs meet up with the requirements.\nGameplay feels much better using a controller \"xbox 360\" then using a standard mouse and keyboard.\nI would totally recommend getting this as Ive had no major problems with it.", "hours": 13.3, "username": "sketcherskt", "products": 310, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 113, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-06", "text": "I can imagine Altair cutting himself with the hidden blade when he's about to use it.\ncracks me up everytime.", "hours": 9.1, "user_id": "76561198094914271", "username": "Mentality", "products": 63, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-08-02", "text": "Highly trained assasin capable of sneaking into one the most fortified buildings of his era will die if he swims\n10/10", "hours": 14.8, "user_id": "76561198057672452", "username": "Tranquilo", "products": 439, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-08-01", "text": "This videographic game experience was not a great one for me as there is not enough freedom\nJerry Rice/10", "hours": 1.7, "username": "oof", "products": 107, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-31", "text": "+ As the first game of the franchise, it is both novel in concept and scope of narrative\n+ Platforming elements are extremely polished and satisfying; climbing is simple in practice and is competently animated\n+ Environments are large, detailed and absolutely gorgeous\n+ Voice-acting (with one notable oversight, addressed below) is excellent; general sound-design, too, is strikingly original\n+ UI, though it breaks the immersion a bit, is practical and aesthetically pleasing\n+ Bissfully short load-times; game's engine runs smoothly and efficiently\n+ Quick-travel is available as the explorable areas increase\n+ Swordplay, though not as emphasized as a gameplay element, is still quite cinematic and enjoyable\n+ Myriad collectibles and viewpoints to unlock, scattered throughout the world\n+ Stalking targets is broken down into a series of minigames; though tragically un-varied (there are only 6 variations), they nonetheless do their part to uphold immersion\n- Exiting the game requires movement through 3 or 4 menu screens; quitting a game has never been so frustrating\n- Segments revolving around Desmond (in the year 2012) often seem to drag on well beyond what is required to set up that angle of the plot; seriously breaks up the pacing\n- Beyond the drive to get a 100% save file, there is little incentive to replay after a successful playthrough\n- Limited tangible incentive to explore and collect; doing so is done so for its own sake\n- Protagonist's voiceover is decidedly American, in stark contrast to the authentic accents of virtually all other characters; massive break in immersion", "hours": 15.2, "username": "LockeProposal", "products": 312, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-30", "text": "One of the best games ever!\nThis was the first time I played a game of the assassins creed series. I am almost through the game and I already bought part 2. Well what do I have to say t thi game?\nPro:\n- nice graphics (considering it came out 2007)\n-open world+ big maps\n-freedom of doing things (how to get from A to B , from the alleway or over the roofs)\n-story 'outside' the game (Desmond) is really interesting.\n-Many key combinations (many fight styles)\n-parkour is so much fun\nNeutral:\n-Story ( Altair) may not be really good, but I like it. It's a good introducton to the world of the assassins.\n-gameplay may be dull or repetetive in the sense of story (same citys)\nNegative:\n-those \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing 'side quests' :D saving people from guards, I mean c'mon...\nAll in all one of the best games I ever played, looking forward to play the second one!", "hours": 21.2, "user_id": "76561198169331227", "username": "\u2764 DarkFairy\u2764", "products": 14, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-30", "text": "A game in which you lose all your items and have to earn them all back ok thats enough about metroid.\nSeriously tho this is a very fun, fairly open world game and is worth having in your Assassination based game collection.", "hours": 9.9, "user_id": "76561198041444828", "username": "GedLegend1983", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-30", "text": "Sick Parkour!", "hours": 16.3, "user_id": "76561198106369075", "username": "wiweki", "products": 8, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-28", "text": "Fun game!\nClimbing and jumping through the cities, is a lot of fun.\nFighting is fun at first, but gets a bit repetitive in the end.", "hours": 11.3, "username": "Dudwls", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-27", "text": "You should begin your AC series journey from this game. Reccomended.", "hours": 12.7, "username": "Coke", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-26", "text": "A good start of the series. Tells the story of Altair and sets the setting for the entire franchise.\nA word of warning: Block the game on windows firewall to prevent crashing, because the game is looking for DRM servers that are offline and think it is illegitimate version.", "hours": 4.2, "username": "Strazdas", "products": 171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 114, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-25", "text": "After finishing the game the first time, I thought I'd never play it again, but here not 1-2 months later, I played it through again.\nIt's simple and yet elegant. The quests are all the same, but I still liked going through them because the combat is very good. In the 2nd game I did better because I mastered more moves. I owned this a long time ago on PS3 and could never get the controls right, but I bought it for the computer and computer controls for fighting is what I grew up on.\nI got to where I'd have 20-30 guards coming at me and I would own them. Run from the guards? Blend? Why? I just cut through them after I got counter moves. And after I mastered breaking grab, I really was almost unstoppable.\nIf I could ever figure out how to counter the templay combo move that ends up with a throat punch, I'd probably never lose a fight.\nIt is a great game.", "hours": 82.6, "user_id": "76561198005069670", "username": "Gilmer", "products": 111, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-07-24", "text": "The game wont play. I have more than the recommended specs, and I'm getting around a whopping ONE frame per second.", "hours": 5.8, "username": "Solominondas", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-07-21", "text": "The first AC is a pretty bad game.\nThe theme is extremely cool and the parkour is fun but the game is too repetitive and gets boring quickly (the sidequests don't help at all).\nThe sci-fi sections are dumb and the history parts are always the same: go here, kill him, beat up him, steal from him, sit on a bench and listen to him... awwww\nThe game gets interesting towards the end though and there are some great philosophical thoughts in AC but the gameplay is just too repetitive which makes the game feel like a chore.", "hours": 17.1, "username": "Le Loup Blanc", "products": 169, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-20", "text": "cool", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561198095073401", "username": "Sadbart", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-20", "text": "Great game, highly recommended although it can become a little monotonous.", "hours": 41.5, "user_id": "76561198119478565", "username": "kaireilly64", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-20", "text": "The one that started it all. Not as refined as the next ones in the generation but still a fun time and a good port to pc. Best played with a controller.", "hours": 10.7, "user_id": "76561198044567406", "username": "Panda Pope", "products": 1380, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-20", "text": "The first Assassin's Creed will always be my personal favourite of the series. Such a great game: awesome graphics (for the time), intriguing plot and a unique gameplay. It's an amazing game, and always will be.", "hours": 50.0, "user_id": "76561197995086333", "username": "Destiny883", "products": 931, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-19", "text": "The environments are beautiful.  The music is pretty cool.  I liked the story, although it was a bit slow and some of the lab scenes felt rather pointless in the end.  I liked the main character quite a bit.  It was a bit repetitive in some parts, and the final battle was not fun for me, but overall I enjoyed it very much.", "hours": 59.3, "user_id": "76561197982373819", "username": "Rendroc", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-17", "text": "amazing game. the controls are not as nice as later games in the series, and the visuals are not quite as gorgeous, but there's something really awesome about this first Assassin's Creed that the later games in the series don't quite capture, as far as i'm concerned (although the other games are pretty cool too). thumbs up for sure.", "hours": 28.7, "user_id": "76561198081102222", "username": "Frobie", "products": 58, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-17", "text": "Its the begining of the legendary series. It is a perfect game for its time...\nI played this game when I see the teasers of the AC unity which means years later. Still I enjoyed the game. Although some where the game play gets routine, the senario keeps it going.\nWorths the time...", "hours": 31.1, "user_id": "76561198020212223", "username": "ozgunozer", "products": 243, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 115, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-17", "text": "Repetitive, but still a good looking and playing game.\nThe first one and still one of the best imo.", "hours": 16.8, "user_id": "76561197972939512", "username": "jozuasgrunt", "products": 1230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-12", "text": "Very smooth gameplay, especially during the fights.  Great story as well.", "hours": 53.6, "user_id": "76561198160671363", "username": "Dr. Dank", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-11", "text": "Assassin's Creed is one of the most unique story-action-RPG game ever made. Smooth combat and facial animation put even recent RPG games to shame. The middle east during the times of the crusaders is believable and feels very authentic. This game is executed to a very high level and is definitely worth the full price even after so many years.\nAssassin's Creed on the PC is however not without its faults. Make no mistakes, this was made-for-console. Any PC gamers will immediately find the PC controls clunky. There are many console-nastiness such as checkpoint saving and ridiculous combat controls which plainly does not work on a mouse and keyboard. I gave up trying to remember all the different keys for all the combat moves and used only block/retaliate which requires only right and left mouse buttons.\nThe gameplay can also get quite repetitive and it's a chore to do the tasks because 90% of the time you are wading through people and trying to blend in. Run a bit and you get caught. Bump into someone, you get caught. It's fun the first few times, but gets really annoying after a few hours. Sometimes people just wanna play and walking slowly doing nothing is not playing. Replayability is poor because after 20 hrs, i just wanna get it over with.\nAll the funky console issues aside, I would definitely still recommend all RPG fans to get this game. If you haven't played Assassin's Creed, you are missing out.", "hours": 20.3, "username": "\u2605DogeJo\u2605", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-10", "text": "This remains the only Assassin's Creed game that I ever enjoyed, also the only \"Almost\" historically correct one too.\nWhen the assassin ancestors turns into arrogant italians, and other random nationalities in the new games, instead of the cold blooded silent killer Alta\u00efr from the Middle east, I simply vomit.\nThe Franchise became so popular, that it ruined the continued series.\nThis Assassin's creed though, is not any of that. It remains a pearl in the evolution of games in everyway.", "hours": 3.6, "user_id": "76561198036662065", "username": "Hashash", "products": 1268, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-10", "text": "The ONE Assassins Creed game that doesen't require UPlay.\n10/10 IGN", "hours": 24.5, "username": "Gru's Num.1 Minion", "products": 404, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-08", "text": "Better late than never. :D\nXP or some loot for killing would be an added value to this game.", "hours": 21.0, "username": "SteeL", "products": 178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-06", "text": "Decent enough fun, despite it being Ubisoft. Found all the items, and spots, and extras. Spent quite a bit of time in it and thought the premise to be a bit odd, but different enough to not be same-ole-same-ole.\n... and then steam then wouldn't let me write a review because it only thought I spent 4 minutes in the game. *ahem*", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Frigidman", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-04", "text": "Pros\n1. The game is very well designed and beautiful.\n2. As the difficulty level ramps up, there are tutorials for you to practice within the game in a realistic way.\n3. The game gets progressively harder in a manageable way, until the end.\n4. The missions are challenging and interesting, especially early on.\n5. The sword fighting is pretty realistic.\nCons\n1. The game gets tedious after the fourth or fifth major mission. Each new city seems to have the exact same tasks with a big assassination at the end.\n2. Some side missions seems pointless (especially collecting all the flags).", "hours": 8.1, "user_id": "76561198054142661", "username": "Mine", "products": 210, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-02", "text": "STOP THIEF! You are FENF!", "hours": 13.1, "username": "Henman", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-07-02", "text": "I'm completely new to the Assassin's Creed franchise.  Quite how I've managed to steer clear of it for quite so long, I don't really know and now that I have finally played it, it would seem it's been a happy accident.  I've obviously been aware of each release and the hype and disappointment that has surrounded each one but never took the initiative and bought one.  Now with the Steam sales and being ten years late to the party, I thought I'd pick it up where it all began for less than \u00a32 and see what all the fuss is about.\nThe atmosphere and free running mechanics are great and show great attention to detail which I love but that's about as far as the positivity goes.  The storyline has so much potential but is ultimately crap and the ending is just shocking.  And the journey you go through to get there is just so damn repetetive!  Finally, it plays more of a brawler than actual stealthy assassin work.  Overall a big disappointment and with much the same criticisms hanging around the franchise as a whole, I think this will be my first and last foray into the world of Assassins Creed.", "hours": 11.3, "username": "T\u00f8rsryk", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 116, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-01", "text": "One of my favourites, if not personal favourite in the series.\nThe setting is perfect, controls can be clunky at times but theres a combination of fluidity and harshness that makes combat feel GOOD in this game. Traversing the world is enjoyable, and the story is enjoyable.\nMissions are rather repetitive, but never enough to detract entirely from the game. That being said, for any newcomer I'd highly recommend reading a synopsis and jumping into Assassin's Creed 2. The gameplay is arguably much superior, and the missions are much less repetitive.\nThat being said, it is a great game unto itself, if a bit aged.", "hours": 25.4, "username": "Scyllable", "products": 1303, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-07-01", "text": "Died drinking a glass of water\n10/10 would drink again", "hours": 14.4, "username": "Mypowerbob", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-07-01", "text": "Assassin creed PC at first glance is beautiful and the main character one of the coolest looking. Assassin creed is fun with it's unique fighting style, art work, mechanics. BUT it has it's flaws from not properly saving to clunky jumping, lack of weapons, attack animations, and terrible repetitive gameplay forcing you to find and do boring things like climbing tall towers, pick pocketing that seems so bland and useless, than you realize everything is copy and pasted. The story feels awkward, with no immersion everything you do in the game you do in the first coupe of hours.\nThe game sometimes forgets weather you want to jump down or go up and bugs out  on some of the simplest climbing movements. Some games didn't save properly, and some broken missions caused me to restart several times.\nAlso 4 a Assassin game, no stealth is ever needed for the main missions whats up with that?\nThe dialogue beside the main assassinations are all repeats just like the buildings, gets old pretty quick.\nI can see why people like this creed, I do not.\nI like the concept of the game, like most it failed horribly at keeping me entertained.", "hours": 22.7, "username": "Silent Hightimes", "products": 462, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-30", "text": "First I want to start off with no Uplay!\nThe first Assassins Creed game is personally one of my more favorite of the AC titles next to 2, but this game isnt the second and im not going to compare them, im just going to say my honest opinion on this version.\nTo start i really like the whole concept of this taking place in the middle ages, the idea of fighting knights in armour with awesome kill cinematics back in the day for me was sweet! Sprinting over roof tops tossing throwing knives at anyone standing in my way was very entertaining. Personally I really like the whole AC story line even though it confuses the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665out of me at times.\nOn the downside i found the controls when trying to traverse over water areas to be a little touchy and spent a solid half hour drowning, as you progress further into the game the guards are more and more likely to attack you for no reason which albiet is understandable at that point but the running mechanics well they tend to fail you, considering you got like 10 some odd guards chasing you, but even so thats not too bad heyre easy to kill.\nLastly the thing i hated the most and always will is those \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing beggars! holy\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665i killed soooo many of them i dont care theyre anoying as\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665and constantly block you at the worst times. \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 i know your homeless but I dont want this sword going up my\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\nTo surmize this is a really good game and personally if your going to play the series i recommend this one first just for the story if not anything else.\n9.1/10 would stab beggars again.", "hours": 16.2, "user_id": "76561198020176219", "username": "SmokeyTokes", "products": 377, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-29", "text": "Nice game better then any assassin creed franchise. But, the story is very simple: go to assassin bureu, find information about the target, kill the target, listen their conversation, escape the city, hiding in assassin bureu, back to Masyaf, and do it over and over again. Also there are no minimap so you need to open map every time u lost. i reccomended u to buy this game but, make sure u have a compass if you wanna play this game.", "hours": 5.6, "username": "Toolsofevil", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-29", "text": "Just like reading a history book while jumping off a building!  9/10 (You jump off a bigger building in the sequels)", "hours": 16.9, "username": "Clearness", "products": 436, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-27", "text": "It's fair to say this is a good beginning for the Assassin's Creed Game Series.", "hours": 20.1, "username": "Sp0cky-", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-27", "text": "if this game were a fork, it would be a good fork.", "hours": 4.3, "username": "Scizoria", "products": 24, "found_funny": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-27", "text": "You just have to be fan of Altair no matter what :) The storyline is pretty simple for the first AC game though, if you wish for better story, aim for AC II, Brotherhood and Revelations instead. Graphics is amazing for 2008 game and mechanics of climbing and killing is well made, I cannot complain about it at all. You may get some repetetive feeling sometimes, but you can just search for flags and roam around cities if you do not want to play the main quest right away.", "hours": 43.1, "username": "Youko Akira", "products": 239, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-26", "text": "Classic assassin's creed. See the world through the eyes of altair once again. Remastered, Reimagined, Revisited.This game is great fun it removes the repetetivness of ac1, fixes bugs and improves graphics. Great game 5/5 pick it up when you can.", "hours": 11.2, "username": "Cremated Nan", "products": 150, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 117, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-25", "text": "Interesting title. Altair's story in the past is quite interesting, but the Desmond's story in the present works more like a backstory than anything else, works fine with other titles in the franchise, but is meaningless by itself. Altair as a character is... strange a little, but he turns from an unlikeable dummy to quite likeable merciless killer! Yeah, I did just say that, likeable merciless killer, that's jut how it is. The game has its key standing in the franchise and goes really well especially with Ezio's trilogy, which is, by the way, following right after this, neat!.\nAssassin's Creed is recommended by just 1 out of 10 templars, but don't worry, that guy was a traitor and the others.. well, they didn't make it, the hidden blade is damn sharp.", "hours": 27.5, "username": "Jpelda_CrazyCat", "products": 122, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 118, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-25", "text": "Summary:  --> Recommended\n+ Interesting action title. (Story / Action / Graphics / Killing )\n+ Casual playing, should completed around 30hrs of gameplay.\n+ Graphics is fine and smooth for me (even the game is 5-year old)\n+/-  Combat mode is personal, but I would say the control flows smooth (I use a controller)\n- Some repeat missions are frustrating to re-play.\n- Dead bodies may interrupt ongoing missions, which is extreamely annoying (solution is to re-start the game)\nNotes:\n-> I have spent a budget on the Assasin's Creed titles due to its positive repetation, in the Steam Summer Sale 2015 (carefully selected only PC sequels, not implents from other consoles)\n-> Price was around \u00a33 (really worth it, but resonable)\n-> Steam reviews are fairly accurate to look into, in this series.\n-> Looking forward to the playing the 2nd title.\n--> \"Young man, you have done me a kindness. Be assured, I wont forget it)\" -The most annoying quote ever.", "hours": 28.3, "username": "Kaito", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 118, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-25", "text": "Entertaining for hours on end with fun stealth and combat based gameplay. I'd recommend skipping this game and going straight ot Assassins Creed II only because the stealth mechanic in this is not nearly as good and the controls are worse. Still, I'll recommend this game if you want to play from the beginning.", "hours": 3.4, "username": "GameScoot", "products": 259, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 118, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-24", "text": "Really awesome game just the controls are kinda odd for the mouse and keyboard. On the Xbox 360 it was great. So.....yeah.....better controls..... 9/10", "hours": 1.0, "username": "vira", "products": 106, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 118, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-24", "text": "The controls are clunky, the camera is atrocious, free-running is terribad and the gameplay is repetitive.\nThe storyline is mediocre at best.\nStart with Assassin's Creed II.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "yeet", "products": 320, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
