{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-19", "text": "The game that started it all, still lives up to the hype from many years ago.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "The Bearded Ninja", "products": 254, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-19", "text": "1) No running or you will be killed on sight.\n2) No galloping or you will be killed on sight.\n3) No walking on the roof or you will be killed on sight.\n4) Dirty thief! I'll have your hand for that!\n5) No loitering in the guard's treasured personal space for more than two seconds or guess what?\nYou will be killed on sight.\n6) No swimming or...never mind, you'll die anyway.\n7) No bumping into people or you will be killed on sight.\n8) No climbing buildings or you will be killed on sight.\n9) If you don't slouch and leave one hand hanging while trotting at a snail's pace on your horse, you will be killed on sight.\n10) They say it is a crusade! But a crusade for what? Ignorance? Violence? Infidel! I'll have your hand for that!\nSilliness aside, take these with a sackful of salt, as they are very subjective:\n7.0/10\nInteresting, but doesn't tug too hard on those heartstrings.\n8.5/10\nIf you're a history buff, you are in for a ride. The Holy Land! The Third Crusade! Islam and Christianity butting heads! Ancient conspiracies! Illuminati! (well, not exactly, but close enough) Violence! Madness! Infidel! I'll have your hand for that!\n8.0/10\nNothing much to shout about, but if I walked through Syria eight hundred years ago, I think this would be pretty accurate.\n6.5/10\nIf you are not a patient person, don't buy this game. Many a time I have pounded the table because something was tedious or inscrutably difficult. However, it wasn't so bad as to keep me from completing the game. Bringing some grey matter with you while playing is highly recommended.\n7.5/10\nIt's not a bad game, but it's not overwhelmingly awesome either. My main sticking point is in the gameplay. However, if you can tolerate that, I think you might like this classic.", "hours": 4.7, "username": "BOT Derek", "products": 63, "found_funny": 268, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-19", "text": "not great but a alright game if you want complte the set", "hours": 2.5, "user_id": "76561198076933110", "username": "dragonbreath100", "products": 41, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-18", "text": "I really don't understand all the hype around Assassin's Creed franchise. These first one seems like prototype with very many flaws. Only thing that I can really approve is graphics which are pretty good (in respect to release date). Story is so-so, it's good idea poorly executed with bad pacing (it gets better closer to the end). Sound/music is decent but nothing memorable. The biggest problems are emptiness of the world, lack of content and poor and overly simplistic combat. Also, this is a game about assassin's and there is no stealth. And to mention it, controls and camera could use some improvements but they are good enough most of the time. Overall, I am disappointent with first Assassin's Creed game.\n4,5/10", "hours": 15.6, "username": "crnisokol", "products": 658, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-17", "text": "The AC games are repetitive and the first one is awful about it.  Good game, but like many others, I played it to say \"I've played it\" and couldn't wait for it to end.", "hours": 15.8, "username": "Arten", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-16", "text": "From the old days, when Ubisoft isn't EA. Comes a game inspired from The Prince of Persia, that spawn a way better franchise than Prince of Persia. Assassin's Creed.\nYou probably already played the sequels, so now play the game that start it all. Where you will get totally dissapointed and bored if you already play the rest of the franchise. Play as Desmond Miles, a bartender who's actually have the most awesome family tree ever. Who was kidnapped by an evil company, like Ubisoft now, where he's forced to use a machine to play a game about his great great great great great great great great great great great great great great great great great grandfather, Altair, a Syrian assassin that spoke like he's from The United States. So with the Animus, you will journey to 1191 Syrian, where you ride along in Altair's quest to kill a few templars. How? By doing the same old side mission like, Listening to people talking, Pickpocketing, Collecting Flags, and Being hired as a bodyguard. When you're finished, you can kill those templars with your limited set of weapons like swords, hidden blades, throwing knives, and nothing else.\nSo, if you think Assassin's Creed Unity was bad, Black Flag is boring, AC3 is dull, and The Ezio Trilogy is awesome, this game is well pretty much worse than the others.\nStarring :\nSyrian Desmond, Assassin Saruman, Lex Luthor, One handed Bass, The 7 deadly templars, and nothing else.\nAssassin's Creed 1", "hours": 16.6, "user_id": "76561198113093878", "username": "Flying Banana", "products": 44, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-16", "text": "Assassin's Creed is a bit of a mixed bag. It's very well presented and entertaining, albeit repetitive and mundane at moments. My favorite aspects of the game are the story and general ambiance.\nThe plot follows Desmond, a bartender who's kidnapped by a corporation due to his lineage to assassins. After he's forced into a simulation that recreates the past by using the user's DNA, the player assumes control of Altair, a Crusades-era Middle Eastern assassin. After failing to follow a tenet of his organization, he's ordered to assassinate a set of targets in order to redeem himself. As he investigates his targets, he and Desmond begin to unearth a series of conspiracies. It's an interesting, well-written, and believable story. While it isn't remarkable, it manages to entertain.\nIn terms of atmosphere, the game has a simply sublime aesthetic due to it's blend of a Crusades-era Middle Ages and a modern-day subtle cyberpunk setting. The art direction is also great, and as a result it's visuals are arguably better than some later iterations in the series.\nHowever, gameplay-wise, it fails to live up. The story segments are enjoyable, however, in order to reach these segments, Altair has to investigate his targets. This consists of repeatedly racing across the map, beating up a target for information, and so forth. The game is also infamous for it's collectibles, which are arduous to collect and fail to provide a proper reward.\nOverall, Assassin's Creed is worth playing if one's interested in it. It's a game that was simply too ambitious for the time, and was rushed out in order to sell to the new console generation.", "hours": 61.2, "username": "Alex", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-15", "text": "This game can get a bit repetitive and linear at times, but it still proved to be a lot of fun. I got to kill people, and then upgrade my ability to kill people. The story line was good as it brought about more killing, and the graphics were good, especially the ones where you got to be murder-y. This probably sounds like the rant of a psychopath... But it's still a fun game. I liked Altair more than Ezio, which is probably the minority opinion. For the start of the series this worked pretty gosh darn well, the health mechanics as it related to the storyline was one of the more inspired ideas. Buy it, kill some gaurds and templars, throw some knives and nap in some bureaus.", "hours": 46.9, "username": "BEARD", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-14", "text": "Awkward and unfocused gameplay, with tragically awful writing. This game does a lot of things right, but at the end of the day it didn't work for me. Beautiful scenery, much wasted potential.", "hours": 13.0, "user_id": "76561197970800398", "username": "Wish", "products": 358, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 120, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-14", "text": "My first time playing any of the Assassin's Creed games, and I really got into it to my surprise!\nMuch easier if you can connect an Xbox controller than using the computer keyboard.", "hours": 15.8, "username": "MonklyStitch", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-13", "text": "I did play Assassin's Creed III which I loved, but the story of Desmond seemed really intresting and Assassin's Creed III was really fun.\nSo I bought It.\nGameplay could be a bit better but it's not really a problem.\nParkour could be better.\nAltair was an easy character to get use to and enjoy, but saddly you can't swim.\nThere is nice spaceing in the game. So you can run around, climb, and hide.\nStory was great!", "hours": 20.9, "user_id": "76561198120698777", "username": "King Diamond", "products": 27, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-13", "text": "One of the most immersive games i have ever played. I did not want to stop", "hours": 5.0, "user_id": "76561198178164415", "username": "Graves", "products": 62, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-13", "text": "This game was released on November 13, 2007. I am fairly new to the Assassin's Creed series and just recently began playing the second game on PS3. I highly recommend this game to anyone who plays any of the Assassin's Creed games. I wanted to play this one first because the storyline does connect to the other games and I didn't want to miss out. This game includes basic gameplay. No achievements, upgrades, money system, etc. Basic weapons and missions. The maps are very diverse and if you like challenges, you will enjoy flag hunting. There are a lot of flags to find throughout the game and several missions to complete.\nThe PC version of Assassin's Creed is the only one to have the Director's Cut Edition which includes 4 bonus missions. The following mission types are as follows: Archer Assassination, Rooftop Race Challenge, Merchant Stand Destruction Challenge, and Escort Challenge. You will be able to play these in each kingdom you travel through. Though these bonus missions are very basic compared to the latest Assassin's Creed games, they were unavailable on the console versions for the first game.\nAlso, Jesper Kyd composed the music for the game. He is known for several video game scores including the Hitman series, a few Assassin's Creed games, and Splinter Cell: Chaos Theory, to name a few.\nI give the game 5 out of 5 stars. It was excellent and the storyline is awesome.", "hours": 51.1, "username": "Red76", "products": 135, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-13", "text": "I love this game and a good start of a good serie.", "hours": 30.4, "user_id": "76561197976447316", "username": "borasezgin", "products": 2566, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-13", "text": "Broken", "hours": 5.1, "username": "Prasfear", "products": 370, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-12", "text": "I would much rather replay this 10 more times than buy Unity. The quality of these games have really gone downhill. While I find Assassin's Creed II more fun, this is certainly a good introduction to the series.", "hours": 15.8, "username": "do not engifear", "products": 57, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-12", "text": "A pretty crumby console port, to be honest. Even if you can set aside the genetic time-travel nonsense, I found the controls and free-running to be much too buggy and inconsistent for me, plus the clunky combat and avoidance mechanics were a pain. I say skip this one and instead pickup Shadows of Mordor, the Batman Arkham games, or even some of the better AC offerings.", "hours": 2.7, "user_id": "76561197974634162", "username": "istari101", "products": 392, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-11", "text": "This is the first Assassins Creed game, featuring Altair as the assassin. This title achieved a impressive recognition and is responsible for one of the most successful franchise of all time.\nAs all of AC games, the graphics are awesome, atmosphere is great and the historic context are very interesting. The problem with this game is that after play a number of missions you realize that the missions are kind of repetitive and then the game will be losing it\u00b4s appeal.  But anyway it\u00b4s a great game, it was a blow when released and have a important role in the games history.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "Boliv\u03bbr", "products": 320, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-11", "text": "This game created and defined a genre.\nIt shows it's age a bit at this point, but the gameplay remains fun and immersive.\nStop deliberating and get it. It's worth it.", "hours": 2.3, "username": "Some Newb", "products": 222, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 121, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-10", "text": "This game is so amazing. i couldnt help but think of Prince of Peria the entire time i played it, although the 2 are very similar. you may have heard the game is very repetitive, however, on PC, there is enough mission variety for you to feel you do things only once per region. the controls are very difficult as well as combat, but it seems to get easier throughout the game. Parkour combat and unique routes of going around assassinations were all great fun. Before, i played, i didn't think there would be much story beyond \"kill 9 dudes.\" Boy, was i wrong, the story is great, even with some twists and turns. I love the ancient Middle East setting, although i havent played any other assassin's creed games yet. The prsent day story line is actually really good as well despite what i heard, especially after the main campaign is completed... Easily a 9/ 10 now one of my favorite games.", "hours": 22.2, "username": "ShyGuyShayan", "products": 259, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-09", "text": "I love this game", "hours": 67.8, "username": "HellFyreQueen", "products": 127, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-07", "text": "the best game ever", "hours": 2.1, "username": "Young king", "products": 6, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-07", "text": "The game that started a very popular and succesful series. What I liked the most was the never seen before freedom of vertical movement. Climbing was probably the most satisfying element of this game. Story was very intriguing, although missions are very repetitive throughout the game. Game is split into several memories. You do a few side quests gathering information about local person of interest and then you proceed to asssassinate him. You repeat this formula until the very end boss battle. What broke the monotomy is returning to reality, to present, and learning more about the templars and Assassins in our time. Ending was very mysterious and opened infinite posibilities for future Assassin's Creed games which Ubisoft, as we all know, used very agressively. Not a year passes and we see another AC game. But about those later.\nAll in all, this game was something unique for its time and was a very solid game. It features increadibly lifelike cities and it is one of the best parkour games with very unique setting. Worst thing about it though, was trying to exit the game, which required something like 5 loading screens. But that was finally fixed. Main story gave me about 20-24 hours of gameplay, but there's tons of side things to do and explore which can prolong the game to over 30 hours.\nGameplay 7/10\nStory 8/10\nSound 8/10\nGraphics 7/10\nPolish 8/10\n-------------\nOverall 7.5/10 (very good game)", "hours": 23.6, "username": "Zeus_CM", "products": 432, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "One of my favourite Assassin / Stealth / Parkour kinda game. Gives the epic Atmospheric surroundings and a good storyline. This is where it all begins.", "hours": 18.8, "username": "EchoZero0ne", "products": 158, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "Runs great with everything maxed but I had frame drops during the last few chapters of the game with a gtx 760 and an i7 3770. Thanks to the community I got it to work with  a xbox one controller too.", "hours": 186.8, "user_id": "76561198083877607", "username": "Dr_N-gin", "products": 73, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-06", "text": "The story is gripping, however, the gameplay involves an awful lot of horseback riding, and the blend mechanic is a bit wierd (it drastically improves in all the later games).\nOverall, the story is fantastic, and the thrill of the chase (once you have ridden to a city) is great, and I would recommend this game, despite its minor flaws.", "hours": 18.9, "username": "ollie299792458", "products": 483, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-06-05", "text": "This game realy does not work on windows 7 (or maybe it does not work at all - I dont know)", "hours": 0.2, "user_id": "76561198008220397", "username": "rihards", "products": 70, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 122, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-06-05", "text": "Not bad. It only finally took me 8 years to start playing. I'm enjoying it so far. It's got an interesting concept behind it.\nA+, two thumbs up, very nice.", "hours": 59.8, "user_id": "76561198194049839", "username": "theiceman0021", "products": 6, "early_access": false}
