{"product_id": "15100", "page": 125, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-05", "text": "An oldie but a goodie, Assassin's Creed still holds up quite well in this day. The graphics don't look terrible, the gameplay is fun. The controls are a bit janky at times, and combat is pretty simple, but at the end of the day, it's a good game. Note: DO NOT GO FOR 100%. THOSE FLAGS GIVE YOU NOTHING.", "hours": 4.1, "username": "Valkoor", "products": 375, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 125, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-05-05", "text": "Love/Hate this game.\nI've played through this game to roughly the 50-75% mark because it's a beautiful engaging game. At the time of release, the game was very original, set in an era that more games should explore. The controls work really well,and it looks great, but there are points in the game where I sit watching nothing, and listening to dialog that doesn't at all help me, or add to my enjoyment of the game.\nThere are times where the game feels action packed and other times where tasks feel tedious. That's what usually causes me to lose interest. Leaving me with a game that I like, but can't bare to finish.", "hours": 17.0, "username": "Y2J1245", "products": 1145, "early_access": false}
