{"product_id": "15100", "page": 129, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-29", "text": "An ambitious open-world assassination game with some impressively realized locales and a serviceable story seemingly culled from the unused manuscripts of Dan Brown. Unfortunately, repetitive missions and combat and frustratingly inadequate stealth mechanics rob the game of its glory, resulting in an impressive yet significantly flawed game. Still, at this point, it's worth the price of admission, if only to see the game that started it all.", "hours": 19.8, "username": "Rush", "products": 509, "early_access": false}
