{"product_id": "15100", "page": 131, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-15", "text": "Odds are that you've either already played Assassin's Creed already, or never will so this review seems a bit like an exercise in futility so I'll keep it short.\nAssassin's Creed pretty much single-handedly created the open world parkour platformer game that everyone ended up making eventually. The game itself is still decent despite some design issues, such as doing the same repetitive side quests in order to progress the convoluted main story, or being able to beat the game by using a single combat move ad nauseam. Still, Assassin's Creed (both the first game and the series) does a great job of taking you through various historic locations and keeping you engaged as it does. It's a definite recommendation from me.", "hours": 10.5, "username": "PaulP", "products": 666, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 131, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-03-15", "text": "Best Assassin's Creed game in the series, because it was such a novel experience at the time it came out.  Great new mechanics, fun storyline, good game.", "hours": 28.2, "username": "Bartholomew Cubbins", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
