{"product_id": "15100", "page": 139, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-12", "text": "Algo para empezar a comentar acerca de la primera entrega de esta saga de asesinos es que a pesar de que no sea un juego que me guste mucho, la historia es interesante con un broche de buen final\nJugabilidad-(8): Mas viniendo de Ubisoft, no es una innovacion esto del parkour ya que en una de sus anteriores sagas, donde si que fue una jugabilidad totalmente novedosa, se aplico.\nNo son movimiento muy pulidos aun ya que al saltar o intentar acrobacias puedes no acertar a agarrarte a algun sitio y poder caer y bueno al igual que el sistema de lucha que se hace algo repetitivo al ver que las muertes son casi siempre iguales, a pesar de ello no esta mal del todo, son unos movimientos caracteristicos que le da algo de vida a este juego.\nGraficos-(8,9): No esta mal graficamente esta obra, pero si que se puede apreciar el personaje el cual manejamos esta bastante cuidado graficamente mientras el resto no lo estan tanto, al igual que algunos objetos o el trasfondo de escenario no jugable que vemos al subir a las torres para sincronizar, pero en general es una buena cosa que tiene este juego\nSonido-(8): Este juego no es muy destacale en el apartado de sonido, no tiene una banda sonora de la que uno pueda quedar impresionado, bien es cierto que en ese apartado se podrian haber hecho las cosas muchos mejores, aunque no deja de tener encanto pasar por las calles del pueblo y encontrar pregoneros y gente recitando un discurso que es un bonito detalle de epoca.\nInnovacion-(7,8): Si, el titulo en si es innovador, pero a la vez no, la idea como juego basado en hechos historicos hecho y planteado de esta manera no se ha visto en ningun otro titulo pero digamos que no deja de tener un poco de otro juegos anteriores, lo cual no quiere decir nada malo, hay sagas que le pasan lo mismo y son estupendas, pero no puede ser todo lo innovador de lo que decian\nEn resumen, en mi experiencia, no es un juego de mis favoritos la verdad, y no creo que lo vuelva a jugar dado a que la mayoria del juego se me hace pesado y repetitivo, siempre el mismo procedimiento a la hora de asesinar y asi hasta unas 9 veces, auque es cierto que en el final tiene un poco de cambio, que para mi gusto, es una de las mejores partes del juego\nPuntos fuertes:\n+Representa muy bien la epoca de la edad media junto con tematicas como la de los temmplarios\n+Graficamente esta bien dise\u00f1ado en cuanto a ciudad y abiente de la epoca\n+Es un sandbox interesante a la hora de explorarlo\nPuntos debiles:\n-Monotono a veces hasta la medula\n-La escasa variedad de ejecuccion de enemigos y de armas\n-La historia de Desmond no recobra mucho protagonismo salvo al final, pasa a un segundo plano\n-A veces es absurdo preparar un asesinato con demasiados desafios, pues el procedimiento no se diferenciara mucho", "hours": 17.0, "username": "Osuna", "products": 209, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 139, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-12", "text": "This game is reason why Assassin's Creed: Unity sucks balls !\nAt time when this game was released Ubisoft find their Gold Mine and estabilished new franchise called Assassin's Creed which is still active to this day.\nSome people called this game a repetetive but even if you consider that its still a hell lot of fun !\nInnovative gameplay mechanics,Stealth,Epic Story,Realistic Parkour and Amazing graphics to this day !\nWhat more should i tell to convince you of buying ???\n90%\nFeel like a real assassin,Defend your brotherhood,Explore the HUGE world and discover the terrible truth !\n-Chobotik", "hours": 3.6, "username": "AntiSocialBoy", "products": 630, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 139, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-12", "text": "hated it", "hours": 1.6, "username": "Sidney", "products": 1021, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 139, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-11", "text": "A so-so start for the game's franchise.\nPros:\n+ Graphics are really great and still hold up good even today\n+ Locations (Masyaf, Damascus, Acre, Jerusalem and Arsuf) seem realistic and nice\n+ Running and parkour-ing from rooftop to rooftop is very fun and cool (though it gets boring after a while)\n+ The combat system is quite good and can result in very stylish kills/assassinations if you master it (similar to Batman: Arkham Asylum's combat system, though not as good as the latter's)\n+ The story is good enough: the whole concept of the animus and reliving the memories of your ancestors stored in your DNA, plus the alternate history scenario are both nice (it reminds you a bit of an alternative matrix story too)\nCons:\n- The biggest downside of the game is, in my opinion, its repetitiveness: in each and every city you go, you end up doing essentially the same things (pickpocket, assassinate, eardrop, save citizens, end up being discovered by the guards -> run and hide over and over again etc.), while only the boss fights are different each time and offer a nice challenge\n- The lunatics and beggars that hit you or stop you while you are running to escape can get really really (and I mean really really) annoying, especially since they multiply in the final levels of each city\n- The characters in the game are a bit dull and not easy to connect with, both the ancient and the modern ones, but only just a bit, generally they are ok\nOverall this is a good game, you can feel it and I can recommend it, but its repetitiveness in each level is its biggest weakness in my opinion, it makes it feel boring after a few times, even though you get to do really cool things... if only the tasks were more different each time.\nThankfully I read that the next installments (kind of) fixed that and made the progressing of the game more enjoyable and less repetitive, so I have that to keep me and eventually continue to the next game.", "hours": 32.6, "username": "Buttman", "products": 509, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 139, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-11", "text": "This game's an odd one, in a way, I'm not sure I can describe it.\nAssassin's Creed felt a bit unfinished game, more like a game mechanic test of some kind, but still, I think it's the one I like the most in the whole series.\nIt wasn't perfect, not even near, but it had that certain challenge, that just made me feel good for surviving. This has definitely the hardest combat, and it's just SO GOOD. When the game was published, it was one-of-a-kind and it kind of still is. Assassin's Creed II changed so much, that it feels like a totally different game. (Don't get me wrong, loved AC2 also)\nIt's sad, how many people, who play the games of this series have skipped the first part, though. They missed a lot.", "hours": 21.9, "user_id": "76561198046741114", "username": "Glass Half-Spilled", "products": 247, "early_access": false}
