{"product_id": "15100", "page": 140, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-05", "text": "It took me a couple tries to get going on this game.  I saw it described as the natural progression of the Prince of Persia series, and that makes complete sense.  The sets in this game are beautiful, the cities feel alive and bustling.  I found the story to be *extremely* compelling, particularly Desmond's.", "hours": 22.8, "username": "Autumnal", "products": 1512, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 140, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-05", "text": "To Windows 8.1 users:\nThe game randomly crashes which are caused after completing certain events. (Example, completing the quest or collecting flags for achievements). So buy it if your willing to bear with it or wait until someone fixes the game.\nThe game is still good after 7 years. It's like wine. Let it age and it will taste even better in the future.", "hours": 24.8, "user_id": "76561198061095473", "username": "Nomadic_Engi", "products": 102, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 140, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-05", "text": "Finished the game below 10 Hours, Good game, but there is some glitchy when trying to take vistas..\n8/10", "hours": 3.1, "user_id": "76561198073848058", "username": "Bentod", "products": 23, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 140, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-04", "text": "good game gets boring tho", "hours": 19.7, "username": "Snowtrain", "products": 68, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 140, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-04", "text": "One of the best series, beautiful environment, a very good way of fighting, long gameplay. Certainly it must buy.\n9/10", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Scotsman", "products": 148, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 140, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-04", "text": "i really like assassin's creed games but this one isn't so funny when the fullscreen turns off automatik and then you have to restart the game over and over again and it's a pain in the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 Unless they fix the bug this game is a waste of money.", "hours": 38.0, "username": "Danny D", "products": 30, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-03", "text": "Assassin's Creed is a game about repetition. You enter a city, do two or three information jobs, then you go kill your target. It's that for the entire game. What sets this game apart from others is its originality. A world like this has never been seen in video games and it's a truely unique experience if a little dated. Give this one a shot if you're wanting to begin the Assassin's Creed series.", "hours": 12.7, "username": "spiceninja", "products": 721, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-03", "text": "Great Introduction to the whole Assasins and Templars Story line playing as Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad.\n9/10 Nice Gameplay and Environment.", "hours": 27.0, "username": "Ys", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-03", "text": "Start of a dynasty", "hours": 2.7, "user_id": "76561198037211832", "username": "Verity", "products": 303, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-03", "text": "First installment of a great, great, awesome series. I personally prefer the Ezio (II, brotherhood, revalations) storyline. This game will get you started with an awesome series. It has great playability as a start out game, but less so after you did the newer ones, since you lose alot of functionality when you don't play yhe games in order.\nFor an older game its pretty cool, If you don't care to much about 100% (collect a load of flags, bit boring) you'll easily get 15-20 hours out of it. Afterwards just move on to AC2 :)", "hours": 15.0, "user_id": "76561197961548510", "username": "Nescio", "products": 69, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-02", "text": "NO UPLAY 10/10", "hours": 2.4, "username": "leffereality", "products": 604, "found_funny": 434, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-02", "text": "For it's time the game was really good. Playing it now it feels a little dated. If you want to get into the franchise I would say to read up on the first game and skip playing it just to start with the second one since it fixes a lot of the problems me and other people had with this one. Also the lack of subtitles makes it kind of hard to make out some things people are saying (expecially when trying to hear though the vents.) All and all it is a good game I would just say if you don't like it to skip it and move on.", "hours": 9.6, "username": "Snorlaxin", "products": 987, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-01", "text": "The biggest problem here is that it gets repetitive. Repetitive quests, traversal, combat. Thankfully combat changes with new abilities, with experience of the player, with difficulty of enemies. Moving through the world doesn't, and has some problems, but otherwise is a lot of fun. That leaves the story progress which sadly isn't very interesting. The story is cool, the method to get to it is not. And I can not imagine collecting all those flags. Pure insanity :D. So this one is a bit \"grindy\". Not exactly how I like action adventure games.\nAs for the look of the game, it's all very pretty :).\nAnd why does quitting the game need to take so many screens and button presses? :P\nAnyway, the first Assassin's Creed is a fine game. Certainly makes me want to continue the saga. It's my first AC so can't compare to the others. Good enough start this is.", "hours": 19.5, "user_id": "76561197968468189", "username": "themooddoom", "products": 472, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2015-01-01", "text": "Rubbish jumped into a Haystack and the game Auto saved on a glitch while my character is falling through the map, Everytime I reload the save its glitching out the map and kills me with a de-sync, Uninstalled.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "Razz", "products": 197, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-01", "text": "The pc version of Assassin's creed is a bit better then the console version. With its extra missions the game has become less 'repeatable'. The gameplay isn't bad but also can't really blow us away.", "hours": 54.1, "user_id": "76561197997821626", "username": "cronodude360", "products": 238, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 141, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-01-01", "text": "This game does have some slightly framerate stability issues due to porting issues, but the game ultimately plays the best and looks the best on the PC.", "hours": 1.3, "user_id": "76561197970527145", "username": "Jedah", "products": 265, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-31", "text": "My blade sees for me\u2026 It cuts through the darkness.\nThis is how it all began, the journey of Desmond Miles and his Assassin-ancestors. You play as Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad, the assassin who founded the Order of the assassins. As Alta\u00efr, you have to uncover the secrets of the creed and the mysterious apple of eden, while fighting against your enemies, the templar!\nIt is a good game on it's own, but definatly not as good as it's sequels, since you can't even air-assassinate people here. This game clearly isn't made for a Pc Keyboard, but for consoles, so I suggest you get a Gamepad to play with before you play this game with the frustrating controls of the Pc version.\n5/10", "hours": 9.7, "username": "NightCloud", "products": 173, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-30", "text": "Refreshing Game as i am new to the AC series. I wanted to play the entire series from start to finish and what a way to start. It is almost a complete game for me, I am familiar with other reviews this game has received and some negativity. But you hardly notice any fault as you play this game. Its a lot of fun, and it is what i look for in games such as this. A lot of climbing and jumping, the fighting mechanics is awesome compared to other games. I can go on for hours with the good.\nA few bad points;\n1. Running into people, may loose control of player.\n2. Cut away scenes get annoying after a while.\n3. Player jumps onto walls repeatedly gets annoying as it makes no progress climbing.\nGet this game if you like to have fun. Something they forgot about in AC Unity", "hours": 32.2, "username": "Prince Idrana", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-30", "text": "First of the saga. Not bad, but full of defects. No need to play to this one except if you want to know the whole story of Desmond.", "hours": 32.5, "user_id": "76561198001584035", "username": "BobMammoth", "products": 314, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-30", "text": "The gameplay is very cool though somewhat repetitive.  The combat is simple the brutal assasination cut scenes grabs your attention. The graphics breathtaking.  This is the game that got me to buy several series of the game that I have yet to finish because of the sheer tasks and objectives that I want to get and accomplish.  But like I said, this game started it all.  The first installment of an amazing game series.  All of the AC games, nothing beats the original and no Uplay by Ubisoft before you start the game.", "hours": 23.4, "user_id": "76561198112486038", "username": "The Infamous El Guapo", "products": 1046, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "This was the real assassin's creed. the one and only. Altair. Dedicated, passionate, driven by ideal, completely focussed. An ideal assassin. Ezio and the rest were a bunch of womanizers.", "hours": 13.6, "username": "Complexkay", "products": 147, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "Picked this up on sale and can't say I am disappointed. Graphics not bad for a 5+ year old game and worked with my controller. Great story and enjoy exploring the world.\ncons\n-controls can be Clunky/touchy at times but the game is forgiving\n-engaging in battle can be fun taking out as many with one shot as possible, but once your in combat with sword it can be a little lackluster\n-can be a bit repetitive, especially if you do all the side quests.", "hours": 12.2, "username": "DarkkDragon", "products": 320, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "Nice game...=D", "hours": 27.8, "username": "-=]|S.M.I.L.E.Y|[=-", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "This is the good game for the fist step of Assassin'creed series\nbut the quest in the game have some point of boring", "hours": 1.6, "username": "Verseruz", "products": 25, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-29", "text": "So, you'll probably notice that my gameplay time isn't that high, and, well, I have a good reason for that. The gameplay. In my opinion, this game had one of the worst types of gameplay I've ever come across, so this kind of forced me to try and get through the game as fast as I could. The fighting was very bland, the missions were VERY repetetive, and to be honest, I didn't enjoy any of the fights. There's also the fact that there were no subtitles, which is a must-have for me, very limited soundtrack, Altair spoke in an American accent in a time where America didn't even exist (Yes, I'm aware that they change his voice in Revelations, although I haven't played it yet.) and it was far too easy to escape the guards. One of the things I really did enjoy, though, is the storyline, especially the bits with the one-armed assassin. I'd recommend this to anyone who can stomache bad gameplay for a good story, but otherwise, I don't feel like this game deserves a recommendation. Unless, of course, you're planning on understanding the whole series' story.", "hours": 17.8, "username": "Nani the Fuck?!", "products": 186, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 142, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-28", "text": "Good game for it's time, I personally find the Assassins Creed franchise a bit repatitive in terms of game mechanics and it kills the games for me, the storyline in this game is passible but not gripping, the game mostly focuses on introducing you to sneaking around and killing whoever you please like a bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\n8/10", "hours": 11.4, "username": "LowNineFive", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-28", "text": "I finished this game on the xbox. Yes the missions were the same, but i really enjoyed my time playing the game. For me personally, i have a hard time playing this game on the PC. I wonder how the \"master race\" as you call yourself, are doing this. With a controller it is so much easier.\nI would recommend playing this on a console.", "hours": 27.4, "user_id": "76561198081648492", "username": "linkz0rs", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-28", "text": "The one that started a amazing franchise.", "hours": 6.6, "username": "Moffeltje", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "I really enjoy this game. This is my introduction into the franchise and I thought Assassin's Creed 1 was really good starter. The only problem I had was the amount of time it takes to fully exit the game tied in with minimizing the window without glitching up or accidentially closing the game window. However, other then that, I love it.", "hours": 24.6, "username": "Kebabalicious", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "-Hide In Plain Sight\n-Stay Your Blade From The Flesh of an Innocent\n-Never Compromise The Brotherhood\nSeems to me I always break these tenets. :D", "hours": 18.8, "username": "Meowww~", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "Altair can't even swim in water\nApparently water is toxic and touching it is instant death\n11/10 for realism", "hours": 21.2, "username": "NecroTed", "products": 807, "found_funny": 240, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "I have created a pie chart to show you what your gaming experience will be like:\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _ _#####&&&&&\n_ _ _ _ _########&&&&&&&&\n_ _ _###########&&&Doing&&&\n_ _############&&&Side-&&&&&\n_#############&&&Missions&&&&\n_#############&&&&&&&&&$$$$$\n##############&&&&&$$$Assass-$\n##############&$$$$$$$$inations$\n#############################\n_############################\n_#########Running from########\n_ _##########Guards#########\n_ _ _######################\n_ _ _ _ _################\n_ _ _ _ _ _ _##########", "hours": 30.9, "username": "Dr. Steel, Professor of Memology", "products": 145, "found_funny": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "Starter of the franchise and as such navigation and side quests lack behind the second part. Positive though, that it isn't divided into a million sub-levels like with AC2 . Also, it is historically closest to reality and thus in this sense the most interesting part.\nWeapons are quite basic, compared to the other AC's, but the graphics are still enjoyable besides it's age, though cannot compete with the latest sequels.\nOf course, forget about the Animus gibberish and the 21st Century story (nobody needed it anyway) which acts as a mere distraction and bear in mind that this game is far more repetitive than the follow-up ones. As well, I found some earlier missions harder due to the lack of equipment than later ones.\nI still give it a plus and recommend the series in generell, if you liked the Batman franchise or just love medivian costumes.", "hours": 86.9, "username": "600piecesof8", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "Extremely repetitive.", "hours": 19.8, "user_id": "76561198042184560", "username": "TwoArmedMan", "products": 263, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-27", "text": "When this game was first released it introduced a kind of gameplay never before seen, giving you whole cities to explore top to bottom, and even now over seven years later this game is willing to take you back a thousand years to a beautiful middle eastern landscape and throw you into a bloody secret war between the Assassins and Templars.  This game is what the Assassin's Creed franchise was all about before it became a franchise by giving you something new and original, pulling you out of reality from modern times, quite litterally threw the animus, to the past giving gamers an almost cinematic experience that does its job at getting the player interested in the its story.", "hours": 0.8, "username": "AlixChevalier", "products": 776, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 143, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Pros\n+Good story that its actually based on some real events. (which make it very interesting)\n+Parkour style gameplay (+stealth) allows you to approach your target as you want.\n+The architecture of the cities represented perfectly\n+Voice acting is quite good\n___\nCons\n-Altair can't swim\n-You get a little bored during the investigations you do before the main mission can be access\n-Lack of armor or weapons upgrades\n-Repettetive speeches and no subtitles\nAssassin's Creed is definitely worth every penny. Particularly if bought on sale.", "hours": 17.4, "user_id": "76561198056000019", "username": "bulletcluster", "products": 250, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 144, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-26", "text": "Open world fighting game\nCool story, in depth characters. Interesting gameplay aspects. Unrealistic, but still fun.\nIts and old game so the graphics aren\u2019t that great, but to be expected. Its really repetitive. But if you find it entertaining enough the repetitiveness won\u2019t bother you", "hours": 21.0, "username": "M4j1k N1nj4", "products": 453, "early_access": false}
