{"product_id": "15100", "page": 146, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-18", "text": "One of the best games of the century - a lot harder and more punishing than the later installments. Worth a play if you haven't yet picked it up. - 9/10", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561197980926911", "username": "Colby", "products": 436, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 146, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-16", "text": "This game is a bit odd. On the one hand it's a good game with a cool concept. But on the other hand it's taken back a bit by the fact that it's just drowning in repetitive tasks. Get used to do the same three things over and over again. After a while it kills the immersion. I found myself doing the minimum of tasks just to get back to the plot. But all in all it was a good game that definitely got a much better sequel.", "hours": 16.6, "username": "Crim", "products": 1390, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 146, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-14", "text": "This is the most inconsistently frustrating game I've played all year. The game seems designed to make you think it has quality and then it punches you in the face with annoying NPCs and redundant quests that have nothing to do with the sparse primary storyline. I'm bailing on it half-way through. I have better, less frustratingly annoying games yet to start. That, and my cursing at the screen has my wife concerned for my physchological state. Seriously? I know people swear by this series, and I purchased several titles in the series on super-sale a while ago; but I think I'm putting this in my \"I hate the Game Mechanics\" library category. I'll watch the YouTube \"Let's Play\" to finish the primary story. This game has way to much grinding and struggling with swooping camera struggles for my taste.", "hours": 26.2, "username": "Xonikz", "products": 313, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 146, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-13", "text": "With its riveting story, beautiful visuals and surprisingly lifelike world, Assassin's Creed is an incredibly deep, enjoyable game that kept us addicted from beginning to bizarre end.\nAlthough not completely historically accurate. The game still has a fascinating and well thought out story with good replayable gameplay. This game also has awesome graphics and cool cutscenes. Each character is unique and important to storyline and dialog is interesting.\n10/10", "hours": 25.4, "username": "mkinG", "products": 595, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 146, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-13", "text": "So I recently bought Black Flag off the Steam autumn sale, and it hit me. I haven't actually touched the Assassin's Creed series yet. I own 1-4 and Brotherhood/Revelations. It was always on my \"to do\" list and it kept getting pushed to the side. Well I finally got to playing the first one.\nIf like me you've played any of the modern \"Prince of Persia\" games Ubisoft released a couple generations ago, then it won't take long for you to get into the gameplay. The game is built on the concept of parkour, scaling walls and running over the city rooftops and pieces of environment. It's basically a free running sandbox, with the goal of stealthily killing select targets in your missions.\nI have had people tell me that Assassin's Creed 1 has got nothing on 2, but I decided to play through 1 anyway, and for a first in the series? It's pretty solid. It did feel like it was missing a key element or two in it's formula, and that's what I assume 2 addresses. But for a new IP it's definitely a strong start.\nOnly real complaint is that you never pull off an assassination as cool as the opening FMV. At least, I couldn't figure out how to do something like that anyway. The game is still quite enjoyable besides. If you plan to play the entire series, getting the first game on sale is worthwhile.", "hours": 15.4, "username": "MeleeKirby", "products": 1787, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 146, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-13", "text": "excellent game", "hours": 12.3, "username": "CrePoW\u2122\u30c5\u25e2 \u25e4\u30c5#Coach", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
