{"product_id": "15100", "page": 147, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-12-07", "text": "Combats are basically quick time events, quests are highly repetitive, camera likes to freak out oftentimes, AI is ridicolous, the automatic save system is trash\nAdd to all that the crazy and drunk people in the street costantly pushing you, killing you in the water, blowing your cover... Altair didn't kill civilians, but boy how much I enjoyed cutting the throat of every single of these guys, I don't care, de-sync me all day long!\n5/10 because of the story and the pretty 2008 graphics, but honestly save your money and read it up on a  wiki", "hours": 12.4, "username": "Markinho", "products": 182, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 147, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-07", "text": "This is the real assassin's creed. Any other AC like Unity or Black Flag is not welcome.\nI give this an 8/8.", "hours": 0.7, "user_id": "76561198011004336", "username": "Dr. Stone Trophy", "products": 377, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 147, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-12-06", "text": "Sometimes during a battle the character not responding well, and there are some annoying bugs.\nThis first game of the series could be much better!\nBut I will recommend this game and vote positive, because in general this is a good game.\n*Awesome Story\n*Good graphics for 2007\n*Good background Music\n*Good sound effects\n*Sometimes during a battle, the character not responding well\n*Once i had a problem with the sound of the citizens in Jerusalem", "hours": 33.4, "username": "lofty", "products": 38, "early_access": false}
