{"product_id": "15100", "page": 150, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-23", "text": "Monotone, boring, downright awful piece of a game, that's how I would describe the first Assassin's Creed entry. The missions are so unbelievably tedious it almost hurts. Fetch some flags here kill couple of random guards who spawn out of your\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665there, climb a tower to unlock the map now rinse and repeat 50 more times. That pretty much sums up what the game is all about. The story is almost non existent, you're just on your way killing 9 random dudes because they are bad doing bad stuff there is absolutly no motivation whatsoever. The parkour part is partly broken. For some reason Altair keeps jumping in every direction except the one I want him to, he also gets constantly stuck looking at the damn edge of a building which is 10 cm above his head instead of climbing it up. Come on man, you're a goddamn assassin, that's ridiculous! At the end I wouldn't recommend this game to anyone, just start with the second entry which is by miles better and offers tons more of content than this piece of garbage.", "hours": 9.9, "username": "DonGurke", "products": 523, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 150, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-22", "text": "Story: Excellent concept, but very poor dialogue script. The people are neither charismatic nor interesting (except the ones you assassinate).\nGameplay: On the one hand plain horrible (mission design, fighting  balancing/AI, annoying and repetitive side quests), but on the other hand great level design and \"jump and run\" mechanic! It makes so much fun to race the rooftops of ancient cities! :)\nPresentation: Pretty impressive for its time (I guess). Besides its character design or overall logic flaws (like running around in full armor and wearing the brotherhood's emblem is ignored by the game world. ..And in case things get hot, all you have to do is clap your hand to disguise as a monk (!), sit on a bench only seconds after being chased (!!) or jump off a hundrets of meter high building & land in a hey waggon (!!!).", "hours": 16.5, "user_id": "76561197972870150", "username": "Zhiu", "products": 342, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 151, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-22", "text": "12/10 like Skyrim with assassins", "hours": 12.7, "username": "Kendrick Lamario", "products": 193, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 151, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-22", "text": "Years ago when Assassin's Creed first came out, I wasn't impressed. I played a few hours of it, only to walk away annoyed and disappointed. Recently however, when the majority of the Assassin's Creed franchise was on sale for less than $5 a game, I decided to give it another try. That was one of the best decisions I've made in gaming and I've been hooked ever since.\nThe true historical applications of the game, albeit slighty modified, is intriguing, educational, and very well-done. I felt as though I really was fighting an oppressive force during the Third Crusade in the Holy Land in 1191. This game takes advantage of historical events, locations, and terminology in the same way the Metal Gear series does. The ancestoral concept throughout the game was like nothing I've ever seen in a game and brought a uniqueness to it. The protagonist, Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad, is a competent fighter and agile acrobat. The growth of character witnessed during the course of the game was satisfying and gave you a clearer understanding of what the creed means.\nOn the other hand, the tasks were a little repetitive and stealth wasn't very prevalant. You had very few ways to sneak up on someone and would rather kill someone then have to run away each time. Regardless, the game was immensely satisfying and paved way for numerous sequels that I loved as well.\nThis is a must buy.", "hours": 31.0, "username": "Maul Scarreign", "products": 78, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 151, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-11-22", "text": "\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 you auto target lock, stop switching to sword you\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665i can 1shot these lowlifes with hidden blade", "hours": 24.8, "username": "IZftw", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 151, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-22", "text": "It's Buggy, controls can be awkward when you first play, there are an excess of menus, and missions can be fustrating and annoying by how they are designed, yet inspite of all of this, the game managed to captivate my attenion and keep me coming back for more.\nIt has an alluring atmosphere, intresting characters, and an alright story. The voices can be a bit bland, the ending is a little weak, and the Desmond scenes feel like an abrupt stop sign, but overall the story still works.\nThis is my personal favorite of the Assassin's Creed Series. This is the original Assassin's Creed, and despite what some may think about more recent installments in the series, this game still delivers the experience that made the series so popular.\nThere is a high resolution fan mod I would recommend with this, you can find it in the guide section for this game.", "hours": 126.6, "user_id": "76561198058904839", "username": "Heretic", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 151, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-22", "text": "A great game made greater in HD. Controller settings are poor to begin with, but after tweaking with the bindgins, you can find a playable layout. If I had any advice to new players to the AC series, it would be to stop buying games from Ubisoft. Except for this one. This one's okay.", "hours": 2.5, "username": "Edison", "products": 86, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 151, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-11-21", "text": "This is a phenominal game. A great place for a franchise to start, with great storytelling, and a plot that will keep you guessing. While the voice audio is less then steller, you can learn to deal with it.", "hours": 122.9, "username": "RoboEggGaming", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
