{"product_id": "15100", "page": 159, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-20", "text": "Great game.  If you haven\u2019t played it, you should.\nPros:\nStoryline, gameplay, visuals, and overall enjoyment (for it's time) 10/10.\nCons:\n-Widely considered to be overly repetitive in some of it's missions (I did not find this to be an issue)\n-This is a port so you may occasionally run into bugs, although nothing that makes the game unplayable.  If you have a NVidia graphics card I found that enabling VSync in the NVidia control panel fixed all my issues.", "hours": 18.8, "username": "Pertransient", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 159, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-19", "text": "In 2008 a new IP was released by Ubisoft which quickly turned into a huge franchise with yearly iterations. Story, setting and atmosphere are great, the main problem is that the gameplay becomes repetitive quite fast. Overall a must-play though.", "hours": 20.6, "username": "vai90", "products": 1250, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 159, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-18", "text": "As much as this game had potential to be good, it falls short in way too many areas for me to think its any more than a 6/10. I really wanted to enjoy this game, but theres nothing about this game that goes beyond good. For starters, the controls are unnecessarily complicated. The fact that it takes 2 buttons and WASD to sprint really proves that. The whole high profile low profile aspect of the controls really make the entire thing feel really clunky. This also leaks over into the combat, which I love in concept, but in execution eventually becomes hold down RMB and then spam LMB after theyre done attacking, at least until you get countering. After that, the combat becomes even more of a joke. Parkour doesn't feel satisfying in the slightest, really all you have to do is press \"W\" and RMB and press space when you plateau. All of this gets really repetitive fast with a storyline that reflects 2 boring AAA movies forced together , a main character that almost borders on shadow the hedgehog levels of edge and sci-fi elements that are completely uncalled for. I really wanted to like\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665crud, but if I want to play a good open world stealth game, i'd just play Sly Cooper 2 or 3 which does everything this game does better.\n6/10", "hours": 3.2, "username": "Yakman", "products": 408, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 159, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-18", "text": "Now where do I begin.....\nTHis game isnt perfect by no means especially on the PC, I have encountered so many bugs and have had the game crash on me dozens of times, but this game just has that charm with it that you can't just can't say no to. the story in my opinion is great which kept me in the game and the mechanics at the time were revolutionary even though they were a mess looking back at it. Yes it gets very repeatative when you are finding information for each assassination and some of them drove me up the wall but performing that assassination without a problem was just so rewarding. Recomending this game however I just can't do, I love the assassin creed series and I'm always telling people to play them but for PC this was a buggy mess and my DX 10 file would not play so I had to use the DX 9 and that still didnt work perfectly. I recommend you play this on console as it is more stable and less bugs, the graphics might not be up to scratch with the PC but the gameplay will imporve dramatically and less bugs will occur\nRating 7/10  but as mentioned will play better on consoles", "hours": 11.1, "user_id": "76561198134844142", "username": "Mr Leffiluff", "products": 665, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 159, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-18", "text": "Assassins creed was an interesting game. loved climbing buildings and mingling with the crowd.  However, it blurrs the lines between killing and murder; one line that clashed with my beleifs, making it hard for me to truely experience the game.  if You are into parkour, then you can get a little kick out of it.", "hours": 11.9, "user_id": "76561198048486148", "username": "Rei Shards", "products": 191, "early_access": false}
