{"product_id": "15100", "page": 160, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-10-17", "text": "Assassin's Creed is the first entry of the franchise and an unforgettable one.  Set during the third crusade, you play as Altair, an arrogant master assassin whose pride almost ruins his order.  He get's another chance to redeem himself and that's where you come in.  Here are the pros and cons:\nPositives:\n- Interesting Sandbox assassin game.\n- Excellent setting during the third crusade.\n- Inventive gameplay and different approaches to take down the targets.\n- Lively cities.\n- Bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665protagonist.\nNegatives:\n- Extremely repetitive process: go to bureau, climb buildings to get sight of event points, solve events, get information, go to bureau, take down the target, run away, go back to the Mualim.\n- Desmond's story line is completely boring.\n- That ending...\nVerdict: A-", "hours": 24.3, "user_id": "76561198018443943", "username": "Cadis Etrama Di Raziel", "products": 358, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 160, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-17", "text": "The first Assassin's Creed. For its time, it had great graphics, an ok-ish storyline, and repetitive gameplay. Nice to play if you really like the genre, but you can skip it for something more modern. Only recommended for AC fans.", "hours": 6.2, "username": "The Falcon", "products": 202, "early_access": false}
