{"product_id": "15100", "page": 161, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-10-12", "text": "The game mainly consists of assassinating 9 key figures throughout 3 districts of 3 cities. In order to assassinate them, you must first complete a few missions which boil down to collecting items, pickpocketing a person, or assassinating another person. There are 6 of these missions in each district along with around 10 missions where you save citizens from guards. You don't have to complete them all to move on in the story and there's no incentive to. You don't gain any kind of reward for doing anything beyond the bare minimum and even the activities that you do are extremely repetitive. The game looks and sounds like it should be fun, but it's basically just grinding the same things over and over with nothing to motivate you.", "hours": 9.4, "username": "Killer Kid Clever", "products": 737, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
