{"product_id": "15100", "page": 172, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-16", "text": "This is a great game. Absolutely fantastic. It is my favorite video game series ever and though it is a bit repetative at times it is one of the best games I have ever played. There are a few annoying things with windowed mode and dual moniters and stuff, but they are avoidable and don't stop the game from being a master piece.", "hours": 3.1, "username": "SpinDerp", "products": 402, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 172, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-15", "text": "Brilliant series - Assassins, Pirates, Conspiracy theories, Twisted Plots, roof jumping and more!\nWorks fine on pc and controls are easy to master however some players may prefer to use a joystick controller\nGathering all the flags in the first episode unlocks extra levels for back stories", "hours": 33.5, "username": "EwwaBean", "products": 130, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 173, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-14", "text": "Loved it, looking forward on playing the rest of the series\nOnly one thing I did not like :- While jumping from building Altair's momentum does not apply and you sometimes just suddenly drop... annoying\n9/10", "hours": 13.9, "user_id": "76561198057074200", "username": "Recall", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 173, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-14", "text": "Relatively easy to beat. Combat is decent. They were really confident in making a sequeal/many sequeals, because there is no \"definite\" ending to this game.\nPros: Free-running, amazing kills and an interesting storyline.\nCons: Funny AI, some bugs and \"eagle eye\" is the worse vision feature I have ever seen. Historical inaccuracies.\nThe idea of assassinating people is to kill a few, to saves the lives of many. Ironically, there are many cases in which you kill like a GAZILLION soldiers to save ONE poor civilian. I have probably killed about a few hundred guards in a city of a few thousands [Jerusalem] but I guess it's still less than 0.1% so thats' okay. Makes you wonder who is right after all. Still, \"\n\", so even the creed can be cast away once awhile.\nOverall, It's a good game. Would recomend.", "hours": 22.3, "username": "Ascorbic Acid", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 173, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-12", "text": "Such an amazing series! Extremely addictive, would recommend this game to anyone!!", "hours": 17.5, "username": "Betahouse | Bradoeoe", "products": 234, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 173, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-12", "text": "This has to be THE MOST frustratiing game I've ever played, in fact I've deleted it. I should have known beter than to buy the first addition having played 3 first. IMHO...", "hours": 31.5, "user_id": "76561198060506395", "username": "DunMac", "products": 65, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 173, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-12", "text": "I've heard so much about the assassins creed games over the years that I decided I finally should jump in.  I didn't make it.  I drowned.\nBut seriously,  I think unless you are a big fan of the series you may as well skip to the newer games.  Even though the graphics aren't too dated I found the controls to be awkward and the story to be slow and uninteresting.  Games have come a long way in the last 10 years and it shows with this title.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "951Jimbo", "products": 473, "early_access": false}
