{"product_id": "15100", "page": 178, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-23", "text": "This is the perfect game for you if you want to spend one hour on gameplay, and twenty on stupid, meaningless yet unskippable cutscenes.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "Leachaiem", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 178, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-22", "text": "Horrible story, good graphics, boring repetitive gameplay. Nope.\nSeriously, I got about half way through the game and realized, this is awful. This story is just some done to death templar nonsense. The gameplay is just a bunch of QTEs. The voice acting is totally removes you from any ambiance the game is trying to create.\nI Really, REALLY wish i hadn't spent money on this game.", "hours": 19.4, "user_id": "76561198043972761", "username": "Professor ZeitGeist\u2122", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-22", "text": "I played this a long time ago on the 360 but could never really finish it due to varying reasons. But seeing as all the Assassin Creed games are on sale I went ahead and got all of them for a pretty decent price of $5 a piece, which isn\u2019t bad for such a big series. Replaying through the game the story isn\u2019t half bad, and am looking forward to reviewing the other Assassins Creed games in time.\nOne big negative thing is the way climbing works.  It isn\u2019t horrible, but there are times where you would want to climb up a building fast rather than jump off a building killing yourself in the process.  Other than that, this was a big hit in the series and is a great story, providing you are more of a story driven person. 8/10", "hours": 16.4, "user_id": "76561198008241330", "username": "Petroph", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-22", "text": "In this game, you play as a Syrian man named Altair Ibn-La-Ahad, and he is part of an order of Assassins (hence the name Assassin's Creed). You start the game in real time, as a man named Desmond who has been taken by a company known as Abstergo Industries, a company where they are secretly part of the order of the Knight's Templars. The Templars are enemies to Assassins, and since Desmond is an ancestor of the previously meantioned assassin Altair, the head executive and his assistant Lucy put Desmond into a machine called the Animus. The Animus lets a person delve into his ancestor's memories, and since Altair is an ancestor to Desmond, the executive (i forgot his name, but lets just call him Bill) puts you into the Animus so he can monitor Altair's memories and find a secret that the Templars need that only Altair know. Once you are in the Animus, you finally play as Altair. You start in a mine looking for a Templar named Roberto, and once you find him, you see he is planning to steal the holy artifact known as the Ark of Covenant. You fail to kill him, and your other Assassins are left to kill him (one of them fails by the way). You go back to your master, Al Mualim, and he finds out about the attack. Suddenly Roberto and his fellow Templars are attacking, and you send a diversion to help. After you send the diversion, they flee, and Al Mualim punishes you because you did not remember the three strict rules to being an Assassin in the earlier mission. He stabs you, and you pass out. You are still alive and you must kill 9 other Templars to redeem yourself and be one of the master Assassins again.\nThe game is overall very good, but there are a few things I did not like. First of all, I know it is set in the First Crusades Period (somewhere around 1000 A.D it started) but Altair cannot hold any type of currency. Your gearand weapons are gained from each of the 9 Templars you kill. Also, in the trailer, Altair is seen to have a crossbow as one of his weapons, but that crossbow is nowhere in the actual game, so that got me dissapointed. Another thing is that youdont carry any types of medicine or potions or things like that, which would be useful in fighting because Altair isnt the best fighter without ALL of his weapons. Speaking of health, you dont have an actual health meter. Your health is displayed in something called a Synchronization Bar, a bar that fills as you do good in the game. If you commit crimes, your Synchronization Bar goes down. If you lose fights, it also goes down. Basically, anything bad makes it go down. Those are basically all the problems i have with this game.\nTo wrap it up, Assassin's Creed is a fun game with a really cool and exciting storyline, not alot of  situations i was mad or angry about, but it is old. The graphics are from somewhere around 2000 (i dont know when the games came out by years). So if you dont mind about graphics and want to have a fun action-adventure game with enticing storyline, Assassin's Creed is the game for you.\nMy Rating: 9/10\nNote from Author: There is stealth in this game. You will have to blend in with crowds, pickpocket without being caught, and if you are caught by a guard or someone you are pickpocketing, you can go blend in by sitting in a bench, hiding in a haystack, blending in with a group of scholars (they look similar to you in clothing), or just running away until they give up. There is a fourth way to blend in, but I forgot it. Another thing in this game is climbing and parkour. You will have to do alot of that, so be prepared.", "hours": 18.8, "username": "big chungo", "products": 35, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-22", "text": "After only having played a little of this game, I can honestly say it is some of the most fun I have had in a game in a while. If you liek collecting things and completing tasks while parkour-ing  around the crusade era middle east, you'll love this.", "hours": 23.3, "user_id": "76561198058816682", "username": "Face-Melting Build Tool", "products": 164, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-22", "text": "Not a bad start for a game. It's very repetitive though.", "hours": 17.9, "user_id": "76561198001826588", "username": "Soloder", "products": 483, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-22", "text": "A proof of concept for the games that followed and a bit bare bones for it.\nUnless you really really want to see the story of Altair skip it and start with the vastly better Assasin's Creed 2.", "hours": 4.1, "user_id": "76561197984389163", "username": "RuMp3l4$k1N", "products": 108, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-22", "text": "A good game to play that gave birth to a series of great games.\nIt's a good starting point if you want to get in the series, but if you want a game to fall in love with, skip this one. As much as I love this game, it is indeed repetitive and slow.\nFor those who want to experience Assassin's Creed completely. If you couldn't care less about story or completion, start with AC2", "hours": 35.8, "username": "FSantoX", "products": 536, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-21", "text": "While AC I is not the best of the series, it was revolutionary when released and heralded in a wave of open world climbers.", "hours": 3.6, "username": "Joellen Agael", "products": 411, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-21", "text": "Well, I've been warned that this is the most dull entry in the saga.\nThere's repetition in the \"quests\" you'll have to undertake - but most of them are optional and may be avoided. (You may not want to avoid them in the beginning, because you'll benefit from them.)\nBut the world! It's a fantastic place and the cities are a sight to behold.\nAlso, even I, clumsy as I am, had a blast jumping, climbing and stalking through these scenes - this games makes you feel much more competent than you are, which adds a lot to the fun.\nThe story has an interesting spin (you'll see right at the beginning).\nAll in all very recommended. I'm looking forward to the other entries in this series.\nHere are some play tips (very mild spoilers):\nDon't try to collect all flags. This is seriously madness and not needed, unless you are unhealthily obsessed :-)\nYou can skip \"save the citizens\" sidequests BUT every 15 finished sidequests (informer quests, view points scaled, citizens saved) your hit point increase by one and you may even gain extra abilities, which helps a lot. You max out at 20 (two bars), so plan accordingly.\nI'd always scale all view points. These discover side quests and reveal the map, which is helpful when fleeing or planing to strike.\nYou don't need to do all informer quests (3 out of 6). The info gained is not that helpful either. But - see above.", "hours": 23.2, "username": "ELSupremo", "products": 653, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-21", "text": "love tis game not played in ages but still one of the best game out ther", "hours": 4.7, "username": "mac2040", "products": 366, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 179, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-21", "text": "Great game! It might seem a bit stereotypical but has an awesome story and great gameplay elements.", "hours": 13.6, "user_id": "76561198095387806", "username": "kanga roo", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-20", "text": "its alright i guess", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Yendor", "products": 114, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-20", "text": "I am pretty late coming into this game but I can honestly say it does not feel as dated as it is. The graphics are still okay and the combat felt really awesome. I put about 17 hours into the game which isnt a ton but I felt satisfied when it was all over. There are two story lines going on at once, a kind of crusade era timeline which I felt very immersed in, as well as a modern story line which was very interesting with a nice twist at the end of both. The gameplay during the modern story however leaves a lot to be desiered and can get dull at times, but luckily you spend maybe an hour or two at most in that arc. Overall worth the current price.", "hours": 17.1, "username": "H07F337", "products": 459, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-19", "text": "I was really excited to play this game to start the series. However, it crashes on me every 15-60 minutes. Spent hours on the forums and Google, tried all kinds of solutions, nothing has worked. Core i7, GTX  770, 12g ram, so I'm fairly confident my system can handle it.", "hours": 6.2, "username": "ihatebrooms", "products": 913, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-19", "text": "This game is better than most people give it credit for, and while it does have many shortcomings (i.e. repetitiveness, angsty opening) it also excels in many areas like the location, story, and aesthetics. While it's not a 10/10, I give it a solid 8/10.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "JCPennies", "products": 501, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-19", "text": "It's a pretty good game and it introduces some neat mechanics, but it's very unpolished. Considering that the game ends with a \u201cto be continued\u201d, you should play it if you're interested in the franchise as a whole, but I'm not sure how strongly I'd recommend it by itself. It's a great launching point for a franchise and does some cool new things but it does have its flaws.\nFull review here:", "hours": 10.1, "user_id": "76561197987047936", "username": "The Squid", "products": 345, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-19", "text": "Overall pretty good.\nThe story is a bit confusing with the future part of the game (BTW there is a future part of the game)\nbecause in the end it leaves the player with a cliffhanger (for Assasins creed 2)\nThe Graphics looks good and has a nice feel to it.\nHowever the gameplay is a bit clunky and the wallrunning and the abillity to escape the guards is a bit buggy.\nthe ambiance/sound/soundtrack/what ever it is called is okay, not that much really rememerable.\nHowever even though the sound is okay, the voice acting is good.\nIt is worth it", "hours": 12.1, "username": "Alexander452", "products": 727, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-19", "text": "It's really not a terrible game, but compared to where the franchise is now, it's hard to recommend buying it unless you want to go back and see where it all started. You could honestly just start with Assassin's Creed 2 (or do what I did and start with Black Flag) and go from there.", "hours": 19.6, "username": "speham", "products": 239, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-18", "text": "Gameplay 8/10\nGraphics 7/10\nControls 8/10\nStoryline 7/10\nBug-Free 9/10\nReplayability 10/10\nLevel of Challenge 10/10\nExtra note: No subtitles, bad move for game developers.", "hours": 18.4, "username": "Gettys63", "products": 252, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-15", "text": "If you would like to know what the fuss is about this franchise you came to the right place - sure, the first episode is at least 6 years old but it still looks good and plays smoothly. Sure, it is not as \"refined\" as the rest - it has its shortcomings but many you can only realise once you played the sequels. It has its repetitive side missions, yes, the combat is a bit more difficult than in current gen games (even controlling the protagonist requires you to learn several \"stances\"), yet, this was what started it all and to understand the rather complex and detailed story of the franchise you have to start with Altair's journey.\nIf you do not like the first ride you can leave the rest. But if you grow to like the Assassins you are in for a very long journey, my friend!", "hours": 1.0, "username": "CorvusCorax", "products": 687, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 180, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-14", "text": "A great game based on history and information theory. 100/100", "hours": 203.7, "username": "simurgh559", "products": 234, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-11", "text": "I really like the game. It has an amazing story and the universe itself is very interesting. It's really worth playing through the game, and a good one if you are planning to start the series.\nHowever, one of the problems of this game are the controls. If you are thinking of playing this game, you should buy an X Box controller for your PC, as playing with the keyboard is a lot harder. Also, if you really want to play this game and complete it 100%, make sure that you don't collect all the flags until near the end of the game, as it gets really annoying.", "hours": 74.8, "user_id": "76561198058447871", "username": "meme12345bunny", "products": 236, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-11", "text": "Very nice, only minor flaws found - some camera positioning can be annoying and sometimes fight can be tricky. Gameplay doesn't really change throughout the game, so it may (and only \"may\" - not \"will be\") become boring after prolonged game session. And the ending of course - not a chance for me to understand it....\nAbove that - nice graphics, even for today, good interaction with your sorroundings, very good and interesting plot - though at the end you actually can guess the ending, but still - very good plot.\nDefinetly worth playing", "hours": 29.9, "user_id": "76561197963321051", "username": "Troll", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-10", "text": "So here's what is odd.  If this review was written after my first play through when I played the game back on a PS3 some many years ago, I would only half-halfheartedly recommend this game.  However, after a full play through and many years to consider what had been bothering me before about the game, I finally had the proper mindset for this game.\nYou see, in this game, a game about stealthy killing (or in my case, not so stealthy killing) all the mechanics feed into that activity.  For example, it annoyed me in the original play through that I couldn't just pickpocket money to give to beggars to make them go away, or to buy knives from merchants.  Now I realize in my second play through that these things are mechanics meant to make being sneaky that much harder; the drunks, mentally impaired, beggars, etc are all there to make it harder for you to kill and silently blend into the crowd.  It bothered me that the game seemed more interested in making me run than stand and fight; with this newest play through, I see that they are trying to teach that discretion is the better part of valor, sometimes.  In other words, running from a fight is not a bad thing.  Not that that kept me from killing over 20 guards in a row, but it takes a bit of finesse, and full command of all your abilities.  This isn't God of War or Darksiders or some spectacle fighter, you aren't meant to hurtle towards foes (though near the endgame you certainly can).\nThe game feeds that need for moving fast, for speed and alacrity that is fed in other games by battle, but here it's fed by efficiency.  Be it moving over rooftops, through streets, killing guards, hiding, climbing, assassinating, escorting, whatever you do, the game expects you to be as efficient as possible, to make choices and change those choices as the situation demands.\nIn other words, even 6 years after its release, this game still is very good at forcing you to know all your tools.  You can't just know one attack, one move, and expect the game to work fine.  You could still get through, but the game would be much less fun.  No, this game demands that you know it well to play it well.  In that, it demands knowledge, and the intelligence of when to use your knowledge.  Much in the same way Altair must learn, you to must learn.\nAnd to me, that is a possible mark of a good game.  Highly recommended, especially with those for the patience to learn.", "hours": 29.0, "username": "Kalnaur", "products": 608, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-09", "text": "Fun Game, a bit repetitive and Simple but I like it.\nThe Missions don't give you Money, like in the sequels, but the people thank you, and give you hints about your next big target, I don't know why, but I find that more rewarding than money.\nIt has an interesting story, not the best one but, an interesting one. :)\nThe controls are a bit weird if you've played the sequels before, but for beginners it shouldn't be a problem (except if you're not playing with controller)\nBut it also has its downsides, you can't fast-travel, can't explore the open world after the end of the story and are bound to 1 arsenal of weapons the whole game.\nI'd recommend this game definetly for all Assassin's Creed Fans and those, who want to become one.\nBut if you're just looking for a Game, that you wan't to play for a long time, you should better take a look at the sequels. :)", "hours": 65.4, "user_id": "76561198038643305", "username": "LORDPRETTYFOKKO", "products": 97, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-09", "text": "epic", "hours": 4.0, "username": "Legion", "products": 99, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-07", "text": "Great gameplay mechanics and story. Pretty much everything is repetitive though. Definitely still worth it.", "hours": 19.4, "username": "Villermen", "products": 386, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-04", "text": "Want a game that has cool sword fighting and amazing stealth then look no further. Assassin's Creed 1 was and still is an amazing game to play. Basically the entire game is done in your mind by unlocking memories from your DNA.  Now after a certain point the game is the same where all it is is making sure you hit the button at the right time to counter and such. But still a must play game.", "hours": 1.0, "username": "Zai", "products": 1183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-04", "text": "Great story, gameplay more repetitive than an MMORPG's.", "hours": 22.4, "username": "Jerzukekka{/id/Jermurzu}", "products": 138, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-02", "text": "When I first played this on Xbox, I was astounded at how unique and interesting this game was. Assassin's Creed is a good game, but obviously if you've played it within the last few years it definitetly seems lacking in some aspects. Without going into detail, if you like the sequel and haven't played this... Give it a go.", "hours": 15.3, "user_id": "76561198090493870", "username": "simokingo", "products": 67, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 181, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-06-01", "text": "Assassin's Creed is an action-adventure stealth game with open world environment from Ubisoft.\nThe first of the series, this game tells the story of Desmond Miles, an assassin descendant who tried to escape his life as an assassin and try to live like normal people. Instead he got kidnapped by the Abstergo Industries. There, his real adventure begins. Desmond is forced to interface with the Animus, a device that is capable to replay genetic memories of the user's ancestors. The Abstergo seeks to uncover information about Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad, a legendary assassin from the Third Crusade.\nThe gameplay of Assassin's Creed is quite interesting but also very repetitive and linear. It's repetitive because before you assassination missions begin, you need to conduct some side mission to get information for your main mission. The side mission include pickpocketing, eavesdropping, interogation and completing various task of your fellow assassin's which include, killing guards, race or flag capturing. You will do those side missions everytime you're going to assassinate someone. The good part is, you are free to choose which side mission you want to complete, only 3 from 6 side missions needed for the main missions to unlock. The freedom of the game is also quite big. You can explore the whole city of Damascus, Acre and Jerusalem. Kill guards from behind, help civilian from rogue soldiers, find and kill templar soldiers or climb a tower and perform a leap of faith. You can travel from a city to another city with horses. Despite all these freedom, the game is till linear.\nThe graphics are beautiful and amazingly detailed. The textures are just, amazing. The animation are also very great. The physics effect are also good, you can watch dead guard roll over the rooftops and eventually fall to the ground. The lightning is perfect too. The environment combined with the AI make the game feels more alive with the civilians walking around, the guards patrolling about and some beggars will try to annoy you.\nAssassin's Creed is a good start if you want to dive into the world of Assassin's Creed series as this game contains the foundation of the whole story. Even with linear story, you still have the freedom to do many things in this game. I recommend this.\nRating 8/10", "hours": 18.6, "username": "Ank", "products": 2599, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-06-01", "text": "Assassin's Creed has a great plot coupled with an excellent and unexpected ending. The graphics are great compared to most of the PC games in that point of time. But the main issue of this game is the gameplay - it's repetitive. After assassinating the first leader, everything that follows will be nearly the same. The guards may be stronger, and it may take longer to assassinate your target but nothing else vary. This game is worth playing for the plot but if you just want to play the game for gameplay, I wouldn't recommend playing it after assassinating the first leader. You can just look up YouTube to catch up on the plot.", "hours": 18.2, "username": "zamzam", "products": 369, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-30", "text": "This made me want to play Stronghold Crusader\n10/10", "hours": 16.1, "username": "suce ma marde", "products": 486, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-30", "text": "Imo, Altair is the best assassin in the series ...you have to play this if you hadn't already :D", "hours": 45.2, "user_id": "76561198013073925", "username": "ChibiNico", "products": 381, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-29", "text": "Skip this one and head on to the next installment of the series. The gameplay is repetive, the story was obtuse, and the flow was hindered by very long, unskippable cutscenes. Only my opinion, though, of course.", "hours": 1.2, "username": "H Jack Silver", "products": 237, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-28", "text": "Ezio takes on his most deadly adventure in this up coming title! wristblade/10", "hours": 30.4, "username": "Wun", "products": 260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-26", "text": "70/100", "hours": 1.8, "username": "wonderfulll", "products": 209, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-25", "text": "PRETTY COOL GUY", "hours": 8.9, "username": "Rattems", "products": 438, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-23", "text": "9/10. Great, except for all of thos goddamn flags. Every true gamer must collect and find all flags.", "hours": 7.7, "username": "MoDZas", "products": 1141, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-22", "text": "Assassin's Creed is possibly one of the greatest games released in 2007. It's a sandbox nature game with remarkable visuals, sound effects and story, which is based on historical events and people. There are two overlaping stories in this game: Desmond Miles and Alta\u00efr Ibn-La'Ahad, through machine called Animus. Within the Animus, Alta\u00efr's memories reveal that he was attempting to stop Robert de Sabl\u00e9 from taking an artifact from a Solomons temple, but broke all three of the assassin brotherhood's tenets in the process. The brotherhood leader, Al Mualim, demotes Alta\u00efr to the rank of novice, and assigns him the task of assassinating nine people, all of whom are Templars, to regain his former status. As Alta\u00efr assassinate them one by one he realises something is wrong about this assignment and that these people somehow are connected. Overall pretty good story,\nThe gameplay consist out a series of assassinations ordered by Al Mualim. To achieve this goal, you must travel from the Brotherhood's headquarters in Masyaf, across the terrain of the Holy Land known as the Kingdom to one of three cities Jerusalem, Acre, or Damascus to find the Brotherhood agent in that city. There, the agent, in addition to providing a safe house, gives the player minimal knowledge about the target, and requires them to perform additional \"recon\" missions before attempting the assassination. After completing each set of assassinations, the player is returned to the Brotherhood and rewarded with a better weapon and then given another set of targets, with the player free to select the order of certain targets.\nOverall it\u2018s pretty good game, worth your attention but it does have downsides. The bad: It\u2018s repetitive and does not provide much graphic options for high end pc, combat is clunky and sometimes feels awkward. The Good: Fun parkour mechanics, great story, huge sandbox world that feels alive, great soundtrack, many little details. 7/10", "hours": 14.3, "username": "Zardu Hasslefrau", "products": 99, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 182, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-22", "text": "The game suffers on lack of options like resolution or fullscreen mode. The game must be forced to go fullscreen and sometimes the Steam overlay doesn't work while playing this game. Also quitting is seriously too long. But ignoring that it's a pretty nice game. Short enough to not get bored, also completing every single DNA segment is also fun.\nAnyway I don't mind this game and I can't say if I recommend it to you or not. Give it a try if you want.", "hours": 14.2, "username": "TSx* Naxer", "products": 272, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 183, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-22", "text": "I want my money back. I don't have the best computer but this game runs like crap, the differences between when people are talking and when I hear them are appalling. The game is slow to react and VERY glitchy.", "hours": 88.1, "user_id": "76561198106306612", "username": "Rubber Duck", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 183, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-21", "text": "I have issues when it comes to games, I feel like I need to play through entire series to get the storyline even if people say the original ones suck.\nEveryone told me that the original assassin's creed was one of those games, just to avoid it and move onto 2 but I couldn't do it.. I had to play it.\nIt's a really pretty game, even by current 2014 standards.. but aside from that there's not much else in the way of redeeming features. You'll be doing a couple of things in this game, running around exploring, fighting and doing side quests.\nAll the side quests are the same, there's a million 'save a citizen' quests that just involve fighting some guards and then getting one of three canned replies from the person you rescued.. there's no variation in conversation.. by the end of the game you'll have heard a million other people say the same lines whenever you start to climb anything or knock anything over.\nClimbing / freerunning is the other big thing, but it feels a bit gimmicky in the game, there's very little reason to use it other than the game forcing you to use it to explore areas by getting to vantage points.By the end of the game I was using it for that purpose and just to get places quite far away quickly, everything else was easier to just stay on the ground in my opinion.\nCombat itself isn't fluid and locks away most of your combat moves until you progress the game, which makes combat start out clumsy and boring and ends up the same way as every combat move you get is defensive in nature, the entire combat system boils down to defending and counterattacking.. there's never any storming in and killing everyone like a badass.. there's storming and and defending yourself until everyone dies which just does not have the same feeling at all.\nEven the ending just really truly sucks, I don't want to put up any spoilers but it's one of the most dissapointing experiences I've had finishing a game.\nThe entire game is repititous and feels extremely grindy, by the end I was putting it on for an hour and then turning it off because it just felt like work.. unless you have the same issue as me and need to see the game yourself for the storyline before moving onto the next, then honestly skip this game. It's not awful, but it's absolutely not fun.", "hours": 23.3, "username": "neversleeps", "products": 2685, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 183, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-19", "text": "And so that's how the awesome Assassin's Creed franchise begins!\nHaving played this game on its release time frame back in 2008 on the PS3, I now felt compelled to replay the game on PC and I have to say, the game do look much better on PC! As for the controls, I managed to play with the Xbox 360 gamepad so they weren't as clunky as mentioned with Keyboard+Mouse. Although, since this game is the first of this annual release franchise, there was many aspects that was clunky and boring. I'll get to that down below!\nThe game itself is linear and repetetive, but the amazing art style(which makes the game feel kinda \"dusty\"), freerunning mechanic and combat made the game a revolutionary success!\nPROS:\n+Intriguing story that keeps you guessing until the very end (both the animus and real reality),\n+Interesting visuals and especially the artstyle (Impressive graphics even to this day).\n+Amazing soundtrack (Jesper Kyd really truly rocks! It's great that he's back with AC2, AC: Brotherhood and AC: Revalations. Sadly, Ubisoft discarded this great composer for AC3 and AC4).\n+Freerunning gameplay adds some exploration to the game.\n+Escaping \"your assassination\" pumps your adrenaline! Sad this feature was removed on the other AC games as you actually feel like an assassin there.\nCONS:\n-Experienced a few game crashes and freezes so maybe it can be attributed to Windows 8.1 although, I haven't left any game progress!\n-Audio stuttering.\n-No subtitles (closed captions).\n-Repetitive submissions, tasks.\n-Can't swim!\n-Eagle Eye vision mode cannot be use while moving.\n-Annoying NPC that hinder your progress during freerunning (namely the beggars, drunks, etc).\n-HUGE amount of collectibles that serves no real purpose besides collecting (Flags).\n-Last missions requires you to SOLO fight multiple enemies at once and that repeats a few times. If you haven't mastered the controls by then, you'll be restarting quite often!\nRECOMMENDATION:\nYes, I really recommend this game if by some chance, you haven't played THE GAME that spawned a big successful franchise. You may become bored though once you finished the game so for the replayability factor, it can be either low or high, if you really liked it. In my case, since I haven't played it since 2008, it was worth a revisit as I was due to catch up my Assassin's Creed craving.\nRATING:\n8.0 / 10\nNothing is true, everything is permitted.", "hours": 18.0, "username": "LIKEUCARE", "products": 1534, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 183, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-14", "text": "Assassin's Creed is something of a classic, the beginning of one of the biggest series of all time. While the original AC had was a very fun game, it definitely had some flaws. It was a transitional game, trying to move the parkour of Prince of Persia into a world of stealth like Tenchu or Splinter Cell, and was definitely still growing through its awkward phase. The game feels very slow at times and pickpocketing missions are tedious to say the least. Some missions feel forced or don't make sense, and some of the stealth/alert mechanics really didn't work.  The combat is shockingly easy; counter kills all around!\nIt's definitely worth playing for its gripping story and the combination of stealth and parkour action. It's a masterpiece in spite of its shortcomings. While the sequels have been getting progressively better, this is where it all started and is definitely worth a play through for fans of the series.", "hours": 19.1, "username": "StoutYeoman", "products": 347, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 183, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-13", "text": "Short and a bit repetitive, but plenty of fun. I still think the character of Altair and the setting he lives in are more interesting than the characters and places in later iterations of the series.", "hours": 14.7, "username": "Chrome", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 183, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-05-12", "text": "Just NO!!!!!", "hours": 10.4, "username": "Nick \u30c4", "products": 156, "early_access": false}
