{"product_id": "15100", "page": 187, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-22", "text": "Amazing Amazing game highly recommend!!!", "hours": 29.1, "username": "Verolain", "products": 967, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 187, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-21", "text": "not a bad game", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561197996723737", "username": "SlowbearDruid", "products": 504, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 187, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-21", "text": "Not as good as the sequls of the franchises,however; not the worst game I've ever palyed and is a game I would recommend those starting out the Assassin's Creed franchise. This game also explains some questions about the series. I give this game a score of 8/10", "hours": 23.2, "username": "Dire_Dragon", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 187, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-20", "text": "This game spawned the series that we know and love.\nStarted a generation of gamers who have a penchant for white hoodies.\nI have this on my console and when i saw it on sale, i grabbed it as fast as i could.\nThe story here was where it all began for the AC series.\nMan, i could keep typing about it but i'd rather play it. After i take a nap. Hell yeah Altair!\nThere are of course issues like the CTD's every now and then (Not sure what causes that)\nIt didn't register my game time correctly (Played it for 3 hours and it only clocked 50 mins)\nBut that is more of a porting issue than anything.\nPlay it. If you don't want to or do not like the games, you are a Templar.\nlol.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "Leonair", "products": 591, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-17", "text": "Picked up Assassin's Creed: Director's Cut during a Steam sale as I never played any game of the franchise before. I had high expectations due to the popularity of the franchise. At the beginning you get blown away by the detailed graphics and the openness of the world. You started digging into the combat mechanics, enjoy your stealthy kills and exploring every hidden city corner. But after a few missions, the repetitiveness of it all becomes quite apparent: always the same mini missions, always the same chain of events, the open world where you can do... nothing. Yet another few missions later and you are wondering why you are wasting your time on this... Boredom changes into irritation once you find out that you really don't need to be stealthy nor do you need to explore everything or finish every mini mission. And then I didn't even mention the excruciating game menu, the crappy ending, the poorly scripted conversations (no, there is no escape button). Quickly I didn't feel any sympathy for the main character and the unfolding story. What a missed opportunity this game is... Even at sale, I would not recommend this game.\nScore: 4/10\nPro:\n+ visuals\n+ open world\n+ climbing towers and enjoying great views\nContra:\n- empty world\n- repetitive missions\n- clumsy controls on pc\n- painful game menu system\n- irritating camera system", "hours": 19.9, "username": "S_C_S_I", "products": 1068, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-14", "text": "1. Good Story line\n2. Good Graphics\n3. Beautiful Soundtracks\n4. Good Game Play\n5. Open World\n9/10", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198076271880", "username": "Paul \u2665", "products": 940, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-13", "text": "First assassins creed game , which you are the templar hunter Altair , from Syria Damascus .\nthe game has some bugs and glitches not that i can say that much , cuz its the first version , although the graphics are really good, combat is awsome as always . the storyline is ok though , but you have to fight your way into templar territory < from the crusades era>\nRecommend ? Ofcourse", "hours": 3.5, "user_id": "76561198073456365", "username": "Xx Jensen xX", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-12", "text": "The best start of a game series I have ever played. Already saving up for the third one!", "hours": 51.3, "user_id": "76561198109897216", "username": "6thBrick", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-09", "text": "I love this game, its a little slow at times but it has a great story with a so so ending. Every AC fan should have this in the library!", "hours": 16.4, "user_id": "76561198126811475", "username": "vice419", "products": 26, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-09", "text": "It all began here.", "hours": 4.4, "username": "Great Mazinger", "products": 61, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-08", "text": "I have waited a very long time to get Assassin's Creed. When I saw it was on sale, of course I couldn't pass up the chance to buy it. I had never played an Assassin's Creed game before (I only watched videos) and it was worth the cost. Great graphics, interesting storyline; it has everything I love in a game. The one problem I see is the difficult time I have with the controls. They are slightly confusing and it is very hard to turn your character when sprinting. When I am climbing up a wall to get away from soldiers and they manage to make me fall down, I try to run away, only to constantly try running up the wall again since it takes so long for the game to understand that I want to turn away. I am usually almost dead by then so a ragequit follows. With the only complaint I have about the game, Assassin's Creed is a fun and interesting play. I definitely recommend it for those who are unsure.", "hours": 14.6, "username": "Katsudon", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-07", "text": "A revolution in 3rd person gaming. Truly extraordinary for its' time. Obviously high quality as it led to a series of sequels that has since turned into one of the most successful franchises in gaming history.\nThat aside there are several components of AC1 that have not aged well. The missions are woefully repetative. Go to a new city, find all the viewpoints, \"gather information\" by doing the exacty same side quests over and over again, etc etc. After the first 4 hours the latter 16 hours are pretty much the same thing on repeat until you get to the end. And to describe the ending, all that can be said is \"Curse your sudden but inevitable betrayal!\".\nThen you wake up as Desmond feeling really satisfied and the game ends in the middle of more stuff happening that you don't get to explore.\nOverall 8/10 for its time. Today? 6.5 out of 10. TL:DR Just start the series off with AC 2", "hours": 22.5, "username": "Zxoran", "products": 448, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-07", "text": "Excelent game,but repetitive after a while", "hours": 55.8, "username": "one3dmt", "products": 207, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 188, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-07", "text": "Comparing this game to the other Assassin's Creed games would not be fair but I am still gonna do it.\nThe game starts good but the first thing I notice is that the voice acting seems a bit off.After awhile I got used to it but it was a bit annoying at first.The dialogue in the game is clever and interesting.I was more entertained by the dialogue than the actual gameplay.I was getting bored hacking and slashing through dozens of enemies and I was motivated to do so only because I wanted to hear the next part of the storyline.\nThe gameplay itself is decent even compared to the other AC's(even if the game is kinda old) but it gets boring fast.Each time you get a new target you do the same thing over and over again(9 times to be exact).My point is that they could have put more effort into diversification instead of doing the same exact thing for every new assassination.The sidequests are not fun and you will probably end up ignoring them after 2-3 hours of in-game play.\nAnother thing that annoyed me was the lack of one-liners for the citiziens and guards.After some time you will start hearing the same exact thing from the citiziens and guards in all of the cities.I heard the following line : ''When he falls,I'm not gonna help him'' like 200 times and it really got on my nerves.\nIn the end I would like to say that the game has a good storyline and some dialogue that is definitely worth listening to.", "hours": 1.7, "user_id": "76561198034782339", "username": "OrNaM3nT", "products": 2194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-06", "text": "Being the first of this awesome series, it's totally worth playing.\nThe game itself has some things that displeases me, such as the fact it is really repetitious and has some unnecessary cutscenes (after half of the game, checking Eagle Points and listening to the rescued citizens become very annoying).\nBut besides these \"bad things\" (IMO), the plot, the scenario and everything related to the story itself are more than satisfactory. Not only Ezio's story, but also Mr. Miles', since there are some extra actions that can be done outside the Animus.\nThe fights, limited at the beggining of the game, become more challenging near its end, with some \"boss\" fights that are kinda enjoyable.\nGood game, great saga, highly recommended.", "hours": 20.5, "username": "Lukgil", "products": 122, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-05", "text": "SO this game obviously created quite a legacy and there's no denying that. It offers a unique perspective on the period of time surrounding the crusades while providing some enjoyable gameplay elements. Unfortunately, this game has many flaws (all of which have been corrected in later games in the series. The initial segments of the game are fun as you explore the world and acclamate to the gameplay mechanics. However, shortly after, you realize you have to do the same thing again. and again. and again. This game gets boring fast, and while the high-level assassinations can be unique, the long periods in between leavemuch to be desired. Additionally, the lack of steam acheivments renders the collecting of flags and the murder of templars pointless, and doing so unlocks no in-game features. The games that would follw this one are spectacular, but I would be lying if I said I really enjoyed this entry in the series. 3/10", "hours": 27.8, "username": "Bro Onionrings", "products": 775, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-03", "text": "pretty good game, it's got good combat(at least when you get later on in the game and actually get more ways to kill, good stealth- the stealth really isn't a big precept so fighting is really the main way to get assassinations done-props if you did get any of the main assassinations on stealth kills though, and finally it has a great story-there are some hidden campaign facets and such and though this game starts slow i guarentee you willbe addicted by about the 5th assassination.", "hours": 86.5, "user_id": "76561198091413941", "username": "Causus", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-03", "text": "Deleted my all saved games. Twice. Thanks, Ubisoft.", "hours": 8.9, "username": "Dzikon", "products": 222, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-03", "text": "boring as queuing at the post office.", "hours": 2.2, "username": "[BUIO] Fobetore", "products": 470, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-02", "text": "The original Assassin's Creed has set new boundaries for the adventure genre. The parkour and the overall gameplay are simply impressive for a 2008 game.\nI've only played this game in 2014 because I wanted to get into the AC series and figured AC1 was the first step I should take. Although it is EXTREMELY repetitive, it's a game I'm willing to finish 100% if I ever have the time. If not, I'll just complete the Story.\nIt's worth adding that, although I have not reached the game's ending, I've already found a plethora of collectibles. Be it small flags or side missions, this game has a lot of that kind of extras.\nAll in all, AC1, despite lacking in variety, has re-defined the adventure/action genre in a way that is yet to be seen in any other game outside of the AC series. Or so I think.", "hours": 15.7, "username": "Denolth", "products": 220, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-02", "text": "I had this game first time on my PSP and still enjoy it. Tha campaign is good and long but gets slightly repetetive. Even the hiding from guards and jumping on people with a knife in your knife never gets old =D\nJumping from insane hights into hay stacks, feeling your spine break every single time and leaping from roof to roof is just too thrilling to put tha game down for a while", "hours": 5.5, "user_id": "76561197988603510", "username": "Ungrim Ironfist", "products": 515, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-02", "text": "Repetitive Repetitive Repetitive. The first few hours are quite fun. Once you hit the middle part of the game you realize you are playing a series of mini games before you reach a boss. If you dont have all the time in the world skip this game.", "hours": 24.4, "user_id": "76561197999778785", "username": "Adrian Frenetic", "products": 49, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-02", "text": "Excellent game to the original series; a bit laggy on older pcs but well worth the time.", "hours": 0.9, "username": "Glyph", "products": 17, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 189, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-02", "text": "The Assassins Creed series has always been spectacular and this game shows it, this game has great story telling and exiting gameplay. One of the greatest ways why this game is so enjoyable is the brilliant voice acting you feel the anger and emotion that the characters feel.\nRating: 9/10", "hours": 10.4, "username": "theDuskNinja", "products": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "nothing is forbidden.\nexcept buying this game lol OWNED.", "hours": 17.1, "username": "Captain ACAB", "products": 162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "Unless you like doing the same thing over and over again, then this game is not for you.\nThe good:\nGraphics - Considering it is not new game, it looks pretty good even now, large cities all with distinct features.\nStory - This is the only reason, I wanted to keep playing as story is great, but I just can't force myself to do it anymore.\nMovement - Parkour is great, one of the coolest features. Jump anywhere, climb, running on the roofs is pretty fun.\nThe bad:\nControls - It may have been made for consoles, but controls are not really intuitive (default) ones\nCombat - Very simplistic, that doesn't require much thought, only pressing button at the right time.\nRepetitive gameplay - Quests are the same, everything is the same, if you've done it once, you will do the same thing another 20 times.", "hours": 6.1, "username": "DMINATOR", "products": 699, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "Just getting into this genre. The game LOOKS great. Gameplay is interesting. Controlling isn't too tough. Should have made a bigger area for the tutorial. Being sneaky wasn't ever my thing but I was to play this! Couldn't beat $5.", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561197972471665", "username": "Happy!", "products": 151, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-03-01", "text": "30 Hours to complete - Not as good as AC2, a lot of issues with controls and the lack of UPlay support is a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665.\n6/10 Dragons.", "hours": 35.2, "username": "Druss - tGtribe", "products": 1256, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "Bad points first - The missions are almost identical, turn up, do minimum of three from a mostly boring selection of mini assassination missions, collecting flags, eavesdropping, pickpocketing etc, get the go ahead to assassinate the 'boss', see your leader for an upgrade, rinse and repeat. Some of the tasks weren't worth including, eavesdropping for example is sitting on the nearest bench and pressing a button. The 'kingdon' between cities was a wasted opportunity and may as well be skipped unless you're looking for flags and templars. The assassinations themselves can rarely be carried out in the delicate stealthy way you might imagine, more often than not you end up fighting half a dozen or more to get away to a rooftop. The mental people and beggars get annoying quickly with the same sound clips over and over again so I ended up spending most of the game on the rooftops to avoid them, missing out on a lot of the city and feel at ground level. The Desmond parts could have included more backstory and the two doctors got boring quickly.\nGood - Looks great, I bought it in a sale last year and for a game so old it looks superb. The free running is well executed and something I never got bored of, nothing like seeing two or three steps ahead when running away from guards across the rooftops.\nBecause it can be had so cheaply in sales, and if you take the fastest route possible completed in a handful of hours I would recommend it as part of the AC saga.", "hours": 31.0, "username": "Tomathee", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "Rubbish story, idiotic unresponsive controls, full of bugs, stupid ending, so on and so on. How on earth did this become a big name game, pac man has more polish and substance than this broken game.", "hours": 1.6, "user_id": "76561197993589983", "username": "Madash", "products": 351, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "I didn't enjoy this game. I know enough of the story from watching lets plays before I started playing that over all the franchise is pretty good but this game is just really dull to play. Once the novelty of running around wears off the game is ultimately just a grind fest of similar challanges. If there where acheivements then maybe I would of enjoyed it more but I had no reason to pick up those last few flags or complete all the challanges. I recommend you pick up this game at some point, like I said its a good series and the story is worth a look but gameplay wise it's fairly dull and a chore.", "hours": 23.0, "user_id": "76561198018575662", "username": "Javaman", "products": 383, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "Awesome gameplay with a great story line, and lots of violence too :3", "hours": 22.6, "user_id": "76561198099291153", "username": "Dilara", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-28", "text": "Tried this one and no 2 but couldn't get any where", "hours": 8.7, "user_id": "76561198030074132", "username": "drochow0", "products": 66, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 190, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "I have no idea how a potentially great game could be made so annoying and frustrating.\nIt all started with traveling to the cities for the first time. Since you've never been there you don't have fast travel. It was really boring riding there especially when guards came by and I had to walk slowly, taking a lot of time for nothing.\nAt the cities as I got deeper into the game was when I realized how flawed and annoying this game could be.\nMost of the time Altair never jumps where I want him to, even if I point my controller at the exact position. This can be really annoying when accidentally falling down or trying to escape guards.\nAnother very annoying thing is the distracting citizens. The beggers, the drunk fist fighters, the people who just push you for no reason. I fail to understand why this content got into the game for any other reason but to annoy the player. You can't really make a stratigical move to avoid them since they are at random places and/or follow you around.\nThe gameplay becomes very repetitive once you got your first assassination, it's just climbing towers to find mini-missions, completing them and going for the big kill, which would be the only fun part of the game if all the careful planning, taking care of rooftop archers and finding a good escape route would not be ruined by a drunk guy randomly pushing me into my target or a guard.\nProbably the most annoying thing is the people of the cities speaking the same things over and over again. The high score for me was a guard harassing a guy saying \"You dare steal in my presence? That will cost you your life!\" six times over and over again.\nWithout all the annoying content the repetitive gameplay would not be so bad since the story seems great so far and the great (but currently buggy) engine of the game would compensate for the boring submissions.\ntl;dr: one of the most annoying games I've ever played and all it would take to fix it is a patch", "hours": 15.9, "username": "War Row Gape", "products": 276, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 191, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "Assassin's Creed is a decent game. The game brings a good story and interesting mechanics/concepts along with it. The game has a good story that in itself is reason enough to play. The game falls short in its variation and some elements of the gameplay.\nThe story is interesting and builds up to a semi-expected conclusion. This does not ruin the game though because there is still plenty left unexplained as to the future of where the series will take you and what your actions really mean for the world going forward. The story kept me engaged and interested throughout.\nThe actual gameplay is where this game does not shine. Yes, there are some interesting and fun mechanics. The combat system works well, although counters = godmode. [The game becomes too easy. You can easily fight a mob of 20+ guards and never lose any health].  The game falls flat in terms of its variation. The bulk of the game is made up of the same combination of elements. 1. Go to this city. 2. Gather information. 3. Assassinate. Granted the system works it gets boring quickly. There are no real side missions to speak of and the flag collection system gives you nothing and is not worth the effort.\nOverall, I still recommend playing the game because of the story. It is worth trduging through the repetitive gameplay to build on the lore of a series that gets better and better as it progresses.", "hours": 13.1, "user_id": "76561197993257184", "username": "Exanamis", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 191, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "I think the game has a lot to offer. Psuedo-open world, side quests and objectives, nice graphics for its time and decent mechanics. However, it just could not hold my interest. Most of my time played on this game was it running in the background while I alt-tabbed to do other things. I got it because I was given the latest version (Black Flag) as a bundle for something else I bought and thought I should play through the series as to understand the entirety of the story.\nAlas, I'll probably never get around to finishing this game or ever playing its successors.\nI do think a lot of people will get enjoyment out of the game, even if I didn't and as such would recommend it.", "hours": 39.9, "username": "jon", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 191, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "One of the most epic games ever. I played all the Assassin's Creed, and all started with this one. EPIC.", "hours": 19.4, "user_id": "76561197985481920", "username": "rKINGSMAN", "products": 22, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 191, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-27", "text": "I decided to come back to this game after few years, and i must say it stil looks awesome from graphic point of view and especially if you look at the story whitch is very immersive. It also have its bugs and gliches, repetitivnes of quests is kinda annoying but the main storyline is quite good if you disregard constant misions \"save the citzen\" or some other thet you do over and over again.\nBut you must not forget that this is the first game in the AC franchise and so it is a bit unpolished and its sequels ar better in one more aspects, but again not all agree on this question. I give it 8/10 and say you have to at leaste try it to judge it.", "hours": 15.9, "username": "||xHenco||", "products": 75, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 191, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-26", "text": "I played Assassin's Creed II, III, and Black Flag before playing this and to some extent, I shouldn't have. Assassin's Creed is, I think, a worthy predecessor to the series, but there are some flaws. Combat and movement feels very clumsy at first, after playing for a bit it still is, but you kinda get used to it. The story is also very repetitive. After completing the first three assassinations, you get the idea of what to do. It just gets too repetitive. The visuals, however, are amazing. It really is a feast for the eyes. For a game released in 2007 (I think), the graphics are stunning. A bit low compared to modern games, but still impressive. If you can put up with a repetitive storyline and clunky controls, you'll probably enjoy this game. Despite these cons, I can honestly say that I enjoyed this game.", "hours": 20.0, "user_id": "76561198055831467", "username": "Turd Ferguson", "products": 408, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 191, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-26", "text": "This is to this day my favourite game in the franchise. While the console versions might be very repetetive the PC version actually has a variety of ways to get the info you need to find your targets.\nThis game is still very focussed on the Assassin part of the game when the other games in the series are filled with horrible mini games to lengthen the game time.", "hours": 26.5, "username": "Fhqwhgod", "products": 1867, "early_access": false}
