{"product_id": "15100", "page": 192, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "Very good, but you must keep in mind this is the first episode of the franchise. So the gameplay is a little lesser than others. Beautiful places.", "hours": 28.2, "user_id": "76561198039204919", "username": "F Sawasaki", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 192, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-24", "text": "For all its hype (perhaps its the series in whole), the first game in the Assassin's Creed Series is boring at best.\nThe story is light, perhaps only gets interesting once you reach Robert De Sable.\nThis is repetetive gameplay with pretty visuals and reasonable audio.\nThe side missions are completely filler material and prove very little value to a story driven promise.\nOn the plus side, controls are responsive (confusing at start), camera and parkhour generally works 90% of the time.\nI guess you'd play it if you plan on playing the entire series.. what choice is there?", "hours": 6.5, "user_id": "76561198039084174", "username": "FuriousMonkey", "products": 175, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 192, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "Assassin's Creed\u2122 is the next-gen game developed by Ubisoft Montreal that redefines the action genre. While other games claim to be next-gen with impressive graphics and physics, Assassin's Creed merges technology, game design, theme and emotions into a world where you instigate chaos and become a vulnerable, yet powerful, agent of change.\nThe setting is 1191 AD. The Third Crusade is tearing the Holy Land apart. You, Altair, intend to stop the hostilities by suppressing both sides of the conflict.\nYou are an Assassin, a warrior shrouded in secrecy and feared for your ruthlessness. Your actions can throw your immediate environment into chaos, and your existence will shape events during this pivotal moment in history.", "hours": 418.3, "username": "Tuong", "products": 2374, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 192, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "10/10 took me awhile to get the puzzle at the end of the game subject 17 = desmond :)", "hours": 38.7, "username": "\ud83d\ude48[K\u00c4PY] Pimkuma \ud83d\ude48", "products": 947, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 192, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "Barely worth the $5. All you do is walk around slowly and sword fight by clicking repeatedly.", "hours": 3.9, "user_id": "76561198116965852", "username": "firematt422", "products": 89, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 192, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "I had played this game a few years back, but now decided to give it another shot. It can certainly still compete with today's games, especially from a graphics standpoint, which is, in itself, quite remarkable.\nIf you have never played this game, I would call it a merger between Splinter Cell, Batman and Hitman. You have to blend into your environment and hide at times, you have to navigate rooftops, you can be a vigilante, and you have your mission to complete and have a certain freedom on how to do so. While this game is certainly not as refined as its successors in the series, it was, much like the first Splinter Cell, the first Batman (Arkham series), and the first Hitman, a diamond in the rough, with exceptional gameplay, graphics and design. At least for their respective times. While the subsequent titles had a lot of refinement and improvement, this first Assassin's Creed still stands its ground in the sands of time. Add to that the soundtrack, and you have great entertainment.\nThe only downside - to me - is the obvious console breeding ground, and the somewhat shady save point situation, but I guess that's the way it is. I'm getting used to the whole checkpoint idea these days, albeit with a heavy heart. I do miss my quick save option.\nEither way, give this game a try, especially if you can snap it up in a deal! You won't regret it if you like the other games mentioned above. Also, it's not as repetitive as people say; while the handling is, true, the way you approach diverse challenges isn't.", "hours": 38.5, "username": "jssrfx", "products": 402, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 192, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-23", "text": "hella", "hours": 32.7, "username": "gunji", "products": 72, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-22", "text": "NO SUBTITLES! I'm\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665off.", "hours": 4.6, "user_id": "76561198084430790", "username": "[DEAF] nVicious", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-22", "text": "steaming pile of crap", "hours": 18.7, "username": "Big P [PENISLORD20XX]", "products": 486, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-22", "text": "I guess I can see how this game would have been amazing back at the time of release, but I thought it was pretty lackluster. It's cool hoppping and climbing around like a \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665in' monkey, but the gameplay is so repetitive, the environment is frustratingly similar everywhere you go, and the combat is really pretty boring for how often you get stuck in it. Fleeing was fun the first couple times, but then it just got tedious what with Altair 'tarding out and climbing up\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665I didn't want him to and causing me to have to run another marathon to find somewhere else to hide.\nAnd I can't tell you how many times I actually threw my hands up in frustration at the crazy homeless guys shoving me into guards. I swear they actually follow you waiting to strike. Thank you Assassin's Creed for causing me to develop a legit hatred for homeless crazies.", "hours": 14.4, "user_id": "76561197980947074", "username": "Spankasaurus", "products": 493, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-21", "text": "I really wanted to like this game. Perhaps I didn't play it \"right\" or something, but many parts of the game felt like a chore.  Every single mission is exactly the same. As soon as you've seen all three cities, the game is nothing but tedious \"investigation\" quests which consist of finding lame wannabe assassins and doing fetch quests for them. Also peppered throughout the cities are viewpoints, which are actually pretty fun because you have to find ways to climb tall buildings. Then there are the \"rescue citizen\" missions which are so completely out of place it's ridiculous. Sure, let's make the whole game about stealth kills and then force you to fight some guards in the middle of the marketplace in plain view of everyone. Let's also have you do it about 10 times per city. And every citizen has that same canned \"I will repay this kindness I swear it\" line afterwards. The only time this is worthwhile is when you unlock a crowd of scholars to get past some guards. The AI for the guards is absolutely atrocious as well. Just inexcusable.\nThis series got far better with the sequel and the Ezio trilogy. This game feels like a prototype for the series rather than a worthwhile game.", "hours": 24.4, "username": "WChrisMullen", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-21", "text": "Definitely worth playing for knowledge of the story. Some of the features are frustrating, like dying when falling in water, and it makes some of the swimming concepts later confusing.", "hours": 67.2, "username": "Tobiah", "products": 139, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-20", "text": "awesome!", "hours": 0.6, "username": "alive", "products": 253, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-20", "text": "Gets repetitive after a while, but the feeling of running and climbing the buildings is one of its kind.", "hours": 22.5, "user_id": "76561198047947642", "username": "michalk", "products": 595, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-18", "text": "Assassin's Creed is great game and should not be missed.  Assassin's Creed tries to do something different where the safe thing to do is make a cookie cutter type game. Assassin's Creed not only tries to be different, it does it very well.", "hours": 2.4, "username": "FadedTeleTubby", "products": 743, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-17", "text": "Better than the fourth.  And third.  Isaiah's computer would explode if he tried runnung it, though. (the joke is he has a crappy computer)", "hours": 35.4, "user_id": "76561198058283491", "username": "1952 Goldtop Gibson Les Paul", "products": 91, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 193, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-17", "text": "Impressive graphics for its time, but gamplay is repetitive, and it has unnecessary spikes in difficulty. Buy only if you want to follow the story from the beginning, otherwise start with AC2, which improves almost on every aspect of the game.", "hours": 19.9, "user_id": "76561198058311303", "username": "Nadius", "products": 180, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-17", "text": "+Challenging but not too difficult\n+Great dialogue\n+Graphics and sounds fit the game.\n+Allows you to perform each assassination however you wish\n+Historically accurate\n-Almost no replay value\n-Short\n-Pointless collectibles\n-The story makes little sense and is relatively dull.\n7/10, Good game", "hours": 6.2, "username": "BajES", "products": 171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-17", "text": "ya", "hours": 3.0, "username": "Robaire Shen", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-16", "text": "very fun", "hours": 0.5, "username": "XzXCHAOSXzX", "products": 62, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-14", "text": "This game is unplayable for the most part due to crashes (Win 7).    I've tried all the fixes, and all the usual nonsense, and I'm lucky to get 30 minutes of continuous gameplay before it crashes.    Given that it's a typical PC port, getting in and out of this game and bypassing cut scenes makes the scenario of it crashing unbearable.\nFixes/nonsense tried:\n* DX10 Vista compatibility mode:   Didn't fix crashing.\n* Normal DX9/DX10:  Didn't fix crashing.\n* acii_360_wireless driver fix:   This did fix the controller mapping, imagine it will for AC II as well.\n* All fixes tried with disabling multiple displays:   Didn't fix crashing.\nIf you really want to play this game, I'd suggest snagging it on console (if you have that luxury).    Steam should refund anyone who has experienced the level of crashing/nonsense associated with this game.", "hours": 3.9, "username": "FlushJackson", "products": 1438, "found_funny": 3, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-13", "text": "The first entry in the Assassin's Creed series, and a solid game in its own right but ultimately feeling more like a proof of concept when compared to later entries in the series.\nThe game uses the excuse of genetic memory to send your character on a romp through the historical Crusades, as your character moves his way through assassinating corrupt leaders in order to assist the goals of the character's cult. It features an open world with a small variety of optional missions, but ultimately the game - while showing solid promise - hinges on a few repetitive patterns and collection quests. It's fun, but other entries in the series are better. Expect Good, not Great.", "hours": 21.3, "username": "Jragghen", "products": 1162, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-13", "text": "The game that started it all.. Altair's story.", "hours": 4.5, "user_id": "76561197993848840", "username": "Chirper ^o^", "products": 499, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-13", "text": "The concept is great\nThe exicution is not\nExtremely simple and boring combat on top of a game that makes you repeat the same missions over, and over, and over ad infinitum.\nThis could possibly be good if you are very, very patient and like an easy ride. I however detested it.", "hours": 17.6, "user_id": "76561197973766362", "username": "SCUM", "products": 603, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-13", "text": "This game may be old but it is still awesome", "hours": 16.1, "user_id": "76561198007424814", "username": "Ranger", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "Lots of fun for the people who never played Assassin's Creed. Great for the girls. In fact if you are a girl... buy this game you'll bask in Altair's hotness. This was my first game that was not made in Japan. I'm happy to say the 29 hours of gameplay was worth it.", "hours": 29.3, "user_id": "76561198123993819", "username": "kyllvie", "products": 4, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 194, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "If you want to become a Assassin then play this game\nIf you love taking revenges then assassinate them\nIf you like a open-world game then this is the game for you\nPLUS it's Director's Cut Edition cant buy it for other platforms\nAnd last thing\nYou are Alta\u00efr, a Assassin that must kill all the nine templars (your enemies) think you up for the challenge?\nAnd since it's the 2010s you're Desmond, a guy that got himself stuck in a lab forcing to use a memory machine\ncalled the animus that helps recovering his ancestor's memories to find The Piece of Eden that the Templars (now Abstergo) is looking for\n- Are you Ready? To assassinate 9 people, find the Piece of Eden, Finding your way out of the lab and Become a true Assassin? Then Buy this game and Amuse yourself by going back to the past to The Third Crusade!", "hours": 48.1, "username": "Hoovyspenser", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "The one that started it all and in my personal opinion the 2nd best AC game out there.\nWarning: Contains major spoilers for Assassin's Creed\nAlso here's my \"BUY RANKS\"\n1: Buy this game now!\n2: Wait till it goes on sale\n3: Try the demo first or if they don't have one wait till it's half off.(All opinion wise)\n4: Wait till they make it free or 70-90% off.\n5: Don't buy\nSTORY: You are Desmond Miles a 25 year old man captured by a company known as Abstergo as they have captured you and have forced you to do something extraodinary: to relieve the memories of your ancestor in order to find an ancient treasue. You relieve the memories of Altair an assassin from the year of 1191. The story in this is great and makes you feel like there are two stories instead of one, the story of Altair's fight and stuggle against the templars and Desmond's involvment with Abstergo. Has one of the best twists I've seen in a game since it came out. 9.5/10\nGRAPHICS: The graphics in this game are of course dated since this was made in 2007. Still though they're pretty to look at and the 60fps wins me over with it's smoothness and textures but still it's dated. 7.5/10\nGAMEPLAY: Wow what can I say about gameplay, of course comparing the stuff you can do in AC compared to the others there's not much to do you only have 4 weapons, your fists,knive and mini knives,sword, and the iconic hidden blade but you do receive upgrades in the game as you progress through the main story. There are sidequests and with the PC version I was able to grab 4 more, annoying but helped in the main game. You can collect flags but to me there really was no point into them. Then there was the parkor and the view points....holy\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665their amazing. With the awesomeness of free-running and viewing the map piece by piece by the climbing on top of a tower and viewing it while an eagle is in the background just screams badass. Even though there's not much to do except do main and side missions you still have your own bit of fun. 8/10\nCONCLUSION: AC is a great game and again in my personal opinion is ranked 2nd best in my book due to it being the starting point to the series and NO FULL SYNC! Hope to make more of these soon and thanks for reading my first steam review.:)\nBUY RANK:1", "hours": 35.4, "user_id": "76561198028032411", "username": "Claylex", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "Great start of the series but just gets repetitive.", "hours": 23.6, "user_id": "76561198091765972", "username": "Rugmatt", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "This game has an amazing story to it. My friend suggested for me and I wasn't all over it at first, it has a bunch of really funny glitches as well. It's hours of fun. 8/10", "hours": 32.5, "username": "Sean", "products": 88, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "When I first played this game, I was very disappointed. First of all, I wasn't playing Ezio, which really bugged me because I knew nothing about the other assassins; second, I was VERY confused by the way they incorporated the Animus into the game, and had you switch between history and modern times. And finally, it can be pretty damn frustrating to have to walk across an entire city to simply avoid alerting guards; those cities are huge, man! But after I was about half-way through, I began to appreciate it. Altair is, in fact, a really bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665assassin, and the switch between modernity and history actually makes more sense in this game than it does in the others. Though you need to be a paitent player to enjoy this game, I think it was worth every hour I put into it.", "hours": 68.0, "username": "XentziS", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-12", "text": "This game is so terrible that I uninstalled it three times during my playthrough. Absolutely dreadful.", "hours": 15.8, "username": "alex", "products": 300, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-10", "text": ".", "hours": 0.7, "username": "Aendyr", "products": 231, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-09", "text": "This is the story about some guy who is kidnapped by someone else and forced to use the mumble to mumble mumble the memories of mumblemurf for some reason or other. The game doesn't have subtitles. An unfortunate design choice for two reasons.\nThe first reason: Many of the actors(?) haven't quite figured out how to open their mouth while talking.\nThe second reason: talking is pretty much everything that happens in this game.\nDon't believe the lie about open-world gameplay, parkour moves and total freedom. All I seemed to do in this game was to hold forwards from one dialogue-ridden cutscene to the next. Sure, I had the option of parkouring about the place, but it didn't bring forth feelings of open world movement and pulse-pounding action. Freerunning simply felt like a carrot being dangled over my nose on the other side of a window, designed solely to frustrate me while I wait through another cutscene.\nWait seems to be the keyword in this game. The intro in particular is an irritating wait. Intros are to be skipped. We see them the first time, and then we skip past them because we've already seen them. But no. The developers don't care about me wanting to play a game, they've got religious nutters to placate, leaving me to tap the escape-button with no real hope of being let into the game any time soon.\nStill, if you've got good hearing, a high tolerance for tricky control schemes, and a genuine interest in Mumblemurf's backstory, I'm sure the game is good.", "hours": 2.2, "username": "fippmeister", "products": 3530, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-09", "text": "This game might be a fairly good game in terms of gameplay and design but in terms of control/fluidy of controls and the inability to alt+tab, it makes the experience sour along with the fact the controls are very clunky and this ruins the user's experience. I do not feel like finishing this game using a keyboard+mouse. I may change my mind if I use a PS3 controller but using traditional computer's peripherals, it just doesn't work.", "hours": 8.9, "user_id": "76561198034174831", "username": "Loki Loptr", "products": 224, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-09", "text": "This game is great it's really good everyone should get this game.", "hours": 7.5, "user_id": "76561198060727700", "username": "Octocrunch", "products": 100, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 195, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-08", "text": "Best Game Ever.\nGraphics are amazing and plot keeps you gripped start to finish. Who the hell wouldnt want to be an assassin!?", "hours": 36.9, "user_id": "76561198083936928", "username": "Lady Of Wolves", "products": 64, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-08", "text": "Great game, really enjoyed it. The game has a good storyline, is kinda fluid, and feels pretty natural. A must for die-hard fans. Sometimes, however, the gameplay gets quite repetitive, and the occasional glitch appears. Nice game though, 7,5/10.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "Samma12", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-07", "text": "Slip into the role of an assassin. Learn the skills, tactics and handling of the weapons of the most feared secret society in history. Plan your attacks, strike without mercy, and you fight your escape route.\nThe newly developed from scratch graphics engine for next-generation consoles allows organic game design featuring open gameplay, intuitive controls, realistic reactions of the environment and a fluid combat mechanics.\n83/100", "hours": 2.7, "user_id": "76561198025070201", "username": "EGOiST", "products": 642, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-07", "text": "Climb, jump, kill, jump, listen, jump, run, jump, repeat.\nFun to play, I've even finished it. Still, all the levels have the same pattern, and the cutscenes that you can't skip make it even more boring.", "hours": 35.2, "user_id": "76561198050990473", "username": "maro", "products": 114, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-05", "text": "", "hours": 54.6, "user_id": "76561197975104212", "username": "Cptn. Emerald", "products": 208, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-02-05", "text": "If you love spending hours upon hours of doing nothing but the same thing over and over again, then I highly recommend this game. If you value your time more than an unemployed-by-choice middle aged man living at home with his parents, then look elsewhere for entertainment.\nThis game consists of extremely bad AI, a rather dull, very slow and predictable moving story line (I would have enjoyed a novel based on this. But a game was not needed). It's just one of those games where the concept is good, but the execution leaves much to be desired.", "hours": 19.6, "user_id": "76561198064657663", "username": "Mojocrunch", "products": 446, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-04", "text": "I've owned this game since 2008 (on Xbox 360) but never got a chance to actually play it till today! 2/4/2014\nThe story is awesome! I really didn't know what to expect beyond some story about an Assassin but man I was pretty surprised. For the first few minutes I had to remap the keybindings for my controller which were really off.. but once I got into the game I was really taken for a ride. I've only played this game for a little over 5 hours but one of the best things I like about this game is the exploration and freerunning. Climbing towers and exploring ancient cities. There are many sidequests and the element of danger was definitely there. Crowds of people walking all over the place. Rub shoulders with the wrong guy and you're in for a fight buddy!\nThe combat feels pretty good at this stage of only playing 5 hours into the game. After completing a few missions I unlocked some abilities like Counter Attack that made combat more in my favor.. or that's what I thought until I ran into a Knight that totally kicked my rear end. But you know whats cool? I grabbed that Knight's attention, climbed a tower, he followed up after me planning on destroying my face, but the moment he stepped off that ladder... I threw him off that tower to his death! Splat my good Sir! Sweet revenge after dying a few times to his brutal power.\nAgain I've only played a few hours into the game earlier today, but I've had a blast so far. It's definitely a great Action/Adventure type of game, I'll be talking about this older game to some of my friends next week for sure! Haha", "hours": 7.3, "username": "Dr Leo Marvin", "products": 2237, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-04", "text": "Game is divided in cities, each city has 3 zones, each zone has the same missions as the zone before. So yes, too repetitive. I mean, 20 hours of always doing the same thing; climb the towers to unlock missions (boring), save peasants by killing badmen, pickpoket, kill some, hit some and kill a boss for each zone. Too repetitive. The best part is the very end, which leaves a intriguing plot for the sequels. The out-of-animus gameplay is very, very, (let me stress that word once more) VERY boring.\nDifficulty comes in numbers. Though there are different leveled warriors, the battle-system is too simple. Always defend and when an opponent attacks, counterattack them, you'll always win. I've died few times, most of them because I fell to the water.  Apparently, Altair knows the killing but not the swimming. Nice assassin.\nSo, if you have money on Steam sales and time to waste, buy it. But I still don't understand all the fame/hype the game has. I hope the sequels are better.", "hours": 20.2, "user_id": "76561197985047881", "username": "Sir Olentzero", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-02", "text": "Finally gave Assassins Creed another try many years after it's release, and I actually enjoyed it for the most part. Graphics and gameplay are barely outdated for it's age, the story is fairly good and the controls are managable. Only real problem I had was no way to buy/sell seapons and I felt the game was linear and repeditive. I hope as I make my way through the series I'll be giving higher reviews.", "hours": 9.0, "user_id": "76561198046807659", "username": "Scuba Steve", "products": 150, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-31", "text": "Very good story line. Nice action. Made me a Assassin's Creed Fan.", "hours": 17.3, "user_id": "76561197964796676", "username": "Viper90xt", "products": 203, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 196, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-31", "text": "Mindblown", "hours": 20.7, "user_id": "76561198025553166", "username": "A Noob with a bad Graphics card", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-31", "text": "Excessively repetitive. You do the same things all over the game, use the same methods and even fight in the same way. The game gets very repetitive and easy once you learn the basics. If you enjoy doing the same thing for hours and hours over and over a game, then I suppose you should give the game a chance. If not, move along, this is not the game for you.", "hours": 16.4, "username": "MAO", "products": 112, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-31", "text": "Game is not for everyone, and if you want to get in AC franchise, I advice you to start with AC 2.\nThis game isn't the best in series, but definitely must play for AC fans and those who liked old AC's better.\nGame locations are worth to explore, i really liked music and main story is interesting.\nMechanics feel clunky at times and NPC's aren't the smartest, and there are moments when game just makes you angry.\nHowever overall game experience is OK, and if you are willing to do with some repetitive missions and and sometimes jerky mechanics, than you should give it a try!\nI would give this game 7.2 /10", "hours": 32.5, "username": "ic", "products": 297, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "Assassins Creed is one of the most well know Action/Adventure series to date, and rightfully so! I have always been a big fan of Assassin Creed, and owned all the collectors editions on my Xbox, but as I transitions to PC, I really missed Assassins Creed. AC really kickstarted my gaming hobby, and now that it has finally been released to PC, I am more than happy to say it made a smooth transition, with slightly better graphics than on consoles! Director's Cut is not much different than the original game, but is still a respectable port to the PC. I cannot say much about the graphics as they are very outdated by todays standards, but keeping in mind this assassins creed is over 6 years old! Gameplay feels fast paced, challenging, and smooth! Story is pretty basic, and the entire game is basically repeating the same 3 primary missions, over and over again. The whole climb everywhere feature is amazing, and still beats most games to date! I love that we finally got a PC version of Assassins Creed, because it's an outstanding series!\nConcept: Honestly very basic, the storyline is very repetitive, following one basic task to the next. 75/100\nGraphics: For its time, it's outstanding, everything has a suprising ammount of detail, and is very respectable. 90/100\nSound: Sounds effects are great, but the overall soundtrack is very boring, and feels like it was left to the last second while in development. 75/100\nPlayability: Using a keyboard and mouse feels great and was very well implimented! Combat is smooth and entertaining, and climbing up buildings feels great! 95/100\nEntertainment: Concept is basic, storyline is basic, campaigne is bare-bones, but the amazing gameplay and graphics really boost Assassins Creed: Director's Cut. 75/100\nReplay Value: Moderatly low.\nOverall Score: 82/100", "hours": 11.1, "username": "ANTIoldboy", "products": 237, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "This game is inferior in every way to Batman: Arkham Asylum", "hours": 12.1, "user_id": "76561198004358155", "username": "Gaffer Gonz", "products": 332, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "So I've long been looking forward to play Assassin's Creed and have heard so much good about the series. Now I finally got into it but I'm SO dissapointed! It's one of the most repetative games I have ever played. I can take the view points but I sure wish there was more variety to the save citizen and assassinations. I kind of want to just hurry through the actual storyline and skip all these side stuff, but at the same time I want to complete the game 100%, but playing this is starting to feel like a chore...and a game should not make you feel that way!\n+ Decent graphics and location settings\n+ Storyline is okay\n- Repetative!\n- At times strange and a bit clunky controls.\n- No challenge whatsoever for a decent gamer. The game should feel lucky I'm not too good at games! ;)", "hours": 10.0, "user_id": "76561198032147373", "username": "saberhagen83", "products": 40, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "The first installment of the popular parkour based series is enjoyable for the first half of the game, and then it becomes repetitive. The plot is confusing and intriguing and it paved the way for the future games in the franchise but IMO this game was the least entertaining of the bunch.", "hours": 6.5, "user_id": "76561198040221705", "username": "bumph18", "products": 464, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-29", "text": "Back when this game came out, it was a breakthrough in game ideas, but nowadays, it's rather simplistic.  Time and again the player explores one of 3 sections of a couple of cities, synchronizing at viewpoints to locate the same menial tasks over and over so they can play the one significant mission of the segment.  The story lasts around 8 hours, so when this game is on sale, you'll definitely get your money's worth, but otherwise I wouldn't call it worthwhile.  For newcomers to the series, it's not necessary to play this game to understand the rest.", "hours": 11.6, "username": "Bigredkj", "products": 171, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-28", "text": "Terrible pc port. Stiff and rough game play. Its a great series but a very weak initial offering. Start with the second game.", "hours": 25.8, "username": "Baron Calamity", "products": 2546, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-27", "text": "\uad73\uc790\ube0c\ub9ac\uc158!", "hours": 47.8, "username": "Ganam", "products": 183, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 197, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-26", "text": "Excellent story driven game. However, it is console port, not as bad as assassin's creed 2 where screen does not even display keyboard keys, assuming i know all the hotkeys, but its something you can get use to. Side missions are repetitive, same objectives with different locations, it is optional but it gives more play time. AI is dumb and annoying. Other than that it is really good story, it outweighs all the cons. Game has no replay ability except collecting flags. Only bug i have encounter is game crashes sometimes, but i was recording so that might be the problem. Big plus is no Ubisoft drm :)", "hours": 20.8, "user_id": "76561197971293271", "username": "KRostik", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-26", "text": "It never delivers on its premise and the latter half of the game consists of linear combat sections.  One of the only games I've beaten out of spite.", "hours": 1.9, "username": "THRILLHOUSE", "products": 974, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-26", "text": "Assassin's creed is a great game. This game may be repetitive, but the story is great. I enjoyed running around the rooftops and trying to make sure my assinations were silent, even though that did not always work out. I recomend getting this game if you like stealth, games and or action games.\nRating: 7.5/10\n+Good Story\n+Good free running sysytem\n-Repetitive", "hours": 23.7, "username": "Heol", "products": 1091, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-25", "text": "I came to AC just as AC4 was being released, so I knew that the critics hated the first and liked/loved the 2nd and its derivatives. I also knew how well the original had sold and thought that it couldn't be too bad.\n1 hour in and I thought the game was awesome\n2 hours in and I'd already hit the repetitiveness... I was thinking about dropping the game. However, since i wanted to play number 2 i persevered for the sake of the story and this changed the way I played. Usually i'd be slow and deliberate in games like this, making sure that I completed everything. Now that I didn't care I raced through the cities, attacking guards wantonly and suddenly I found i was having a really fun time.\nFighting large groups really makes you feel powerful as the counter style combat is fluid and, while not overly forgiving, it's not too 'press the button in this millisecond or die' difficult either.\nBiggest downside is the central kingdom area where anything slower than a crawl puts the guards on you. Recommend holding gallop the whole way and just mowing everyone down.", "hours": 19.0, "user_id": "76561198016009376", "username": "Gunta", "products": 187, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-25", "text": "an epic game", "hours": 6.6, "user_id": "76561198110431990", "username": "StevenYJTsai", "products": 729, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-25", "text": "\u0415\u0441\u043b\u0438 \u0412\u0430\u043c \u0434\u043e 15 \u043b\u0435\u0442, \u0442\u043e \u0412\u044b \u043f\u0440\u0438\u044f\u0442\u043d\u043e \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0451\u0442\u0435 \u0432\u0440\u0435\u043c\u044f.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561198039042482", "username": "Tina Korol", "products": 14, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-24", "text": "This a good game. However it does get extremely repetitive. There are about 3 different gameplay elements that help you progress through the story, but this got very tedious and annoying. At times felt like I was forcing myself to play. But I did enjoy the story and that\u2019s what kept me going. If you have played the others, there\u2019s not need to play this, but only for the story. It should also be noted that I didn\u2019t play on PC but on PS3.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "Elektra54", "products": 482, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-24", "text": "This is the first time I play this game. I've never been into to the whole Assassin's Creed hype.\nWhile the missions are silly and repetitive, even after 5 years, the game looks beautiful and the game mechanics are solid, the controls are tight. Combat's engaging and never gets old.\nA fine game, one that made me a fan of the franchise.  5 years after its release...", "hours": 38.0, "user_id": "76561197983384223", "username": "ioan.sambeteanu", "products": 271, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-23", "text": "uPlay fu-cking sucks.", "hours": 4.7, "username": "Rucent", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-22", "text": "I had a whole bunch of people tell me I should play this game for YEARS, so I finally cashed out and bought it. It is a good game and it's not too difficult to get into. The gameplay is very lacking and unrefined when compared to *similar* games like Arkham Asylum/City and/or the latest Tomb Raider. However, as a starter to the fantastic Assassin's Creed series, it is simly one of those must-play games.", "hours": 22.8, "username": "Winston ChurchKILL", "products": 214, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 198, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-21", "text": "Very Intriguing and addicting!", "hours": 13.5, "username": "KingRayRay_Ray", "products": 468, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-21", "text": "Highly linear, boring, repetitive. You end up doing the same thing over and over again plus you will spend a lot of time traveling around, because there is no quick travel on the minimap.  A waste of time and money if you ask me. 2/5", "hours": 3.8, "username": "ottucsak", "products": 781, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-21", "text": "When it comes to Assassins Creed I always think, THIS was the game that I remember I was excited to see. Being able to free roam in a form of feeling like you could use everything in your enviroment was a HUGE step in games when this was released. The story is semi-great but after awhile the gameplay can become a bore. Going through and killing targets 1 after one, each location is the same. The enviroment itself and first time players will feel the excitement after the first few battles, then it slowly will become to a halt after it becomes a long story line of reputation. All in all, this is the staple for the series and I recommend it to anyone who wants to know where the series started from.", "hours": 21.1, "username": "DarkFire", "products": 689, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-20", "text": "this game is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ING SWEET BUY IT...... WHY HAVENT YOU BOUGHT IT YET....... IM STILL WAITING... YOU CAN RUN THIS GAME ON A TOSTER", "hours": 3.2, "user_id": "76561198057135400", "username": "PINK FLOYD", "products": 7, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-20", "text": "Boring and repetetive. Its initial shine quickly fades to give room to endless slodging through the same side quests you finish before each one of the nine assassination attempts that you must complete in order to progress through the game. The stealth mechanic is decent, though it oftentimes is undermined by the overall arcadedy feel of the game. Did it only once to experience the story and don't plan to do it ever again. If you plan to tackle this franchise you might as well skip this one, or just watch the story gameplay videos on youtube.", "hours": 24.8, "username": "MarheF", "products": 123, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "I only beat it because of the compulsion I have not to skip any of the story. The gameplay was revolutionary for it's time, but it really got repetitive. It felt like a grind after the first few hours.", "hours": 13.8, "username": "Robedias27", "products": 552, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Great start to an awesome series!", "hours": 14.9, "username": "Vozzl3r", "products": 117, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-19", "text": "Have to say after playing this game again to refresh myself on the story it has aged remarkably well. Their are annoying moments when Altair decides to jump in some direction you never even considered or when he decides to suddenly have trouble climbing something he just did a minute before but over all the game plays smooth and rarely has any bugs or glitchs. I would recomend this to anyone who wants a little action and a little platforming.", "hours": 24.9, "user_id": "76561198006525408", "username": "Serious Sam", "products": 372, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-18", "text": "The first in the great series of Blockbuster Assassin's Creed games. This first game isn't really great when it comes to Gameplay. You need to assasinate 9 people, but before you can do those missions, you need to interrogate, steal items or rescue someone that has information about your target. What it boils down to, is that you do the same thing 9 times. Combine this with a lacking combat system and you would say this is a piece of sh*t. But, what makes this game great are two things; Atmosphere and Story. Especially the dual story; you constantly want to know what's happening on the other side of the Animus, no matter which story you're in. It's powerful, mysterious and I would recommend this game to anyone who wants to start playing Assassin's Creed games. It's one of the least enjoyable Assassin's Creed games, but it is still interesting and a great starting point for the blockbuster franchise.", "hours": 23.9, "username": "PodjeGamen", "products": 578, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-18", "text": "What I loved about this game is the incredible climbing and the world designed after historic cities. Looking out upon Jerusalem is pretty neat.\nWhat I didn't like about this game is the actual missions, I always felt like the stealth was obtuse and it always turned into one-at-a-time 10 vs 1 fighting.\nI played this game in 2009 and completed the main storyline.", "hours": 19.9, "username": "Findaer", "products": 492, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 199, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-18", "text": "Loved the storyline and open-world feel. Areas were all really well done. Combat can get a little repetative, but cycling trhough weapons and using different combat tactics keeps the missions from getting stale. Overall a very enjoyble experience.", "hours": 15.8, "user_id": "76561198036643440", "username": "LTStones", "products": 55, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-17", "text": "Having finally played this, I have a love/minor hate relationship with this game. This is a good game, but it becomes borderline monotonous and repetetive.\nI loved the story and the settings the game takes place in, being able to ride horseback, the \"stealthy\" parts of the game. Practically everything. What I hated was, no ability to save your game (it autosaves and you can't skip cutscenes so if you exit and start back to a point you already where...you have to wait), it becomes a real pain in the\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665at times. The storyline missions become very repetetive and are basically almost the same until you get to the intended target. Go into city, find person, kill person, etc... It gets very tedious if you try and finish the game in one go. Thankfully you get \"fast travel\" which cut down on the repetetive nature slightly. I got so bored at one point, I started pretending I was Batman and killing guards 'cause they kept bragging about their parents. The timed missions were annoying (some more than others, but I think you can ignore them for other quests to progress if you aren't 100%'ing the game) and one I felt was poorly designed (the timed one where you break the stalls which puts guards on you in seconds which takes precious seconds away, the time is too short, people scatter and you can't exactly grab people and bring them there without automatically throwing them). They couldn't add an exit button to the main screen, so you gotta go back into your profile and exit. My favorite, the main character has Aquagenic urticaria. You touch water and bam dead which was fun when he kept missing simple friggen jumps.\nThe repetetive-ness and the lack of a proper save option were my two main gripes but the rest of the game makes up for it. If anything don't expect to binge play this to the end. I kept playing in blocks, If I played straight through, I'd have been extremely bored. As always, your opinion may differ.\nEdited this (Jan 22 2014) to clarify some things better", "hours": 17.5, "username": "Ant Baby Machete Squad", "products": 2156, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-17", "text": "The ancient and medieval settings and storylines of the world of Assassin's Creed have a really spellbinding effect that will likely keep you holding on for the next installment (of which there are many by now).  If ancient conspiracies (regardless of their validity) and the like peak your interest, then you'll certainly enjoy the bizarre storyline evident in this series.\nThe free-running gameplay in pretty enjoyable, though it evolves and becomes better as the series runs along.  All the ancient cities are well designed for bounding across rooftops and clambering over walls while you avoid the city guard and Templars.\nI hadn't played a game with combat set up like this before I gave it a try, and it's a very rewarding feeling to get the timing just right to dodge, parry, and deliver a killing blow to any number of attackers.  Obviously the system of \"Everyone attack, just one at a time\" is realistically silly, but it makes the game simple enough that you aren't ever overburdened, as long as your timing is up to par, even when facing more than ten attackers.\nThe missions are enjoyable at first, but they tend to get repetitive after a while, as there are only a handful of different types of mission.\nAnd oh god, the flags, they do nothing.  Don't waste your time, unless you're just a %100 kinda guy.", "hours": 60.6, "username": "JustAnotherDecoy", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-17", "text": "Great action, stealth and storytelling in a sci-fi, historic 3rd Crusade about Desmond becoming his ancestor Altair to help his forced kidnappers find a mysterious powerful object. I rate it 8/10.\nPros: assassinations, storytelling, parkour\nCons: slighty glitchy, repetitive fights/annoying npcs and slighty glitched dome syncronisation points.\nEven though there are cons, this game is a must-have!!!", "hours": 3.4, "username": "Blue_Pie_Ninja", "products": 264, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-15", "text": "Good series!", "hours": 3.5, "username": "ghost[qt]", "products": 451, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-13", "text": "Honestly, not a fan.  My biggest complaint is that the gameplay is repetitive, predictable, and just generally boring.  Go to area, receive intel by doing generic activities, kill boss.  Lather, rinse, repeat. The controls are fine... sometimes.  Other times, (usually during a chase when it matters the most,) they are frustratingly bad.  And overall, there are a lot of things that just don't make any sense.  For example, every single city guard has no difficulty whatsoever when it comes to climbing walls and jumping from building to building.  They can even keep up with you, the trained assassin.  I understand why it was necessary, (otherwise you would be essentially invincible on rooftops,) but it feels out of place, especially when the rest of the game strives for realism and historical accuracy.\nThis isn't to say that the whole franchise is terrible.  I've already started playing the second game, and it is better in basically every single aspect.  I personally would recommend skipping this game and going straight on to Assassin's Creed II if you are interested in playing the series.", "hours": 71.3, "username": "Gollum999", "products": 926, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-12", "text": "i liek gayme", "hours": 6.8, "user_id": "76561198046835013", "username": "finnanutt", "products": 163, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-11", "text": "At first i tought that i would not get into assassins creed, i mostly bought this game to have something to play when i was bored but i really got into it. The gameplay is a little repetetive until you get to the assassination missions. The story is great and has alot of twists in it. When i finished the game i bought assassins creed 2 at once (not kidding). Definetly worth bying if you want a stealth game you can play for a while.", "hours": 33.8, "username": "Sniff Sniff", "products": 263, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-10", "text": "Good game. kinda gets stale after a while, still have to finish it. minor glitches in the game dealing with movement, maybe a patch is available? anyways its a good play.", "hours": 11.4, "username": "Gua Sha my Penus", "products": 84, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 200, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-10", "text": "Great game played it a lot on Xbox and just as great if not better on PC. :)\nHas many floors, can feel slow paced and to much talking but it doesn't ruin the fun.\nStab Stab Stab will always be fun I recomend for any fans.", "hours": 13.4, "user_id": "76561198050163193", "username": "looneykiwiman", "products": 61, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
