{"product_id": "15100", "page": 206, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "Slightly hampered by a fussy camera and some rough edges around the graphics, this is still a great game. Towns and cities feel alive, the combat and free-running is relatively fluid and mostly good fun, and Altair makes a decent character to play as.\nIt's still worth playing as the story is well-developed and keeps you going, and the gameplay is rewarding when it all works. The second game may still be the best, but this is by no means a poor second place.", "hours": 21.2, "user_id": "76561197970397217", "username": "Arfpint", "products": 422, "early_access": false}
