{"product_id": "15100", "page": 206, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-28", "text": "The story and concept is wonderful. New and exciting.\nUnfortunately, that is where it ends. if you manage to slog your way through the extremely long and boring introduction, that is plagued by extremely confusing control schemes that are constantly changing, a headache inducing visual affect to tryin and give the impression of \"being in a computer\", that just drags. it's not even a couple minutes. Prepare to spend 15 minutes on the tutorial (unskippable) before even starting the introduction, which slags on nor another hour or so of more tutorials.\nEven if you manage to get past this part, you quickly realize that the game is going to be excessively long as you are forced to repeat the same gameplay over, and over, and over, and over, and over and over again.\nHere's a tip: don't buy this game. Go read the story online. the story is great. the game is not. I've been told at least that Assasin's Creed 2 is much better game and is actually amazingly fun...\nafter about 6 hours of gameplay, I'm stopping playing this one and will jump forward in the series in hope for redeption. This game has not aged well, despite being only 5ish years old", "hours": 8.1, "username": "Sprawlie (LordVic)", "products": 117, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 206, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "Perhaps this game was good when first released on consoles, but it hasn't aged well.  It's pretty much the epitome of terrible console port - starting with the menu and exit game mechanism that makes it literally take several minutes to quit unless you press ALT-F4.  Seriously Ubisoft - 6 menus to quit the game?\nBeyond that, as the game is called Assassin's Creed you would be forgiven for thinking it will be about stealth assassination.  Generally, it's not - very few of the true assassinations in the main plot allow different angles of approach or stealth mechanics.  You would assume an assassin would prefer to avoid doing their work in public, or would prefer to use a handy bow from a nearby roof - you would be wrong, though.  Rather, you are expected to get in close, which inevitably means getting into combat.  That's also a strike - the combat is bloody terrible.  Again, the console port-ness appears, as the combat is typical of other console ports (I'm looking at you, Prince of Persia Sands of Time) and is not at all intuitive for PC players.  Much of it relies on timing moves, which don't appear to register well, and are better suited to a controller.  In fact, the majority of the game is best suited for a controller - or to be watched in a LP rather than played.\nTL;DR:  For a game that was published well after the Thief series, Deus Ex, and a myriad of others that contain aspects of stealth assassination, they all do it much better than Assassin's Creed.  I bought this for $7 and I drastically overpaid.\nNOT recommended.", "hours": 10.6, "username": "MP-Ryan", "products": 98, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 206, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-27", "text": "A good game when you can get it too work. Does not seem to be optimized for Windows 7 and above. Same problem with Fallout 3. Alas old games can be difficult to get working.", "hours": 25.3, "username": "Saturn", "products": 134, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 206, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-25", "text": "This game is awesome!! :D", "hours": 13.1, "user_id": "76561198097709572", "username": "njurgalica", "products": 42, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 206, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-25", "text": "Lack of subtitles is one of the main reasons to avoid this game.", "hours": 4.0, "username": "mason", "products": 319, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 206, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-25", "text": "Went backwards on this series as well... started out with ACII. Realized needed to step back a few hundred years and see what Altair was all about. Got hooked! Line... and... sinker...! The series offers more than a good RPG backdrop but a continuous storyline that stretches beyond a typical RPG. After completing this installment (had been playing ACII when stopped during memory sequence 4 to play 1st AC/Altair) I finished ACII.\nThe rich storyline and a deep one at that, surrounding Ezio makes playing this RPG series compelling, entertaining, and challenging. You will be challenged on many levels while playing this series. AC will seem simple after playing ACII, but if you like reading a book series, puzzles, different skill challenges, and realistic game play, you will enjoy this series... on some level. Looking forward to more Assassin's Creed story line and gameplay.\np.s. the music sound tracks are soundtracks are awesome and worth getting... ACII, ACIII, ACIV\n(Note: have not finished and/or played ACIII, ACIV but do have the soundtracks, the music in all three are worth the purchase)", "hours": 65.7, "user_id": "76561198043756853", "username": "jbird2b", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-23", "text": "If you have played any of the other Assassin's Creed games before having experienced this one, you might end up disappointed. However I find this game highly enjoyable if you can look past it's flaws, which can be excused by the fact that this is the first entry in the series and the developers obviously haven't perfected it yet.\nThe controls can be a little tough to manage at times but that's something you can surely get used to. In my opinion the biggest problem this game has are the missions: there is not a lot of variety in them, which can get tiring, escpecially if you compare it to the sequel.\nHowever the Setting, music, atmosphere, story and gameplay are all just as phenomenal as the rest of the series.", "hours": 61.9, "user_id": "76561198050591978", "username": "Martin", "products": 72, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-22", "text": "The worst assasin's creed\nThat being said, assasin's creed is awesome, so \"worst\" is not saying much.\nIf its cheap, pick it up, get started on the series, etc. You'll love it", "hours": 7.3, "user_id": "76561198028854449", "username": "krzwis", "products": 1717, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "I will be honest, this game is pretty old, the graphics isn't that great compared to modern games, the gameplay isn't fully developed in my opinion. The story though is pretty good and interesting, and if you'd like to understand better the rest of the Assassin's Creed franchise this game has an important role.", "hours": 288.3, "user_id": "76561198024719882", "username": "Gingy", "products": 31, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-21", "text": "For some reason I was unable to play this (and all other of the AC games). I could boot this one up at least, but the framerate was so horrible it was practically unplayable. The others wouldn't even start. I don't know if this is just a problem with my rig, or if it's just a terrible port, but either way I'm not recommending this crap.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Doctor Smiles", "products": 868, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-20", "text": "Great game good way to get you hooked on the series, if you do You'll enjoy it.", "hours": 37.7, "username": "Ullr", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-20", "text": "Amazing game the controls are a little wacked but you get use to it", "hours": 29.6, "user_id": "76561198045945987", "username": "Midnight", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-18", "text": "A sandbox game with plenty of tedium added for good measure.\nare fairly decent. I have not compared to the console version of the game. In the PC version the graphics are not ground breaking but are functional and polished. Animations are smooth and environments are well realised. The cities are modest in size and look the part for the period the game is set. The streets are littered with things you would expect, haystacks, street murchants etc.\nis good. The most noticable thing about the sound is the background music which fits more with the modern part of the modern/historical aspect of the story. Apart from that the audio doesn't really stand out in any particular way, everything sounds like you would expect.\nis heavily story driven. The story and premise is fairly interesting. The historical part of the story (the important part IMO) is about a disgraced assassin trying to redeem himself. The protagonist sees himself as the bringer of justice etc.\nUnfortunately the games is boiled down to but a few core gameplay mechanics such as fighting/evading, eavesdropping and, and the main one, assassinating. This makes the game incredibly tedious. The meat of the story is the assassinations, but to get to that you have to do a set number of the other stuff first. Unfortunately the other side missions become tedious after just a few times because it is ALWAYS the same. After 20 hours of gameplay I completely lost interest and stopped playing. Travelling between locations is also uninteresting, but thankfully there is a quick travel option.\nOne thing that I just can't understand is the requirement to walk when near the authorities, it just doesn't make any sense at all. In Hitman it is somewhat logical, you are in disguise so you must walk to maintain your cover, but in Assassin Creed you wear your assassin's outfit everywhere, so what difference does it make if you walk or run?\nThe sandbox presentation is wasted on this game, I think it would have been more successfull as a linear mission based style like Hitman. The developers limited the core gameplay too much when compared to the likes of GTA.\nIf you have plenty of time to waste, this is an above average game but the repetitive gameplay was just a bit much for me, I can't recommend it to people with limited game time. Take a look at Far Cry 3 if you want a really good sandbox, or the new Tomb Raider for a nice linear experience. Both of those games felt shorter than this even though they probably aren't and they both felt much more engaging and interesting.", "hours": 23.2, "username": "Deimos", "products": 628, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-18", "text": "It took me a while to get to Assassin Creed, but it was a great experience. I focused on the story and it was well delivered. Assassin mechanics also well done. Ever since the first playthrough I can't wait to play other newer parts of AC franchise.", "hours": 20.1, "username": "Maciej Medyk", "products": 333, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-17", "text": "Must play. Don't play the more recent one till you've played this.", "hours": 54.7, "username": "7heTexanRebel", "products": 152, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 207, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-17", "text": "You should see it as the pilot for a series that has an amazing start, but suffers from it greatness and repetitiveness somewhere at the fourth episode. This game is fun, but if you aren't into the assassins creed story you can skip this one and go straight to one of the sequels, which are better in almost every way.", "hours": 29.1, "username": "Fucking Loser", "products": 80, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-16", "text": "How many \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s can an assassin assassinate if an assassin can assassinate \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s?\nWell, go kill some \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s!!!", "hours": 8.3, "username": "Leo Lionhart", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-16", "text": "Bland and repetitive. Looks fantastic though!", "hours": 20.4, "username": "Gigadeath", "products": 215, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-16", "text": "One of the few games which I truly do enjoy playing without any frustration. The game has some beautiful visuals along with great gameplay which keeps you entertained for hours, with a well thought out story. I really enjoyed the controls when in combat and fleeing a scene of an assassination. The first classic Assassin's Creed is the best in my opinion... :P", "hours": 12.2, "user_id": "76561198048856324", "username": "IceCity", "products": 334, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-15", "text": "I love it!", "hours": 25.1, "username": "SummerPupper\u2615", "products": 131, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-13", "text": "finished this in 12 hours and did not feel like i accomplished anything...", "hours": 13.7, "username": "Shadow", "products": 175, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-13", "text": "Most of the time, a game series starts out strong and over the years the quality decays as the franchise is milked to death by its publishing company.\nHowever, Assassin's Creed did the opposite: the first installment in the series is actually one of the most boring open world games I've played. The writing is okay, the storyline is interesting, but it falls short on delivery. The gameplay gets stale and boring after only a few hours. You're required to complete a few mini-missions before the main mission \"unlocks,\" which would be okay if the missions were actually fun. It becomes a chore--a repetitive experience that makes you want to quit playing the game and never finish it, even though the storyline is decent. That's what I did.\nIf you're caught up in the Assassin's Creed hype, do yourself a favor and skip the first one. Start with the later installments.", "hours": 8.5, "username": "tdR", "products": 378, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-11", "text": "Very great start to a great chain of games", "hours": 15.1, "username": "ThePCGamer", "products": 50, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-10", "text": "Assassin's Creed was am amazing game when it was released. The gameplay was novel with fluid movement unlike any video game before, and the plot was intriguing and compelling. The plot is still just as good, but the gameplay has not aged well at all. The game requires a massive amount of grind through the mid-game and most of the end-game, and many games since have surpassed AC1's freerunning and combat (most notably, AC2).\nI recommened that players attempt AC1 as the intro point to the series. If the grinding becomes too much to bear, watch the remaining cutscenes and story missions on YouTube and move on to AC2.", "hours": 15.3, "username": "Zaid", "products": 580, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-10", "text": "I've been meaning to finish this game for a while now. I played Assasin's Creed II first and absolutely loved it. I still haven't completed this one, but I'll get to it some day. From what I can remember, I enjoyed it. Sorry for not being able to give more details.\nI will say one thing though: the minimap is rubbish. It doesn't show the outline of any buildings so you can't use it for navigation at all, unlike the second game's minimap. From what I can recall, the minimap is basically a circle with cardinal directions wirrten on it with a opqaue background inside that contains a load of markers for quests and whatnot that the minimap if of no use in getting to.", "hours": 0.7, "username": "\u041c\u0430\u0440\u043a (\u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u044f)", "products": 165, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 208, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-08", "text": "This game does not require UPlay. That alone will sell it for some people, so I figured I'd start with that.\nStill here? Alright.\nThe controls for freerunning are mostly handled by the game, you simply hold the right buttons down and push the direction you want to go. I'm usually skeptical about letting a game try to decipher what I wanted my character to do based on very little actual control, but in this case, I almost never fell to my death based on a decision the game made for me, which is good. The combat is pretty easy, and the controls are as tight as the sequels. The swordplay is intuitive. Usually, the only time you will get destroyed is if you happen across an elite enemy early on, with many of your advanced skills missing. The combat in this game is very much for fans of the \"one-man-army\" idea. There is very little actual stealth required. Even if you screw it up and the entire city is out to kill you, you can defend yourself without a problem if you can counter. That said, the stealth is not unfun. The game is very up-front about giving you feedback on everything you need to know about who or what is or isn't your enemy, what you can and can't get away with, and when you are and aren't visible, at all times.\nThe story is good, but it's better in the sequels. It's also pretty repetitious in this game. After your first or second assassination, you can probably decide for yourself if you will enjoy the rest of the game. The only break from the norm is near the end, where you will be forced to play out the \"one-man-army\" scenario mentioned above, so again, I emphasize, this is not really a stealth game. It's a hack-and-slash with stealth elements, where both are mostly optional. This means, though, that you are given the choice of how you want to play the game. You can hide in plain sight, mocking your enemies from the crowd, or you can be a total delinquent, make the guards very angry, and kill the beggars that throw rocks at you (the game stops penalizing you for that once the story is completed). The assassination missions also have multiple solutions. You are given a lot of freedom in terms of gameplay, again, except at the end. Stealth is impossible during the final chapter. Overall, I would recommend playing through Ezio's storyline (Assassin's Creed 2, Brotherhood, and Revelations) first, then giving this one a try if you find yourself a fan. The sequels are superior, but this one is also worth looking at.", "hours": 39.0, "username": "MalikNZZ", "products": 237, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-08", "text": "Even though it's so repetitive I almost quit playing it a few times, the story was good enough that I wanted to find out what happened. The assassinations were fun but everything else was just a chore to play because it was the same thing over and over and the cities looked identical but I'd still recommend it overall if you get it on sale.", "hours": 11.2, "user_id": "76561198000722022", "username": "Mr. Mayhem", "products": 3358, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-07", "text": "If you're a fan of action/adventure games, this is a great one to have.\nI am not going to say it's perfect as a game.\nUnless you get really good at the rooftop jumping, and stealth assassinations, early on, you're going to have a sore thumb from holding the low porifile button while walking through the streets to avoid templar and guards alike. The story is great, and leads off into what has to be one of the best game series I've ever played.\nAt the risk of seriously\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665off some fanbase, I dare put it up there with the Legend of Zelda series.", "hours": 28.5, "username": "Templar Arrion", "products": 82, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-07", "text": "cool game awsome fights", "hours": 4.7, "username": "tenatek", "products": 13, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-06", "text": "Slow start but good finish. Worth the play!", "hours": 12.0, "username": "OrangeAce36", "products": 307, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-06", "text": "Pretty sweet game,even though its old.You will enjoy it!", "hours": 7.3, "username": "skin", "products": 129, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-05", "text": "Took me 7 hours to complete, done", "hours": 7.8, "username": "Mikoel\u2122", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-04", "text": "A good starting episode for the AC franchise. Fair combat system and interesting story, but after ~15 hour's of play getting a little bit monotone, and you want to finish the story as soon as possible.", "hours": 20.6, "username": "Endox", "products": 313, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-03", "text": "This is a pretty good game, and i can see why it started off the assassins creed series leading on for many more games to come. The story is good, although it is sort of repetative, as in, heres your target, get info on them, assassinate them. good job, now heres another target, throughout the whole game exept for the begenning and the end, the end is good, its a fun game to run around the open world and do random stuff, and it is worthwhile, it is indeed an old game though the graphics and animations are rather good but not \"up to date\"\n6,6/10", "hours": 5.5, "username": "Jammin Hyaku", "products": 282, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-03", "text": "A really fun game in a beautiful setting. The sword fights and animations are enjoyable, and the ongoing story line is fairly compelling.", "hours": 73.4, "username": "Alcasan", "products": 115, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 209, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-03", "text": "Assassin's Creed series is an EPIC adventure you must experience.", "hours": 46.3, "user_id": "76561198052746111", "username": "geostam", "products": 357, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-03", "text": "One of my favs. The first game in the Assassin's Creed franchise is set in 1191 AD, when the Third Crusade was tearing the Holy Land apart. Shrouded in secrecy and feared for their ruthlessness, the Assassins intend to stop the hostilities by suppressing both sides of the conflict. Players, assuming the role of the main character Altair, have the power to throw their immediate environment into chaos and to shape events during this pivotal moment in history", "hours": 0.3, "username": "\u0434\u0435\u0432\u043e\u0447\u043a\u0430", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-02", "text": "It crashes really easily, otherwise great game. >_> But the crashing is like every time somebody chats me. It's really annoying", "hours": 2.8, "username": "Smeppu", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-02", "text": "Classic frustration, that seems to be the best way I can describe this game. Seriously I wanted to assassinate everyone at Ubisoft going through this game, it WILL make you curse, it WILL make you scream, it WILL make you drown in a puddle of water even though you're a god-like assassin who can jump from insane nosebleed heights, no really it will do that.\nThe thing is I kinda like being frustrated, I kinda like sitting there yelling and cursing at my screen, if I'm not then the game is boring and not worth my time. I've started and stopped playing this game so many times... but I always come back.\nIf you're going to play any of the other Assassin's Creed games, and I recomend that you do, you have to play them from the start. It's a story, one that progresses through the series, and not a bad one. One that is suppose to be made into a movie soon too, a whitewashed version of the story (and please feel free to protest that fact to the company).", "hours": 68.3, "user_id": "76561198053215200", "username": "TimeViewer", "products": 978, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-12-01", "text": "Skip it honestly. AC2 is where the series comes into its own, AC1 is more of a proof of concept, very tedious.", "hours": 24.4, "username": "Chief Savage Man", "products": 842, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-01", "text": "Never gotten a chance to finish the game for console at all but as i play through the campaign and finally beat the game, i realise that the game isn't that bad and people should really consider playing it.", "hours": 20.6, "username": "Shinoyuro", "products": 271, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-01", "text": "Great. Altair is awesome.", "hours": 26.9, "username": "Prezler", "products": 39, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-12-01", "text": "What can be said about the original AC? Not the best in the series but close. I still remember the feeling of climbing Cathedrals in the Holy Land and then jumping from incredible heigths... it felt so fresh and new at the time. A very good game despite its boring side-missions.\nVote: 9", "hours": 47.8, "username": "FedericoV", "products": 126, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-29", "text": "Erm, tried to get this to work for about 2 hours. Game suffered from constant crashes on load and random freezes during gameplay. All the reading I did about it suggested that the primary cause is Ubisoft's DRM trying to phone home and somehow failing in the process. The #1 recommended fix to make the game stable is to disconnect your computer from the internet while playing. No thanks. `.`\nI also tried the various firewall tweaks and host file edits that were also suggested but none fixed the main DRM symptom. Since I'm interested in checking out the series, I'll just be watching the AC1 cutscenes on youtube instead. :P", "hours": 0.3, "user_id": "76561197970549991", "username": "RedFox", "products": 461, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-29", "text": "There is no doubt that the first of the AC games is an unpolished gem. The repetitive side-missions, journeying around, and over-alert guards are pretty annoying, but the story (the Assassin stuff in the Holy Land, not the futuristic pseudo-science \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665t) is pretty good and the actual assassinations are rather fun. It's just everything else is kinda... bleh. I started the series with AC2 and that was alright, though this being the start of the story makes it a natural place to start playing these games. The  sequels vastly improve the gameplay though, so keep that in mind if you plan to check out the entire series, start with this, and get irritated at all the little stuff that gets in the way of making this a great game. Overall, this gets a recommendation from me... barely. And only because it is a stepping stone to the much better sequels.", "hours": 27.1, "username": "Yureina", "products": 666, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 210, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-28", "text": "Great story. Not as good as the later games but you gotta play it to go on to the later ones. A lot of people are saying that it sucks because it gets repetitive, but part of being an assassin is patience. Is there a basic recap of this game at the start of ACII? Yes; but if you skip this game you miss out on a very personal connection to the characters found within. Desmond will seem more relateable, Lucy will be much more human, and Revelations will make a helluva lot more sense if you can just sit down and have some fun with this. People are making it sound like this terribly boring and repetitve piece of crap when if you just sit back and be a little patient, the story will more than make up for sometime buggy game mechanics and slighly repetitive missions.", "hours": 36.1, "username": "Daedalus", "products": 74, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-28", "text": "I bought this for Xbox back when it first came out in 2007, it was brilliant fun and i couldn't put it down until i finished the game. Since then i have played through the entire franchise on console.\nRecently i decided to buy the franchise on Steam to play through them again, Assassins Creed is still just as much fun now as it was when it was first released.", "hours": 22.2, "username": "Moving McTarget", "products": 753, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-28", "text": "Worth playing, but mostly for the story... the gameplay is okay enough and the ending is weird as\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 ah well all in all: 8/10", "hours": 19.5, "username": "IndigoRed / Gard", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "All Assassin's Creeds are legen . . . . wait for it . . . . dary. LEGENDARY", "hours": 26.2, "username": "GKASIOS", "products": 731, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "Though this is the first game in the series it is very repeditive and most of the time you are traveling from one place to the other just to pickpocket, tail and save citizens. If you are intrested I would recomend watching a playthrough and skipping to AC II", "hours": 16.4, "username": "Ansarum", "products": 195, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "A little repetitive at times, but still the beginning of a great series!", "hours": 0.2, "user_id": "76561197995615417", "username": "Stefan", "products": 293, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-27", "text": "The original one. Must play. It's different form its sequels but I like the fact that it is historically correct: Assassins existed... during the Third Crusade. There are few weapons and missions are a little repetitive but I like the setting a lot. Sometimes AI does weird things and some bugs are hilarious.\nOh! Also, no U-Play", "hours": 60.4, "username": "WHAT@FRA", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "The mechanics of the game were no doubt revolutionary for its time. The scenery of the game was very beautiful too.  Unfortunately that is where my compliments end. Nothing can hide the fact that you are a dog fetching a stick throughout the game, with its repetitiveness. The fun factor quickly faded and it became a chore to reach the end. I must be in the minority though, as it seems so many actually enjoyed it? To each their own i suppose... now where did i leave that bone?", "hours": 13.0, "username": "NAYKID", "products": 3497, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "It's the first assassin's creed game and it's awesome, the gameplay is kinda boring but the storyline is interesting and addicting.", "hours": 18.3, "username": "Riven", "products": 602, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "I'm a huge fan of the Assassin's Creed series... except the first one. Really, if you're new, just start playing AC2 instead. You won't be missing much. Especially since the intro cinematic to AC2 covers everything important about AC1's story in about 10 seconds. Every mission in the game is \"kill this guy, because reasons\" and starts out with gathering information, which means doing one of 4 types of sidequest where you can do exciting things like sitting on a bench or following someone into an alley so you can punch them a few times. After you do enough repetitive sidequests you unlock the assassination target's location. Then you kill the guy you're supposed to kill then run and hide. Then do it all again for the next target. Nothing changes about the missions other than the location of your target.", "hours": 18.9, "username": "Ultraviper", "products": 875, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 211, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "The controls don't work quite as well as I remember from the console version, but they work well enough. And all the rest is as fun as it ever was.", "hours": 13.6, "username": "mebs", "products": 265, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "I enjoyed this first creed and although it was short on variety it had plentiful novelty. The free running mechanic, the scale of the cities, and the number of onscreen characters were all refreshing. Combat was a two button walkover and the approach to stealth was nothing but silly, yet the joy of traversal and intriguing plot kept me going.", "hours": 19.5, "username": "INT Paladin", "products": 187, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "Nothing is true, everything is permitted.\nScore: 9/10.", "hours": 15.9, "username": "Eterno", "products": 1180, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "wow such awesome\nsick gameplay\nwow", "hours": 19.3, "username": "Scorpion [M]", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "So this is how the awesome Assassin's Creed franchise was born. The game itself is linear and repetetive, but the amazing art style(which makes the game feel kinda \"dusty\"), freerunning mechanic and combat made the game a revolutionary success!\nPros:\n+Amazing story\n+Unique artstyle\n+Freerunning\n+World to explore!\nCons:\n-Repetitive tasks\n-Linear story\n-Combat becomes too easy after you master the counter-attack\n-Main character can't swim\nScore:\n7/10", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Scyrenus", "products": 1934, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "The game that started it all, it has actually aged fairly well.  Even though newer games are prettier and better and have better storytelling and less repetitive gameplay, I still recommend to go ahead and start from the beginning.  The settings are still pretty, and the gameplay is still fun, if a bit repetitive by the time you get to the end of it (you might skip a few of the optional collections which is just fine).  The storyline of these games are direct sequels of each other, so I definitely recommend starting with this one before moving on to others in this great series.  If you skip most of the optional collecting, the game should only take a few hours to beat.\nController support is enabled but for some reason the default keys seem to not match up correctly.  Especially if you have played later games in the series, be sure to remap the controls before playing or you'll get a little turned around.", "hours": 57.3, "username": "Thortok2000", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "2 out of 10.  Not worth it, even on sale.\nOne of the few games I've actually given up on, and should be the textbook example of why PC gamers hate console ports.  The controls are some of the worst I've ever fought with, the gameplay is terrible and repetitive, and the fact that you have to\nto exit in order to avoid the 5-minute nightmare you'd normally have to go through really tops things off and makes the game more like a bad joke than anything.  It had decent enough graphics, but that's really the only good thing I can say about it.", "hours": 2.4, "user_id": "76561198060634908", "username": "omally72", "products": 610, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "The Game is very well done and definitly worth playing I would say it is a 8/10 on all counts.\nThe story mode could be a little longer but there are many sequels to enjoy the setting in.", "hours": 23.8, "user_id": "76561197978573635", "username": "Paladin [RSR]", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "It has some pretty major flaws, but I do still like it in spite of them. The free-running system was fantastic for its time, but the combat can get pretty monotonous as you wait for an enemy to attack. So much of the game involves doing random tasks for tiny bits of information about your target, so I would recommend doing the bare minimum required to unlock the assassination rather than repeating the tasks (which you'll be doing anyway) even more times.\nUnfortunately the game especially doesn't hold up next to its sequels, so if you're put off by the sound of this, I'd still recommend picking up AC2. It's a lot smoother and with less repetition.", "hours": 25.3, "username": "Scribbly", "products": 742, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 8, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-26", "text": "What happened to the PC port? I remember playing this game on Xbox when it came out. It was a great game. I loved being an assasin. But the bugs are so...Arrrgh! I would not recomend buying this game cause it just won't run on a computer. The console (to my great disatisfaction) is where this game belongs. If you are trying to understand the AC universe, I get it that you want to play the first game, but take it somewhere else. It won't run on your PC and there is nothing you can do about that. I wish you the best of luck.\nBUT! This is the game to play if you want to know where Altiar came from, just remember you have to climb the mountain every, single, time.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "RandomCapture", "products": 225, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 212, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "This game is so boring, it brings tears to my eyes, two hours in and nothing is happening and you can't do anything. Games should be games, not movies which require me to push buttons to unpause it. Also the subplot about the adventure being a genetic memory is boring and stupid. Want a game about sneaking and killing, this is not the game for you.", "hours": 2.2, "user_id": "76561198000283550", "username": "DROB", "products": 402, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "I consider this the best of the series still. The other games are tied up in a needlessly complex control scheme that fits console controllers and they've just added more and more \"stuff\" outside of the central storyline. This game has the right amount of stuff to do, and it has a legitimately interesting storyline.", "hours": 13.0, "username": "Quinine!", "products": 353, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "The first of one of the best known series from this era. The tale of the Third Crusade and the Assassin's brotherhood is rich in details, historical facts and characters, and both the science fiction and history are well balanced. The graphics are impressive, especially in the environment design and art: each building, street and structure is rich in details. The gameplay is intuitive and the sensation of freedom running over the roofs or climbing to a tall tower and looking at the whole city below is just impressive. The game is full of bugs, giving the sensation that it was released before it should, but I didn't find any that really affected gameplay. Assassin's Creed do have a Achilles heel, and it is the level design: you just do the same kind of sub-mission over and over until you have enough to kill your target, the really interesting part of the game. Asides this only major flow, is a great game that everyone should try.", "hours": 15.3, "username": "Celebrimnar", "products": 4591, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "The first entry in an annual franchise from Ubisoft and the most unique. Unlike the sequels this game is far from the open world collectathon that the Assassin's Creed series has become. The majority of the game is fairly linear and consists entirely of assasssinating specific characters. Completing the assassinations progresses the plot and unlocks new abilities for you, this game is far more similar to something like Hitman than what the modern Assassin's Creed games are. Unfortunately there are plenty of faults in this one too. The side activities are almost non existent and by adding fast travel between cities eliminates the majority of the open world exploration in this game. This game is also very guilty of not explaining a lot of the mechanics to the player and providing very poor tutorials. However I still think it's a very unique and interesting game despite all of it's flaws. One of the things I really enjoy about it is the fact that you can play through the entire game with all of the on screen HUD disabled only relying on ingrame visual and audio queues.\nDefinitely worth the going price now.", "hours": 15.7, "username": "Lostconfused", "products": 758, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "excelent", "hours": 22.0, "user_id": "76561198005055481", "username": "Asmod", "products": 305, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Basically the game that introduced me to the \"next gen''. Played it on a PC, that DX10 engine made miracles.When I saw the trailer for this game I concluded that it was simply the best game ever. Sure, I was na\u00efve, but when finally managed to get hold of it I was thrilled to see that my expectations weren't unfounded. It was repetitive, but even nowadays I fire it up for a nostalgia trip. The game that defined this gen for me, plain and simple. Story+Gameplay=WIN.", "hours": 2.6, "username": "somini", "products": 469, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Boring and repetitive.", "hours": 1.5, "username": "Shawgo", "products": 439, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "The first Assassin's Creed is by far THE BEST in the series, followed shortly by Assassin's Creed IV Black Flag, which brought a lot of replayability and multiplayer community fun to the table.\nIn this game, hear hear, you ACTUALLY ASSASSINATE PEOPLE.\nYou literally go from town to town, get information on your victim, get a permission from the assassins to go on your assassinations, like ASSASSINS DO I KNOW RIGHT SO SHOCKING, and then you KILL THE GUY. AND HE TELLS YOU STUFF WHILE ON THE GROUND, BEFORE DYING, LIKE PEOPLE DO WHEN THEY GET ASSASSINATED.\nAnd you're actually HOLDING him on the ground, whispering the discussion, not walking around screaming while he's on the ground bleeding *COUGH COUGH  COUGH COUGH*\nWOW SUCH SHOCK.\nAnd the story is an actual story that makes sense, has depth to it and makes you try and understand what's going on, question your morals, make you learn lessons that are valuably taught by Al Mualim (your master in game) and overall leave you with a \"Woooooahhhhh\" every 3 seconds. An amazing experience.\nBut Galex, you might say, I WANNA BUY A BANK LOL\nWELL MY FRIEND, GO BUY A FREAKING BANK SIMULATOR, THIS IS      ASSASSIN'S         CREED. EMPHASIS ON ASSASSIN'S.\nTL; DR The only game in the series where you're actually assassinating people while on a mission from an assassin organization, no BUYING BANKS, no RANDOM SIDE MISSIONS ABOUT WHATEVER, an AMAZING story and an amazing concept that got finally one up'd only by AC IV. A must play.", "hours": 5.4, "username": "Galex", "products": 46, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "Game production and graphics are good, but thats about it.\nThe gameplay is repetitive, tasks, combat and locations repeat themselves and get boring very quickly.\nBiggest downside of the game is the story. The pace, in which it is told, is so slow that you forget why you have to assassinate people and in what way this all impacts on the person in the lab.\nAnd when you finally reach the end of the game, to get the story conclusion you will be left alone with a cliffhanger to buy part two of the series.\nUtterly disappointing and a chore to play through the whole game.", "hours": 16.2, "user_id": "76561197970595175", "username": "[ITZ!]Trouble Man", "products": 139, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-25", "text": "While the game is nowhere near as good as the games that come after it, Assassin's Creed was the game that kicked off the craze. Yes, the missions get extremely repetitive and the story in this game is utter trash 95% of the time, but it's still a unique and enjoyable game that is a good way to ease yourself into the sprawling franchise. This is the only game in the series that is actually tough at times, but if you can get past it... I guess it's a bit self-rewarding...", "hours": 12.8, "username": "slappycider", "products": 382, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 213, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-11-20", "text": "Assassin's Creed is the quaintessential Ubisoft title - fantastic idea, rushed out before it was finished that leaves you disappointed.\nThere is a core game here, which could be amazing. The idea behind the gameplay mechanics are great, and the free running features are smooth at times. Yet, there's nothing more to it. It's essentially a tech-demo.\nI'm informed that the other Assassin's Creed games are MUCH better, and have a better storyline, and don't have you repeating the game over at the halfway point ala the first Assassin's Creed. If that's the case I look forward to the other Assassin Creed titles.\nI originally played this game on the 360 when it was initially released. My hype was high and expectations were perhaps uncontrolable. I remember getting into an argument with the Ubisoft rep who would come into our store about how crap the game was. He wasn't too happy that I wasn't going to shill it hard to people.\nHowever, the first one is stale and undercooked at the same time. The crashes to desktop are beyond frustrating. DX10 version is unstable and unsupported. The DX9 version strangely runs smoother. I get the impression it's the Steam interface which causes the crashes.\nOverall, I'd suggest watching the story on youtube and jumping on (hopefully) the much improved Assassin's Creed II or Brotherhood. The first game is everything that is currently wrong with Ubisoft:\nFull of Bugs\nRepeated pointless gameplay\nCollect 100 lots of 100 different items\nPromises and hopes that never live up to the expectation\nAll of this distracts from what COULD be a really great game.", "hours": 14.3, "username": "Chris", "products": 1901, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-17", "text": "A good start for the franchise. Stealth mechanics and story really shines in this one.\n8/10", "hours": 7.7, "username": "Ashes.", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-17", "text": "What can I say about this game. Let's start with title it doesnt just scream\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665in your face once, but TWICE. No but really, let's talk the gameplay? well I like the graphics espically for a game that came out in 2007, it is easy to say that they worked hard on impressing us... it was SHINY. The controls are so \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing annoying, you are slow and when you try to sprint you jump into\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665you dont want to, and when you want to jump you \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing run off a building. The story is great, probably the best part about it. I would give it a good 8/10 just because of how classic it is and how it started a whole series that won't end. Good work Ubisoft, you did it with Prince of Persia now you did it with the Assassin's creed. Should you buy it? Well if you wait on sale you can probably catch it for $4.99, but you could also use that money to buy a couple of cheese burgers. I don't know you should do what you want with your money, don't let me tell you what to do. :) I'd go for the game pirated and the cheese burgers. Well it depends what kind of cheese burgers, if it's from burger king no way. And also mcdonalds kind of sucks too, and who the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 wants Jack in the Box. Wow Hamburgers suck, get this game instead.", "hours": 21.0, "username": "Moon", "products": 1234, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-11-03", "text": "A game that rewards you for role-playing as your character: someone who lives day-in and day-out as a top assassin. Recommend going for the challenge of a \"perfect assassination\" for greater satisfaction.\nGame atmosphere, lore, and gameplay keeps you engaged.", "hours": 30.9, "user_id": "76561198050175828", "username": "J.N.", "products": 144, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-24", "text": "This is an excellent game that holds up to many current releases! I was worried about Win7 functionality but it runs like a dream on my computer!", "hours": 25.6, "user_id": "76561198046273056", "username": "Symphoneum", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-24", "text": "Cel mai EPIC joc, un joc foarte bun care te face sa astepti continuarea cu sufletul la gura. Incercati-l, merita pe deplin !", "hours": 3.2, "username": "\u2605 Daniel M. \u2605", "products": 155, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-20", "text": "A war rages between two factions: the Templars and the Assassins. In this tale of redemption you won't always be able to tell if the side your working for is in fact, the right side, and that's part of what makes this game so brilliant.\nThe introduction of parkour into the game industry was spearheaded by this series, along with the aspect of historical tourism that the game provides. This series is still at the forefront of these factors, and although the first game itself can be fairly repetitive, it's still an amazing game.\nThe character of Desmond is interesting and the large amount of intrigue brought on by the ability to retrieve the passwords of those looking over your progress in the present day portion keeps the story rolling.\n85/100", "hours": 104.4, "username": "Jexx", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-18", "text": "I reccomend the entire series, so I thought I'd start at the beginning.", "hours": 1.1, "username": "Viktory", "products": 257, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-17", "text": "Amazing, considering the date it was released. However, it would have been better if the storyline was more creative, or actions were more exciting and not repeating over and over. As you are playing, you will find yourself trying to finish the mission as soon as possible because you are getting tired of it.\nInstructions of controls do not make sense, - you will get used to it soon though- you can not put subtitles on or skip cinematics.\nHowever, generally, it is a good game. I recommend to play this game before playing Assassins' Creed 2 to enrich understanding of the storyline.", "hours": 39.9, "username": "Mr.Protal", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-11", "text": "This game will blow you away bros. It's such an awesome game, great story, gameplay and you will really enjoy free roaming Masyaf. It's really worth the money and this game is epic. You will really enjoy it bros I really recommend it because it will really blow you away bros. it is also a good price of Ten Dollars so get this game bros!.", "hours": 14.7, "username": "\u2605TheAssass1n\u2605", "products": 334, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 214, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-06", "text": "Good game.  I give it a 8/10.  Remarkable for the visuals for a game from 2007.  Looses points for being repetitve and having a camera that you want to kill during combat.  Some points come back for having an intriguing back story.  I didn't realize this is a trilogy with a long story.  I figured it was just run and gun.  Intrigued for AC2.  I stalled out on this game in chapter 2 of 7, mostly due to the repetion, but got going again after seeing an AC4 trailer.  Took about 24 hours total to get through the game.  This is a pretty good stealth game, which is in my wheel house.  The combat is fun, but a bit non-intuitive and timing dependant.  After you get the hang of it though you pretty much can't loose.", "hours": 33.0, "username": "drSpockwa", "products": 189, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-04", "text": "I would suggest this game for anyone who likes actually being able to plan out an assassination instead of just running in and stabbing everything", "hours": 17.4, "user_id": "76561198064043440", "username": "zak467", "products": 159, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-04", "text": "I love Assassin's Creed. The main reason i adore the first one, is that you can go around stabbing everyone without being desynchronised LOL. This game brings me back :')", "hours": 10.9, "username": "bum", "products": 141, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-10-01", "text": "\u041f\u043e\u0436\u0430\u043b\u0443\u0439,\u0432\u0441\u0451 \u0436\u0435 \u043b\u0443\u0447\u0448\u0430\u044f \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0442\u044c Assassins creed!", "hours": 5.9, "username": "Ripen", "products": 246, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-29", "text": "It is impossible for me to look at the first Assassins Creed with fresh eyes. The series is one of the biggest things in gaming for me and many others. It is one of those games that are very easy to pick apart critically but are entrancing anyway. The sense of history is unparalleled as is the general entertainment value.\nThe first entry is more a sketch of things to come than a fully realized game. It is clear just how much thought went into the story and the lore, but the actual gameplay is still quite limited. The variety of tasks is narrow indeed, and repetition is unavoidable. Development process was apparently cut a bit short and Ubisoft was quite surprised by the success. This is also a rough console port, with a menu system very possibly designed by Satan himself.\nAltair is a hard man and hard to like as well. He is completely asexual (in this game at least) and more intellectual than emotional in temperament. Yet this uncompromising attitude has it's benefits and Altair does not wear out his welcome. His voice actor, however, is a completely flaccid line-reader. Peter Renaday (Duncan from Dragon Age) steals the show as Al-Mualim. The gifted Jesper Kyd began a tradition of truly outstanding soundtracks here. Desmond Miles, in turn, began a tradition of being incredibly unnecessary in every single way possible.\nI would recommend the series as a whole for anyone interested in sprawling action-adventure games. Stealth is but one small ingredient. There is little to no challenge in the Assassins Creed series but it is a world to disappear into, with it's own logic and laws. I would also recommend playing II followed by Brotherhood before this.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "Major Moolah", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-29", "text": "76/100", "hours": 21.0, "username": "Fear Itself", "products": 837, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-24", "text": "If you like menus this the game for you! (Or if you like historical adventure, this game has that too)", "hours": 11.7, "username": "FRONK L'EMURS", "products": 257, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-18", "text": "It's too bad that people get to know the more recent AC games before this one. When they decide to explore the first game of the franchise, they find it boring and repetitive. I was lucky enough to play it at the time it was released, and I found it to be a unique, engaging, GORGEOUS game, with an extremely well-written and intelligent theme. Sure, it's a bit repetitive, but building each individual assassination and carrying them out as a true assassin should is very rewarding. It's too bad that the following games in the franchise stopped urging the player to seek alternative ways to kill their targets, 'cause that's something Assassin's Creed does right.", "hours": 34.2, "user_id": "76561197977766807", "username": "Julian", "products": 275, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-12", "text": "It's pretty cool, stories AWESOME!!!!", "hours": 12.6, "user_id": "76561198079751278", "username": "[ETS]The~Un-Killable~Kenny", "products": 54, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-09-08", "text": "For me the best game ever <3", "hours": 21.1, "username": "b4N3_fTw\u2122", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 215, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-08-28", "text": "A very laggy title of a thirdperson stealth action game.\nThe pacing of Assassin's Creed suffers tremendously from high input latency and generally influent animations. Gameplaywise a lot of aspects that seem essential for a good Assassin's Creed title haven't been implemented, such as air assassinations.\nCitizens and the environment have an uninteresting and generally unappealing design.\nMissions lack diversity, as do enemy voice-lines that basically play on loop.\nIt can get really anoying really fast.\nCombat system feels unforgiving and unrewarding.\nIt is very sad that the first title of the glorious Assassin's saga presents itself in such a content-poor and unpollished way as bugs seem to be omnipresent and graphics are badly optimised.\nI'd say don't even bother with this title. It's a bloody mess.\nIf you are interested in picking up the assassins saga I'd recommend you watching a playthrough of the first assassin's game.", "hours": 22.8, "user_id": "76561197970705636", "username": "Lesbillionaire smother-hope", "products": 207, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-26", "text": "This is the one that started it all. Graphics are clearly advanced for 2007, I mean, stunning really, and it still looks great today. And the gameplay is great. Storywise? Could have used some work in developing the plot beyond collecting information and assassinating Templars only to lead up to a big finale that will make you say, \"what?\"\nAlso, Altair is still my favorite Assassin. That outfit, oh man.\n8.5/10", "hours": 20.7, "user_id": "76561198009430218", "username": "JacoRay", "products": 774, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-26", "text": "best histrory game ever created and best assasin story depends on book to game", "hours": 1.3, "username": "strangermoon", "products": 36, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-17", "text": "\u0418\u0433\u0440\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e \u0441\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561197992353914", "username": "DragoDrag", "products": 929, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-14", "text": "Eh, it's tough to rank this one.  2 is better in almost every way but actually planning the assassinations is neat.  That's the only part that was better than 2.  2 did more of a push you along from mission to mission dealyo while this had more of an open ended feel.  Still, I'd probably give this a pass.  Almost everything else is worse and, for the most part, the game isn't that much fun.  Well, unless you didn't play 2 already.  I could see this being a lot better if you hadn't experienced Asscreed 2.", "hours": 13.3, "user_id": "76561197985881367", "username": "Lucius Brimstone", "products": 491, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-11", "text": "Interesting how they mixed facts and fiction to creat the story of this game, very immersive. The activities required to progress in the game can be repetitive, but you can keep it to a minimum and the game is still enjoyable.\n--------\nPortuguese translation:\n\u00c9 interessante como misturaram fatos com fic\u00e7\u00e3o e criaram a hist\u00f3ria do jogo, que acaba sendo imersiva. As atividades que precisam ser completadas durante o jogo s\u00e3o por um lado repetitivas mas mesmo fazendo o m\u00ednimo para progress\u00e3o do jogo ainda vale a pena.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "K-Boom", "products": 4189, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-10", "text": "Not bad. Quite repetetive, but not bad at all...", "hours": 29.3, "user_id": "76561198047884311", "username": "honDziq", "products": 264, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-06", "text": "AC has an excellent story which tackles subjects and presents ideas rarely seen in games these days.  It is delivered in a wonderful package that emulates the platforming/exploration puzzle solving pioneered by the likes of Tomb Raider.\nYet it does not share the problem that title has, jarring boss fights which require one to forget all the mechanics one has learned before, where the exploration is left behind and you're boxed in narrow confines, forced to surpass this poor minigame to continue with what the game excels at, exploration.  No, AC's set pieces meld wonderfully with its core game mechanics so that they are looked forward to and a joy to play.\nHowever, no game is perfect and AC's repetitive nature for the investigation process does bog down the middle of the game.  Overall, though, a great start to a series.  Looking forward to the next 4 installments (Thanks Steam Summer Sale!).", "hours": 17.5, "username": "Greyed", "products": 432, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-06", "text": "A game with an intriguing story about the abduction of Desmond by Abstergo who is then forced into a machine called the Animus to relive the past memories of Alta\u00efr ibn-La'Ahad during the Third Crusade, It's fantastic game play that lets you move your character, Alta\u00efr, stealthily through a crowd, make stealth kills, climb, run over roofs, and admire vistas of the cities Masyaf (the Brotherhood's location), Jerusalem, Acre and Damascus in an unbelievable way.\nHighly recommended, rated 10 out of 10.", "hours": 27.1, "username": "bFunk", "products": 4260, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-04", "text": "\u044d\u0442\u043e\u0442 \u043f\u0430\u0440\u0435\u043d\u044c \u043b\u044e\u0431\u0438\u0442 \u0441\u0432\u043e\u044e \u0440\u0430\u0431\u043e\u0442\u0443", "hours": 19.3, "user_id": "76561198013300872", "username": "Runaks", "products": 407, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 216, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-08-03", "text": "Cuneo 29 Jul 2013 @ 8:45am\nlead the assassins creed to weed", "hours": 21.8, "username": "Homohentai", "products": 940, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 217, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-31", "text": "If you want to feel like an Assassin, play Assassins Creed, this game is really good with a good story and solid action. The game can get repetative over time but it is all worth it in the end.", "hours": 18.9, "user_id": "76561198039801772", "username": "Logan", "products": 698, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 217, "page_order": 1, "recommended": false, "date": "2013-07-30", "text": "Assassin's Creed is filled with good ideas that sound great in theory but ultimately fall flat in execution. The first few hours are definitely fun, but everything afterward becomes a mess. Clunky controls, repetitive combat, and one of the worst plotlines in video game history certainly don't help it either. 5.7/10.", "hours": 16.2, "username": "Battlestriker123", "products": 283, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 217, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-28", "text": "Assassin's Creed is not as good compared to its sequels, but on its own, the game proves to be pretty awesome. Full of action, excitement, and thrills, you're guaranteed to have plenty of fun.\nThe controls are fairly simple, but aren't the best. They take a bit to get used to, and for those who have played the recent games, they are nothing alike. The story is somewhat hard to follow. You are a bartender who is kidnapped by a company called Abstergo to dig through your mind by using the Animus, a device in which plays memories of your ancestor, memories you cannot access on your own. The reason of your capture is because of your family: your family are members of the Assassin's Brotherhood, dating all the way back to the Third Crusade, in which the story takes place, putting you in the shoes of Altair, an assassin whose reckless action cause a friend to die, but is pardoned. Instead he must start training again to prove his worth, assassinating nine targets assigned by the Brotherhood leader, Al Mualim. As the story progresses, you learn more about why Al Mualim wants these nine dead, and the bigger picture in the adventure. The ending is pretty confusing, and leaves you wondering what the heck is going on.\nThe gameplay is smooth, with the emphasis on stealth. You can take out your sword and slash your way through, but it is much more difficult. The sequels improve on the mechanic, but, again, on it's own the combat is much fun.\nFor a 2007 game it still looks great. I even saw some screenshots of the game today and thought, \"Man that looks good for an older game!\" I was genuinely suprised.\nAssassin's Creed is incredibly enjoyable and I guarentee that you will have a blast.\nScore: 8/10 - Great", "hours": 19.6, "username": "PandaMaster", "products": 198, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 217, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-28", "text": "Der ultimative Klassiker, nichts geht \u00fcber Altair...", "hours": 5.2, "username": "Xansa", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 217, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-07-25", "text": "I don't like this game.", "hours": 1.9, "username": "Fo", "products": 238, "early_access": false}
