{"product_id": "15100", "page": 220, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-04-26", "text": "No wonder the series is such a commercial success: without experience yet of it's sequels, the abilities, modes and challenges are encapturing and stunning even at the beninning of the seires. In playing the game you are given the task of fighting the enemy from the ground and rooftops, evading the city guard and for the sake of it roaming and purging anyone you see fit. What a game for it's money; alongside a level system ideal for its sandbox agenda, it's a one-of-a-kind starter that distunguishes itself from any genre of action-adventure stealth games that fall between the boarders of Hitman and Crysis (not surprising, therefore, that the Assassin's Creed empire has spread so easily).", "hours": 18.3, "user_id": "76561198044049785", "username": "Bildeguard", "products": 301, "early_access": false}
