{"product_id": "15100", "page": 225, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-03", "text": "Pretty safe to say that this series didn\u2019t really begin until ACII. The last 2 hours of the game is nothing but fights against groups of enemies with a terribly bare-bones combat system that doesn\u2019t suit group combat. And it shoots the pacing to\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 Worth experiencing how the series started, though.", "hours": 10.9, "username": "JustJim89", "products": 463, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 225, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2013-01-02", "text": "The first of an awesome series where you get to follow in the footsteps of  Desmond Miles's Ancestors who happened to be Assassin's fighting for freedom. In this game you get to follow Altair, who lived during the Crusades of the late 12th century. The game can be repetitive, but I personally think the satisfying combat mechanics makes up for it and it becomes even better as the series progress further. It's most certainly worth a try.", "hours": 10.0, "username": "Flamebeard", "products": 1963, "early_access": false}
