{"product_id": "15100", "page": 226, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-26", "text": "The game features a huge, gorgeous world that feels wholly alive, has fluid controls (most of the times) make it fun to run across city rooftops, joyous mix of stealth (but sometimes AI is plain dumb), action, and platforming, stunning sound design features fantastic voice acting and a beautiful musical score. Tons of small details will constantly amaze you even with its occasional glitches.", "hours": 24.2, "username": "JFERNANDEZ", "products": 184, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 226, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-26", "text": "8/10", "hours": 5.3, "user_id": "76561197987836161", "username": "PatientLandBeaver", "products": 277, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 226, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-21", "text": "Assassin's Creed has a special place in my heart for being a core experience with no extra fluff. The story is much more focused than the proceeding games, which continue to tack on history lessons. The gameplay, while being more limited, is also more focused, as each one of your weapons has their own individual direction on the d-pad instead of a wheel menu which pauses the game and takes you out of the experience. There is only one sword, which means you'll have to get better at the game instead of grinding for upgrades. There are also a lot less canned animations, which while being less pretty, is more satisfying in my eyes. I could go on, but the point is Assassin's Creed is a game that champions gameplay and we need more games like that.", "hours": 20.9, "username": "Fish", "products": 947, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 226, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-20", "text": "Excellent action adventure with great ideas and execution (no pun intended). Doesn't feel like it's an old game, which is a true testament to the quality of the game.\nHighly Recommended if you're not squeamish! LOL", "hours": 37.7, "user_id": "76561197998024791", "username": "Pupplehaze", "products": 1376, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 226, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-12-18", "text": "Worst game I've ever played. I heard great things about the series but now I know better than to waste my money on it. If the FIRST game was this bad, im not going to even bother with the rest.", "hours": 23.5, "username": "Wolfe Mueller", "products": 118, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 226, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-12-17", "text": "Dual storylines and innovative gameplay. The story pulls you right in, and the semi-freeplay world gives you a thrilling sense of adventure.\nPart of the game is purely scripted, and part leaves it up to you.\n8/10 - A classic.", "hours": 65.6, "username": "\u26a1", "products": 309, "early_access": false}
