{"product_id": "15100", "page": 230, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-25", "text": "Although extremely and annoyingly repetitive, the story was awesome and makes me want to spend money on the second one. (8/10)", "hours": 18.6, "username": "Marky Mark the FUN-GINEER", "products": 717, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-11", "text": "Action Adventure-style game set in the dark ages in the \"holy land\", with a really compelling story with assassins and templars.\nYou like conspiracies and fighting with sharp things? Get it.\nAlso check out AC II, Brotherhood and Revelations for the 3-part sequel to AC following a different character through his life as an assassin sharing the same roots.\nThis is one of the very few game series that get better with each new sequel released.", "hours": 4.2, "username": "Nex", "products": 218, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-11", "text": "Played this through on the Xbox 360. When I have time I will play it through again on PC. Loved the experience and the depth of the world. It's a shame that the series has become such a transparent cash cow. This title however, though said to be the 'worse' of the series for repetitive gameplay, is simple and effective, and doesn't have Ubisoft's draconian DRM. Unfortunately, it does suffer from a lack of optimisation which, if you can handle the inconsistency, still shouldn't deter a purchase, at significant discount.", "hours": 2.5, "username": "UberNoodle", "products": 238, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-08", "text": "This game starts off with a tutorial full of people that lack faces.\nI had nightmares for a few weeks, but then continued playing it.\nYou play as some \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 with a dead-end job who's ancestors were successful assassins and actually did things with their lives.\nWhile playing as an assassin, you can run up to innocent people, jump on their faces, and stab them in plain sight.\nDon't worry about being publicly shunned or being prosecuted, because the guards won't be able to find you as long as you sit in a garden or jump into a pile of hay. And everyone has 30-second memory, so nobody will remember you.\nYour first mission is to betray your brotherhood and get a member killed.\nVery exciting game.\nBuy it on\nand use coupon code \"teddybear\" for a 5% discount.", "hours": 2.7, "username": "Gaboya", "products": 227, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-02", "text": "Extremely crap controls and console back port to pc. Cannot even quit to desktop from the game menu. Gameplay is repetitive and frustrating, but bearable if for the storyline. Crap ending, if you can even call it an ending. This game leaves no finality or satisfaction at the end. Suck.", "hours": 27.5, "user_id": "76561198052969087", "username": "Deez", "products": 627, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-09-02", "text": "If you like historical fiction, science fiction, and conspiracy thrillers, this is your new jam. Also climbing on everything. Everything about this game is good.", "hours": 91.1, "user_id": "76561197978009288", "username": "Viscomte Herpderp d'Avrigny", "products": 101, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-24", "text": "Want to murder people for a greater cause? then you have come to the right place, brother. kill, kill, kill, parkour,kill, parkour, parkour, ride horse, die trying to swim, parkour...Oh, and kill some more!", "hours": 26.2, "user_id": "76561198039076006", "username": "Giga Lord Rathamanzar", "products": 328, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-23", "text": "Wow.  Was not ready for the mind-blowing, conspiracy loaded ending.  A bit on the abrupt side, but the final moments of the game left me shaken and completely creeped out, but totally looking forward to more from the franchise.  While the game's biggest issue is repetitive gameplay, the story, combat and movement mechanics, sound, and graphical style kept me coming back again and again, anxious to see the battle between Assassins and Templars to the very end.  Assassin's Creed is a sci-fi conspiracy theorist's fantasy with an interesting injection of historical fiction and definitely worth checking out.", "hours": 18.4, "username": "Mythaelogn", "products": 668, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-21", "text": "The combat difficulty is not really challenging and the gameplay gets repetitive once you know the pattern. Play it till the end if you play to enjoy the story.\nOh yeah, this game needs subtitles during the dialog.\nNote: Don't bother to collect all of the flags (i.e. the additional memories) since it won't reward anything in the PC version.", "hours": 23.6, "username": "P.C.S", "products": 486, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-20", "text": "A lot of people tend to comment on the repititive nature of this game. I agree, it was all very much the same. But I found myself totally in love with the sci-fi story that came with this gem, and the voice acting was fantastic all around. I loved how pretty it was, how mysterious Altair was, and the soundtrack was befitting of the game and not obnoxious. If you like stories that stir your curiousity, and involve a stealthy main-character to play with, try this out.", "hours": 21.7, "username": "TheKittyPeach", "products": 289, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 231, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-17", "text": "All great games start somewhere. Some have rough beginings, but not this one.", "hours": 24.0, "username": "[SiN] Mathx2", "products": 436, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 232, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-16", "text": "Being first and inherently flawed entry in the series Assassin's Creed still succeeds at being an above decent game with a story that takes some time to really kick off, all the while you're drudging through poor game design and repeatable activities, but once it does kick off you become more and more invested. Also, tedium curve ramps up towards the end when game decides to throw wave after wave of enemies at you and dispenses with any semblance of already non-existent stealth elements. Vistas and meticulously recreated cities are amazing, even if somewhat marred by graphics that have long since entered their middle-age crisis.", "hours": 11.6, "username": "Arbiter Libera", "products": 2316, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 232, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-06", "text": "Beautifully crafted open world set in a time period of the Third Crusade, the first part of one of the most amazing storylines ever seen in videogames.\nThe series' ability to appeal to an extremely wide audience due to its fun gameplay elements earned it unprecedented success as well as became its own curse, as many players overlooked the story behind it, forming false impressions about the game.\nAssassin's Creed's storytelling is slow-paced, subtle at times. It doesn't impose the most important parts on the player, it awaits to be explored, discovered, deciphered and understood, rewarding those who try. It provides enough entertainment for everyone else, so no one's left unsatisfied.\nThe game's only downsides are its repetitiveness and lack of challenge, but they disappear as things start escalating closer to the end, and as the ending credits start rolling you will find yourself begging for more.\nDo not miss this wonderful game.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Toff", "products": 3154, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 232, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-08-03", "text": "If the whole AC series is anything like the first game, the whole series has to be one of the most overrated in the history of gaming. The game is so damn repetitive and annoying at times, they'd have to pay me to finish playing this. Not sure why everyone likes this tbh...", "hours": 2.2, "username": "Chris", "products": 340, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 232, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-02", "text": "If you have a gamepad or patience for the PC controls (or customize it), this is a solid offering, especially if you haven't played the xbox version. The story is all cloak/dagger/political intrigue, and of course, looks beautiful on any rig that can handle it.", "hours": 17.7, "username": "Dixon", "products": 489, "early_access": false}
