{"product_id": "15100", "page": 234, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "A little clunky ,but a great start to an amazing series. Stunning visuals from view points, sweet battle system, brutal assassinations, and all the collection flags you could imagine!", "hours": 17.1, "username": "HisEvenSeven", "products": 565, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 234, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Assassin's Creed 1 is great. The only part I can say I truly hated was the ending. It will make you break things and it doesn't get better till the ending of 2.", "username": "SQUENIX BASED REMAKE", "products": 2092, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 234, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Give me assassins creed 1 over the second any day; but not on pc, the controls are an absolute nightmare.", "hours": 9.8, "username": "Vaughan", "products": 360, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 234, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-14", "text": "Finaly completed the damn thing was fun. The graphics still hold up and the game is a must have. Or you could go with the latest ones if you dont want to play the first I read the others are pretty good.", "hours": 30.1, "username": "ForestRock", "products": 968, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 234, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Ok so I only started playing this game when I saw the Assassin's Creed 3 Trailer but so what?  I am kicking myself for leaving this in my Steam pile for so long without playing it.  Very fun and intense game!!  I will be playing till 3 comes out so here I go!!!", "hours": 52.0, "user_id": "76561198011239728", "username": "jsvisi", "products": 226, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 234, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Ok yeah its a little too deep into itself but the core gameplay is damn fun.  9.5/10", "hours": 29.3, "username": "eltee", "products": 1141, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 234, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "The game that launched the massive franchise.\nWhile many will say that this title is skippable for new players due to it's reptative gameplay I would say that you should consider picking it up to give you a basis for the world of Assassin's Creed and understanding the story of Alta\u00efr.\nKeep in mind the game is quite a few years old now and that is something that impacts the gameplay (and amount of loading screens) but it is my personal opinion that it is a damn good game and a proper introduction to the franchise. If you plan to go all the way though the Assassin's Creed games (and you should since AC 2 and Botherhood are absolute gems) you should gather what lore you can because in the end you'll need it to make heads or tails of this game's universe.", "hours": 34.1, "username": "Katanasteel", "products": 1915, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "This is a different type of game, one where busting down the front door is not the way to get things done. You have to be sneaky, blend in with the crowd, doing your best not to be seen. With the amazing graphics, and the interesting story line, this game is a pleasure to play.", "hours": 31.2, "username": "Trillain", "products": 854, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "I love the Assassin's Creed Series to death. Nuff said.", "username": "\u2020\u25baP\u042f\u00ce\u0418\u0152\u2122\u25c4\u2020", "products": 1635, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Great game and it costs just 10 $", "hours": 58.2, "username": "Yung Sun \ub2ec", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-13", "text": "Beautiful game, even if you do not have a top tier card. Controls are awkward to get used to at first, but once you do, you will be at home in any of the series. The story is interesting, the game play length is great, no short 4 hour stuff that you see from other games. I havn't tried a speed run, but the game is way too beautiful to waste on a speed run. Pick it up, have a good time, and continue on with the rest of the series.", "hours": 43.2, "username": "Vella", "products": 898, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "So \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing repetitive but a good start for the franchise.", "hours": 36.6, "username": "Rekronik", "products": 324, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "please sir can i have some money", "hours": 20.0, "username": "Zess", "products": 374, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-12", "text": "Esse eu estava devendo a muito tempo e finalmente finalizei.\nUm jogo bem interessante e com um roteiro bem legal mesmo te deixando maluco para jogar o 2. O cen\u00e1rio \u00e9 maravilhoro e bem realista. Uma coisa que vai te fazer ficar de saco cheio s\u00e3o os pedintes nas ruas, eles perturbam demais e atrapalham em algumas miss\u00f5es o que torna o jogo ainda mais desafiador em alguns momentos.\nGostei muito do jogo e recomendo para quem gosta desse estilo.\nNota:\n9.0/10.0", "hours": 25.9, "username": "\u264a ON Fer_Kenobi", "products": 652, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-09", "text": "Great but tedious game, only for the hardcore stealth fans. Superb graphics and excelent gameplay.", "hours": 4.8, "username": "Hellspawn", "products": 194, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-09", "text": "I wish I could say this was a fantastic game, I really do. There are just so many things done so well that other games fail at...the writing is incredible, the story gets better and better throughout the game, the gameplay mechanics are really cool and new, I was really impressed...and then they went and \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed it up. Voice acting sucks sooo much...I hear wonderful lines and they're ruined by the awful delivery. The story...oh god it's just so amazing and good and creepy and awesome and then it just...ends...no fantastic conclusion, no Desmond escaping from the facility, no we have to wait for the SECOND one to do that >:F. And the allmighty thing that breaks the game is the controls. They're so horribly awful, whoever came up with it needs to be fired. It ruins the parkour because all you're doing is holding down two buttons and watching as Altiar does cool\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665..no skill involved in that part. And then the combat system is \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed because it only responds to what you tell it to do half the time and the AI sucks too so they're constantly trying to hit you but then acting like \"nah Ima just wait here\" so then you try to counterattack and someone else attacks and then you die.\nI'm just so horribly frustrated with how good this game could have been. So many things done amazingly well, and so few \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ed up, but those few things make it a bad expierence. 6/10...and I'm being nice. Buy the third one, that looks good.", "hours": 13.7, "username": "-=TheDoctor=-", "products": 494, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 235, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-07", "text": "Assassin's Creed is the beginning to a engrossing saga by Ubisoft. The story is first rate and the action sequences are seamless. The game has a third-person point of view and allows you to easily traverse terrain, climb buildings and initiate combat sequences from all-out action to stealth assassinations. The game itself is a wonderful breakaway from the all too common first-person shoots. Even though the game seems marketed towards consoles, Assassin's Creed does not forget PC players and offers a fairly steam-lined mode of control. By no means should Assassin's Creed be overlooked by gamers as its on-going story is critically acclaimed.", "hours": 44.4, "username": "Hairbautt", "products": 674, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-05", "text": "Very good game. Definitely worth the buy. The game has everything - good story, idea, the graphics are good, all in all I liked pretty much everything. One of my favorite games for sure.", "hours": 18.7, "username": "heaT", "products": 207, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-28", "text": "The Good: Amazing story, beautifully created visually and technically, lots of different missions to complete, parkour and crowd system are unique and revolutionary, DirectX 10 looks great\nThe Bad: Some control and clipping issues, extremely repetitive missions, not very diverse visually, crowd simulation gets predictable and repetitive\nNothing is true. Everything is permitted. This is a saying heard throughout Assassin's Creed and it really sticks with you. So does the thick plot that has come to take the game industry by storm as well as one of the greatest game characters of all time: Altair. The plot is actually weird at first because it's a sci-fi story. You are actually Desmond Miles capture by modern world Templars. They stick you in an Animus and use your DNA to access your ancestors memories to find the Piece of Eden which can be used to control people's minds. That one ancestor is Altair set during the crusades. The second story is of Altair who ends up losing his rank and status among the Assassin Brotherhood by failing a mission due to eagerness and stupidity. Your master, Al Mualim, sends on special missions to assassinate key leaders throughout the holy land (Acre, Jerusalem, and Damascus) to keep them from taking the Piece of Eden and using it to win the war.\nAs you can see the plot is very interesting with a lot of twists. How is the game though? You have a huge open world that are full of side missions and hundreds of buildings to climb. Assassin's Creed has a parkour climbing system as well as a puppeteering system. You control each of Altair's limbs in two different states. The \"socially acceptable\" state allows you to use eagle vision which can show enemies and key targets. You can gently push people away from you and this is key because is you're running around the city knocking people over the guards will come after you, and towards the end of the game everyone is highly suspicious of you and just a few people knocked over will have the entire guard on your tail. The third thing is obviously combat, but if you hold down the run button you start climbing buildings, grabbing people to toss them, and jumping around.\nAssassin's Creed really tried to introduce crowd psychology into the game and it works here, but does feel limited. If you climb buildings people will react by stopping and staring and saying things accordingly. If you use ladders people don't mind so much. While using rooftops is faster and keeps you away from most guards you must watch out for guards on rooftops who will shoot you with arrows if you don't get down, kill them, or move away quickly. The climbing works well enough, but there are some controls issues, clipping issues, and other issues with the camera. When Altair is facing a different way then the camera he will jump towards his way instead of the way you're telling him too. Also, if you run around a pole or near a crate he'll start climbing it instead of just jumping over or going around. This can get down right frustrating when you are running away from a dozen guards and trying to find a hiding spot.\nThe game also introduces anonymity via a symbol near your health bar which stays white when no ones suspects you, but will turn yellow when you are watched and flash red when guards are on to you. When it does this get away quickly or kill whomever is watching you. Don't just kill out in the open or people will run around screaming and call guards. Get away from dead bodies quickly because guards will come by and try to find who killed them or citizens will give you away. If you are caught you need to kill all guards after you or hide. To do this you must break their line of sight and the symbol will flash yellow. When it does find a hiding spot quickly before it turns red again. You can hide on benches between people, stacks of hay, in groups of monks praying, or draped boxes on rooftops. Stay there for a few seconds and you will by anonymous again. You can avoid all this chaos by just jogging, staying calm, don't flail around and jump around like a monkey in crowded areas etc.\nThis whole crowd system is really something else and works well, but feels repetitive and predictable because of the recycled sayings, animations, and it always happens the same way. The combat is the same way because while you can gain new abilities it feels like a counter fest. You can attack with a sword or short sword, throw daggers, but most guards always block and you just stand there with the block button held down and wait for someone to attack and then counter which is usually an instant kill. This gets repetitive and the combat isn't as deep as it could be since combos are limited, and animations are repeated often. It does control well and feels smooth so I guess that's better than broken.\nThe most repetitive thing, and the game's biggest flaw, are the constantly repeated missions that repeat dozens and dozens of times. You can save citizens, do some time trial flag gathering missions, escort missions, assassination missions (probably the most fun), interrogation, eavesdropping, pickpocketing, and climbing tall buildings to find view points to put more missions on your map in that area. Sure they are fun at first, but after you have saved the 30th citizen, or climbed the 50th building it gets old and you just want it to end. Some more mission diversity would have been nice.\nWhile its cool to be an assassin, sneaking up behind a guard and shoving a punch dagger in his gut, and then running away while he falls to the ground without anyone suspecting otherwise is satisfying you must look good doing it too. Assassin's Creed looks amazing, even today, and the PC version sports DirectX 10 graphics with some slightly higher resolution textures. The game looks a lot better than console versions and is well worth another play through just for that alone. While the graphics are amazing technically, artistically the game feels very Middle Eastern with a great soundtrack to support that, voice acting, and the whole game feels true to its time. The architecture is great, the clothing, lifestyles, and jobs people do in the game, but it all does kind of look the same with a lot of greys, browns, and whites.\nOverall Assassin's Creed is an amazing experience with a story you will talk about long after you finish the game, great crowd simulation, and the true feeling of being an assassin. If there was some more mission diversity, visual diversity, and smoother controls the game would be perfect. This is a game you can not miss and every gaming fan should play this.\n~Score: 8.5/10", "hours": 11.9, "username": "Ivory_Soul", "products": 400, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-26", "text": "Game's pretty good; however, it is extremely repetitive in a lot of ways. The story is repetitive; the investigations are repetitive; the objectives within the investigations are repetitive, and the combat is extremely repetitive. If you don't like doing the same thing over and over, this game will make you want to shoot yourself. If I were to give it a score on a 10 point scale, I'd give it a 6.5. The visuals were actually pretty good, and its setting was fascinating. I found the backstory (there are two stories - one in which you are in an Animus, reliving your ancestor's assassin memories, and the other where you are a random dude being tested on in this lab by a sketchy scientist) more interesting than the \"main\" one. Is the game extremely over-hyped? Yes. Was it worth the $5.00 I paid for it? Yeah, I'd say so. Overall, decent game. Don't buy it if it's more than $10.00.", "hours": 20.4, "username": "mooses", "products": 296, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-26", "text": "\uc5b4\uc34c\uc2e0\ud06c\ub9ac\ub4dc \uc2dc\ub9ac\uc988\ub97c \uc2dc\uc791\ud560\uac70\uba74 \uc774\uac83\ubd80\ud130 \ud560\uac83.\n\ub534\uac83 \uba3c\uc800\ud558\uba74 \uc7ac\ubbf8\uac00 \ud655\uc2e4\ud788 \uc5c6\uc73c\ubbc0\ub85c.......", "hours": 27.5, "username": "\uc9d1", "products": 211, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-24", "text": "Well, I played it for the story. I was very disappointed that it could have been summed up in a paragraph. Gameplay is a big step down from the other games (not a bad thing really, just means the devs have improved a lot). I would recommend skipping this title, look up the story on the wiki before playing the other games.\nI think I'm glad I played revelations before this one. Had I played it first, I wouldn't have the dedication to even finish the game, let alone buy the second one.", "hours": 25.5, "username": "MacroPower", "products": 1351, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-22", "text": "A resounding \"meh\". The first few missions are very good, but once you have completed the first couple of assassinations, you've done everything there is to do in the game. Recommended only if you can get it cheap. If you can't get it cheap, save your shekels for the later games in ther series.", "hours": 27.0, "user_id": "76561198032084191", "username": "marstinson", "products": 157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-14", "text": "Bought the game for $5 when it was on sale with the intentions of getting into the AC series but I found the game kind of boring and repetitive, seems like it's 50% gameplay and 50% dialogue that is not skippable. The gameplay mechanics were pretty good and interesting though, just wish there was more action and less repetitiveness. The game reminds me of the film Wanted (2008), even the plot is pretty similar. Overall good game that could have been better, I might get into the series, I'll give AC2 a chance and see if I'm better satisfied compared to AC1.", "hours": 12.3, "username": "R4DFIELD", "products": 417, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-14", "text": "Not too impressed with this one, the controls are a little wobbly, the AI isn't too good, graphics are alright I guess, quests are a little repetative, and there are barely any idle AI audio lines (gets annoying after a while). I would only recommend getting this game if you want the full effect of the entire assassin's creed (like me).", "hours": 13.6, "username": "\u039e\u20ad\u0399\u0141\u01e4\u00d8\u024c\u039e", "products": 432, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-30", "text": "Freedom is the word. Freedom to go everywhere, to climb buildings, to run over roofs, to ride horses, to fight ...\nSurprisingly different. Character's animations are awesome.\nControls have slow response time so, they can be a mess when surounding by a numerous group of skilled enemies but, 90% of time can be easily suported.\nImpresive scenarios, always ALIVE, very detailed and with a lot of NPG characters doing something around.\nAcrobacies in the line of Prince of Persia, variated and awesome movements.\nStoryboard is interesting but, sometimes you have to suffer an excesive dialog before action takes place.\nSecondary Missions in cities are a bit repeatitive. Their difficulty increases with your character' skills.\nFaith Jump from Towers is really funny.\nWell, small flaws but, HIGHLY RECOMMENDED, anyway (and a bargain for its current price).", "hours": 53.3, "user_id": "76561197970078168", "username": "hermetico", "products": 855, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 236, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-29", "text": "I can't tell you how much fun this game is, I can show you the chair that had leaky pooper stains of enjoyment all over it. 13 mehs out of 9", "hours": 22.5, "username": "\u00d6z", "products": 420, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-23", "text": "My intrest in the series started when the 3ed game was told to take place in the Revolutionary war. Before buying this game everyone told me that AC1 was slow, but I thought that it was a nicely paced game. my main gripe at first was the some what clunky PC controles. you can tell this game was designed for consoles.\nAll in all though, a nice start to the series, cant wait to catch up compleatly.", "hours": 13.5, "user_id": "76561198041101788", "username": "A88mph", "products": 249, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-21", "text": "Very good game. It was a great way to start off the series. The game may be a little.... dull at times but, it is still an amazing game. I would reccomend it to anyone who is wanting to start on a new series and have alot of fun.", "hours": 7.4, "username": "Kealmcking", "products": 610, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-21", "text": "Um cl\u00e1ssico recomendado para todo amigo que vai querer jogar o Assassin's Creed 3\nn\u00e3o \u00e9 a toa que me chamam de Altair na escuela ;)", "hours": 3.9, "username": "Gaicoz o Vil\u00e3o \u1566(\u00f2_\u00f3\u02c7)\u1564", "products": 471, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-16", "text": "I haven't played his game yet, but I think it's supposed to be good. I'm just recommending it because I heard that if you do, Jade Raymond will come to your house wearing a string bikini and will give you, like, the best handjob.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "H A F A D A I", "products": 450, "found_funny": 5, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-10", "text": "A sandbox with good ideas but at the end most of them are badly used. Repetitive gameplay almost ruins a great historic setting filled with wonderfull little details.", "hours": 16.5, "username": "Berto", "products": 567, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-07", "text": "Great game, there are times in which you'll find yourself being chased constantly by guards and there are moments where you feel like you're simply doing the same thing again (which you are since you're basically going out and assassinating people) but the story is wonderful. I started with AC and went onto the others and have not regretted it.", "hours": 34.0, "username": "Aracnel", "products": 412, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-05", "text": "The best dialouge you could ask for in semi repetitive game. Altair story was\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665on after this game through handheld ports and no DLC. I loved AC2, but it doesn't take a genius to see...Why are there more stories with Altair that could have came in the form of another fu ll on game.", "hours": 173.1, "username": "Bandit|MerC|", "products": 205, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-01", "text": "God damn, videogame, stop switching me to the sword while I'm trying to roleplay Rocky Balboa", "hours": 32.8, "username": "Astrowizard", "products": 528, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-26", "text": "extremely repettitive, but there is nothing like the thrill of pretending to be someone else...\nand then spending your afternoon in a haysack", "hours": 7.9, "username": "DA KILLBOY", "products": 277, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 237, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-04-18", "text": "This game isn't really all that amazing, although supposedly its sequels are better.\nThe storyline is cheesy and quite transparent, and Altair is a SERIOUS tool which makes him kind of hard to like, and there aren't really other characters in the game.  Game mechanics-wise, the parkous is mostly serviceable, with a few issues of directionality and getting caught on unscalable objects.  Combat is forgettable and made thankfully less tedious as the game progresses.  Side missions are only rarely annoying and almost universally involve killing something.  Level design and atmosphere is actually quite nice at times.\nGraphics-wise the game ran fine on max settings with a Phenom II X6 / HD6850 / 8gb RAM / Win7 x64 system.  Even with vsync on you can get some heavy screentearing during 360 camera pans, and if I Alt + TAB'd the game I couldn't get it fo fullscreen again.\nThis game is old enough that you can expect good sale prices (prolly 50% off the current $20).", "hours": 18.5, "username": "I'm Not Sue", "products": 603, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-17", "text": "I haven't had this much fun causing mischief since Thief 2.\nAssassin's Creed is, at its heart, a series of minigames. 1) Scale towers to get a look around; 2) eavesdrop; 3) fight city guards who are harrassing citizens; 4) interrogate know-it-alls; 5) pick pockets; and above all, 6) run like heck from city guards until you can ditch them in a cart full of hay, a rooftop gazebo, or blend in on a bench. But there is variety in these challenges, and all of this is stitched together with the most beautiful sandbox cities since GTA IV. You set your own pace in this gorgeous game.\nMy complaints are few: no indoor environments in cities, too much late-game swordplay, and dreadfully long mandatory cutscenes.\nLastly, AC offers fluid swordplay, and a parkour-like experience scrambling over rooftops. It's just fun to play, and the right length.  Thumbs up.", "hours": 24.2, "username": "7grain", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-13", "text": "Repetative, but beautiful. And it's the beginning of a story.", "username": "Von the Wat?", "products": 1177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-19", "text": "Eventhough the first one was not what everyone expected, but if you do all of the missions and assignments, you will have a game worth playing and its required to understand the series's storyline", "hours": 2.1, "username": "IAmTheTrueDuck [Matt]", "products": 263, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-17", "text": "Classic game. If you're new to the series then this game is very fun. However that fun dies out after a while as you just repeat the same missions over and over again. The best part of the game is free-running and the actual assassinations. The setting in the Crusades is pretty cool and the world is well-rendered. Other than that, the game is quite mediocre. The story is okay.  It definitely has its cool moments though so buy it if it's on sale. Assassin's Creed II makes references to this game so I'd recommend playing this before the 2nd one, but it's not necessary if you just want to enjoy the gameplay.", "hours": 21.5, "username": "[\u2665] OMFGeoff", "products": 505, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-09", "text": "Go kill a target as you are told. Discover all you can about it, either by interrogations or sneakily pickpoting. Masterly blends detective work and challanging kills interconnected by free-running through buildings.", "hours": 15.5, "username": "soan", "products": 176, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-04", "text": "A great game, but not nearly as good as it's sequels. You don't really need to play this one to experience the sequels.", "hours": 18.0, "username": "Drunk Russian", "products": 517, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-03-04", "text": "Wow. That was a fun ride. Not perfect, but there isn't anything much more satisfying than countering an attack and then slicing and dicing. Story has an epic if albiet slightly confusing finish, but definitely solid. Play!", "hours": 14.7, "username": "Tabulation", "products": 467, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-03-03", "text": "Assassins Creed is a good example of good concepts that were completely overshadowed by repetitiveness. In assassin\u2019s creed you will hop across and climb buildings as if gravity doesn\u2019t exist, you will fall from the sky to assassinate your enemies like a badass. Yet when it comes to water, you\u2019ll drown every single time. The interface, graphics, and controls scream console port, but it\u2019s still far from being impossible to play or enjoy. The game became super bland and boring sometime after your second assassination, the game has the same routine for every city assassination. Climb buildings, eagle view, \u201cbeat people, steal, or race around town for information\u201d, and then finally kill your target. The storyline is slightly above average with an ok ending but the awfully repetitive gameplay may bore you to the point of quitting before it\u2019s even over. This game sets the foundation for all future AC game; you might want to play this if you\u2019re interested in the series.", "hours": 18.5, "username": "amBADatgames", "products": 5168, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-27", "text": "Writing this after I've played the sequel. The game was fun and almost \"open world\" but not quite. You travel from city to city as you do missions and while the side missons get repetative and boring toward the end the main mission keeps you playing. If you found yourself liking but not loving the game, the sequel makes up for many if not all of the mistakes.", "hours": 16.4, "username": "AvidWriter", "products": 1094, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 238, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-27", "text": "GROUND BREAKING!\nIt's like tombraider, but easier to control and soooo much fun stabbing people in the FACE!\nThe quests are a little repetative but the story keeps it going.", "hours": 29.8, "username": "Tularis", "products": 480, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-20", "text": "Climb, Climb, Climb, Climb.", "hours": 12.6, "username": "not okay", "products": 955, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-16", "text": "Assassin's Creed deja un sabor de gran decepci\u00f3n de lo que pudo ser una obra maestra de los videojuegos, y que se qued\u00f3 en apenas las dos primeras horas de juego. El resto es una obra mediocre, pesada y repetitiva, que adem\u00e1s no tardaremos en acabar. Se salva del suspenso por su impresionante apartado gr\u00e1fico y por parte del trabajo realizado en la historia. L\u00e1stima, porque Altais es un personaje realmente carism\u00e1tico a pesar de lo dicho.\nFicha completa -->", "hours": 17.2, "username": "PablitXu", "products": 443, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-09", "text": "Give it a chance and you will be glad you did. The first couple hours are a little slow because the controls are poor, but eventually you get more abilities and then the controls flow.\nIt has a really amazing story and it is only the beginning. Buy it on sale. Don't skip this one in the series, because it's definitely worth a playthrough. It will lead you into a series you will come to enjoy and love, because in the next game will take you into Ezio's life and the masterpiece unravels from there.", "hours": 24.3, "username": "Demadizzle", "products": 473, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-05", "text": "Don't know why this got so much hate. I loved it. PC version's better than the consoles as it had more time put into it and more variation in what you can do, FWIW. The sequels are better, for sure, but I've enjoyed every single game in the series (ignoring handheld stuff, dunno about that).", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Catovitch", "products": 613, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-05", "text": "I love this game, it looks good it plays well, the combat is alot of fun. Sadly things quickly get repetitive. Even so, it's very good for the first in the series.", "hours": 12.5, "user_id": "76561197993632034", "username": "Glendinho", "products": 297, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-02-04", "text": "A great concept but not executed particularly well.  Playing around in the streets and on the rooftops is a blast, fighting is fun and the setting is a nice change of pace.  Worth a quick playthrough to get a better sense of what is going on in the far superior sequel.", "hours": 24.7, "username": "MisterBlister", "products": 291, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-23", "text": "If you can get over the repetitiveness of the game. It's awesome.", "hours": 19.9, "username": "bashscrazy", "products": 378, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-01-22", "text": "3/10 - One of the worst games I have ever played. There are some cool mechanics in it - I cant deny that but after a while (and this moment comes very quick) it  becomes VERY boring. It is also way too simple and contains a lot of bugs (you can fall under map or you can have situation when you cant trigger cutscene). The worst part is the ending - last chapter is non-stop fighting that looks like this: defeat 5 guys, watch cutscene, defeat 10 new guys, watch another cutscene - it goes like that at least 10 times :S DO NOT BUY IT, DO NOT PLAY IT EVEN IF YOU SOMEHOW GET THIS FOR FREE. STAY AWAY FROM THIS FOR YOUR OWN GOOD. EACH TIME YOU TURN THIS ON GOD KILLS A KITTEN SO BE AWARE.", "hours": 16.5, "username": "DH", "products": 486, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-20", "text": "\u0414\u0443\u043c\u0430\u044e \u044d\u0442\u0430 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0430 \u043d\u0435 \u043d\u0443\u0436\u0434\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0432 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0441\u0442\u0430\u0432\u043b\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0438. \u041d\u0438 \u0441 \u0447\u0435\u043c \u043d\u0435 \u0441\u0440\u0430\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043c\u044b\u0439 \u0433\u0435\u0439\u043c\u043f\u043b\u0435\u0439, \u043e\u0442\u043b\u0438\u0447\u043d\u043e \u0432\u043e\u0441\u0441\u043e\u0437\u0434\u0430\u043d\u043d\u044b\u0435 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430, \u043f\u0440\u0435\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0441\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u044e\u0436\u0435\u0442.\n\u0412 \u044d\u0442\u043e\u0439 \u0438\u0433\u0440\u0435 \u0435\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0432\u0441\u0435!\n9/10", "hours": 2.6, "username": "[UA]WhiteOverlord", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 239, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-16", "text": "really Never Finished the game. I liked the free running mechanic, but Hated the repetitive nature of the side quests. I got bored about half way through.\n5/10", "hours": 8.2, "username": "-[Badger]-", "products": 416, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 240, "page_order": 0, "recommended": false, "date": "2012-01-15", "text": "While this was unique when it came out, with cool traversal mechanics and really impressive open world design, its repetitive missions really hurt it. If you do want to play it just make sure you do as few of the missions to get info on your target as possible, and chose different ones each time. Trying to 100% this game will drive you insane.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Gunrun", "products": 1514, "early_access": false}
