{"product_id": "15100", "page": 240, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-07", "text": "Rather fun and addicting game. The ending makes one want to start the succeeding game immediately.", "hours": 20.0, "user_id": "76561197995238284", "username": "IMtnDewUrMom", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 240, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-07", "text": "I love this game! <3 Its gorgeous as it is captivating. I eagerly look foreward to its sequals.", "hours": 6.3, "user_id": "76561197988549203", "username": "Stormy_Weather", "products": 150, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 240, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-05", "text": "This is one of my all-time favorite series. That's due more to Assassin's Creed 2 than this game, but if you're going to play it, you should start with this one. From the creators of Prince of Persia, the animations are top-notch.  Climbing, sword-fighting, and horse riding never gets old, and it has a great story as well.\nI played the first game on PC. AC2 had some issues with their online DRM, so I avoided that and played AC2 on my PS3. I found that I preferred to play this series in the living room, so I got Brotherhood and Revelations on PS3 as well.  But the game plays just fine on PC and I believe Ubisoft removed the online DRM, so that's no longer an issue.\nSword fighting is graphic and bloody, and it only gets moreso later in the series, so probably not for the kiddies. The game contains some religious themes and tells a story that conflicts with the bible, so if that kind of stuff bothers you, you may want to stay away. Otherwise, it's an excellent conspiracy theory.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "SuperJenius", "products": 327, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 240, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-03", "text": "Played it on the xbox and enjoyed it thourghly and was hoping for another play through.  But I had to quit 45 minutes in because ever time I would get a kill the game would stall up for a few seconds.  I don't know if this is just my problem, but I couldn't find a fix it.  Buyer beware.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "vash207", "products": 470, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 240, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-01-02", "text": "Very good. Nice story. 7/10 Stars *******", "hours": 5.2, "username": "Teaddy", "products": 333, "early_access": false}
