{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-31", "text": "Absolute fantastic game, probably the best of the series thus far. The *only* issue - you dissolve in water (i.e. die), other than that it's awesome", "hours": 26.7, "username": "Hawx74", "products": 128, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-30", "text": "This is the game that kicked off one of my favorite franchises of the last decade. It's maybe not quite as advanced or polished as the more recent additions to the series, but it's a good game by it's own right, and I definitely recommend it if you want to get into the series and you like sci-fi / action games.", "username": "Marty", "products": 458, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-30", "text": "It's\n. Storyline - incredible. Cutscenes - incredible. Interactivity - incredible. Gameplay - incredible. One of the best creations of humanity.\n.", "hours": 39.1, "username": "(GoR)Andrew.zhd", "products": 353, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-30", "text": "An excelent game, I played it all in one go on the 360. Throwing knives and Hidden Blade FTW, barely used the sword.", "hours": 0.1, "username": "Chirishman", "products": 700, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "Great game. Great story.", "hours": 0.1, "user_id": "76561198013131164", "username": "gybbyr", "products": 657, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-29", "text": "The beginning of a landmark franchise. Worth playing if only for the story in this one. Gameplay is rather repetitive if you compare it to its sequels.", "hours": 5.5, "username": "jobyek", "products": 550, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "A flawed game, Assassin's Creed is still mostly recommendable. The proof of concept design path is not nearly as polished as later sequels in this series, but it's worthy of a look to see where the inspired and financially successful series got its start.", "username": "Pre-war Mixtape", "products": 879, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "One of the many classics..GET IT cause the game took place a gazillion years ago!", "username": "The Knightofdeath", "products": 485, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 241, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "A good start to the rest of the series.  I love running around on the rooftops and the stealth assassinations!", "hours": 25.1, "username": "Darq Hunter", "products": 209, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "Very good. With an astonishing presentation and the excelent ambientation in the middle east,  during the crusades, the fight system and the parkour mobility that brings us back to  Prince of Persia: Sands of Time, but much improved, this game is really above the averange. The story is great, though it's not worth to complete all the sidequests, since it gets very repetitive quickly, that, aswell, beeing a significant problem in the game as a whole. Even then, it's worth playing.", "hours": 33.0, "username": "Heenett", "products": 200, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "Great soundtrack, great story, death from rooftop.", "hours": 14.1, "username": "Triad", "products": 132, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "vraiment un  tres bon jeu, le meilleur de la serie pour son epoque et son histoire :-) meme si les combats sont pas tres realistes \u00e7a passe, la version complete rend le jeu moins repetitif et cette impression ne m'est pas apparue souvent ;-)", "hours": 43.2, "user_id": "76561198007263140", "username": "Adrien _ purity of light cleaner", "products": 79, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-28", "text": "People often forget, when talking about the Assassins Creed series, the ambitious story and theme that the first game attempted to sell to a new fan base. This first instalment in the series is often criticised for its repetitive missions and clunky fighting mechanics, fair criticism as well, but what people have missed is that as the series has improved in terms of game play and setting, the intellectual discussion on power and choice has taken a back seat. Gone are the multifaceted antagonists and questionable ethics of the first game. If you want to play a game that asks you whether might makes right and whether murdering somebody is ever a good deed, that questions your moral assumptions, I think you should play this game to the end.", "hours": 10.2, "user_id": "76561198001898905", "username": "KKJSDK", "products": 827, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Absolutely top-notch game. The visual presentation is leagues beyond it's time, looks better than most games of 2011. Movement system is nearly flawless and effortlessly thrilling. The storyline is engaging and combat is extremely satisfying. One of the best games ever made and a must-have for anyone who enjoys good combat, rpg, or parkour movement.", "hours": 33.4, "user_id": "76561198029515750", "username": "Catbert7", "products": 324, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "If you have the computer for it, max settings on the director\"s cut is INSANE.", "hours": 2.5, "username": "Jae", "products": 177, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "One of the best stories I've ever seen in a game.", "hours": 21.2, "username": "Naftali", "products": 293, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "I love this series!!!...you have to own it all!", "hours": 10.8, "username": "[RCF]HAWK", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "It's not as bad as folks say it is. Cheaper than a plane ticket to the Holy Lands, and slightly less hazardous to your health.", "hours": 25.8, "username": "spate", "products": 1575, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 242, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-27", "text": "Fun, but gameplay pales in comparison to the rest in the series. Hard to go back to playing this after Assassin's Creed 2.", "username": "hoserama99", "products": 2130, "early_access": false}
