{"product_id": "15100", "page": 243, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-22", "text": "Terrible piece of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 I had this on the 360 and only got it again because it was part of some bundle I bought a year ago for $10. It's a clunky pile of\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665that makes you do the exact same thing over and over again.\nTLDR: It's\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665buy the 2nd one instead", "username": "Some Guy with Terrible Shoes", "products": 515, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 243, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-12", "text": "Interesting concept, astonishing graphic design, hardly acceptable plot and really, really  monotonous gameplay. That game could be a killer if it was a two, three times shorter. Worth to play anyway.\nP.S. For some reason Steam says I have only 0.7 hours played. Well, it should be 0.7 months or something. It's too long.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "Tikonderoga", "products": 514, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 243, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-12-06", "text": "Anything that forces uplay I cannot reccomend. Uplay makes games unplayable.", "username": "Carlos Danger", "products": 777, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-04", "text": "Lemme explain in one word: REDUNDANT.\nGood: Unique Game mechanics, awesome graphics, good atmosphere. Nice stealthy gameplay.\nBad: Game flow follows a very straight patern: Go in a town, go in bureau, get information/do challenge ,go back to bureau, watch a scene, assassinate your target, watch a scene, go back to bureau, watch a scene, move for about 15 seconds, watch another scene, get a new move/weapon. Repeat 7 more time and congrats you beat the game. I'm not even exagerating. You REALLY do that, EXACTLY like mentionned. There is some pointless side-stuff like rescuing citizens or picking up flags. Who cares. OH, the cities. theres 3 cities(4 with yours) and all 3 look exactly the same beside a slight color change. Fighting is kinda button mashing, controls are a little bit akward when running. Npcs keeps saying the same stuff. Ending is bad.\nThe gameplay is a mix between Arkham asylum and Ninja Gaiden. In my opinion, avoid this game even if it's actually good.\nOverall: 7/10", "hours": 17.3, "username": "hhhhh", "products": 458, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-03", "text": "Buy it cheap and suffer through the frustrating controls. It isn't a bad game, it just isn't quite polished, yet.  I really think you should try to finish it anyway, if only because it gives you an introduction to one of the best story arcs to hit a video game series in... ever? Believe me: the sequels get better!", "hours": 23.9, "username": "mdwyer", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-12-01", "text": "I want to like this game I really do, but its just such a\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665poor job of converting it to pc its unforgivable.\nFirstly it takes 4 menus 2 load screen and a conformation box to exit the game, which in all take about 40 secconds.\nThe HUD is crap, its an xbox dpad, useless for a 1234 keyboard layout.\nthe controls fair no better, it is a littral mapping of pad A = LMB, etc\neach button does about 3 things depending if your holding control or shift, I have 152 keys let me use them!\nAside from that, the game is pretty slow paced, building up to the assisintations, which isn't as bad as it seems, despite the game trying it's best to make movement not feel slow, becomes a chore.\nIt does have some spark to it, the climing animations is fanstasticly well done, and fighting is enjoyable, but you have very little connection with  the enviroment around you, nothing ever changes or progresses, making playing it seem pointless.", "hours": 2.6, "username": "Tuna", "products": 262, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-28", "text": "The origin of AC chronicles,\nThe story is well deployed, the lore is great\nfighting scences maybe too boring due to overpowerness\ntravelling time is taking too much time when one is trying to explore all zones", "hours": 0.0, "username": "Astori Heichalot", "products": 4146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-23", "text": "It's been somewhat superceded by the later games, but this is still a very interesting look into a very different take on the action genre.", "hours": 32.4, "username": "CarlCX", "products": 2372, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-22", "text": "Coole Story, auch wenn sie \u00f6fters eint\u00f6nig ist.", "hours": 26.6, "user_id": "76561198018478327", "username": "Skip", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-10", "text": "Assassin's Creed, strange meta-story, but it really set things up for a great series. If you liked Prince of Persia, it's the same style of free-running, but you play an Assassin named Altair. This game was really fun, though repetitive at times.", "hours": 16.7, "username": "ItadakiTom", "products": 491, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-07", "text": "This game was great at first, but then the side quests start to get monotonous. I recommend not doing all of the side quests, since they don't really offer any sort of accomplishment in the game. The story is slow, but interesting, and the graphics are decent. The controls can be aggrevating in certain situations. The gameplay is much better with a controller.\nRating: 7.5/10", "hours": 23.2, "username": "Walker", "products": 1479, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-11-07", "text": "The first game in what will be an epic saga from Ubisoft. You follow Desmond Miles as he's placed into a machine known as the Animus which allows the partcipant to relive key moments of an ancestor.\nThe ancestor in question is an Assassin called Alair in what history remembers as The Crusades. The story is rich and environments the same.\nThis is a must buy - no hesitation. After, you'll want to play it's sucessors Assassin's Creed II, Assassin's Creed: Brotherhood and the upcoming (at the time of writing) Assassin's Creed: Revelations.", "hours": 3.0, "username": "LordReserei", "products": 230, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 244, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-28", "text": "If you've ever wanted to feel the need to murder a game designer due to clumsy controls, you won't be disappointed by this game.", "hours": 1.8, "username": "Drache", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-27", "text": "It plays a good as it looks. Go back in time and assassinate bad people. What's not to love? Large cities to explore? CHECK! good plot? CHECK! loads of sequels? CHECK! You should probably CHECK out where it all began.... ouch", "username": "Zipomatic", "products": 2068, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-21", "text": "The first of an epic novel, full of twists and unimaginable events. Awesome.", "username": "Humanista", "products": 104, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-11", "text": "GTA IV based on Crusades! :P Nah, really. Love this game. Good concept, better graphics and well planned control system. Another one you can not ignore! Add it to your collection!", "hours": 20.0, "user_id": "76561197967669726", "username": "Krakis", "products": 6704, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-10-02", "text": "Though the following Assassin's Creeds get better and  better, this one is worth it's salt. I am thoroughly enjoying this one and the story.", "hours": 15.5, "username": "Zason", "products": 110, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-28", "text": "A VERY nice game!!!! But the sequel is even better!!!!", "username": "[+rep] RePLAY [DK]", "products": 215, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-14", "text": "NOTE: Don't hold the downsides of this game against the rest of the series. They simply don't apply.\nIt's a pretty game. FANTASTIC game mechanic for moving through the world, but it's like they spent all of their time making a gorgeous looking game and putting together an amazing game engine and almost neglected to actually build a game for them to be used in.\nPretty cool until you realize how repetative it gets.\nAll in all, it's totally worth playing as a way to learn the basic controls that the rest of the series will build on, and as the first part of an epic and utterly insane story spanning thousands of years of humans history.", "username": "Thunderous Clockwork WarMachine", "products": 312, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-09", "text": "Assassin's Creed is a great example of a development studio taking a risk and having it pay off. With it's pioneering of the puppet control system for third person \"platformers\" and the use of free-running (which later in 2009 spurred Mirror's Edge).\nAssassin's Creed has a basic flow. You get a mission in one of five regions, you arrive, you do all the pre-requisite \"open world\" missions to prepare (such as surveying the area from a perch and stealing valuable information that you can use to better approach the target), then you start the actual assassination.\nWhile others seemed to get annoyed with the preperation phase, I didn't mind it so much as it helped push the sense of how preparation was key for things like this, though some variety wouldn't have hurt.\nWhile Assassin's Creed requires a dual-core procesessor, it does perform quite well on anything that meets the minimum requirements. Unlike most console ports, the frames are smooth and the details are much better.", "hours": 13.0, "username": "Freyar", "products": 1368, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-03", "text": "Its a fun rooftop running simulator", "hours": 12.9, "username": "Raymond Tracer", "products": 4093, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-09-03", "text": "An older game but still a great one. If you havn't tried the assassins creed genre yet, start from the begining. The storyline is great the world is spectacular, and the fighting is good. Its an old game so its not too expensive but I believe anyone would enjoy it. Yes, parts of it is repetative but that doesn't make it any less fun.", "hours": 6.0, "user_id": "76561198002986817", "username": "Phantom Virus", "products": 356, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 245, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-21", "text": "+++ gorgeous mapping... feels like the middle ages\n+++ thus nice atmosphere\n++ great character design\n++ free running is very funny, well coded\n- story kind of lame\n- games about evil templers... we had that! like a million times!\n- the fights are SUPER easy, but get a little less easy in the end... still, you are nearby unbeatable due to health regeneration in combat\n- the mission design is very repetitive... the game gets boring very fast", "username": "kingkrabbe.#bof", "products": 178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-20", "text": "Personally I really liked this game. Trying to get 100% on AC1 was satisfying. Nothing over the top, but it was good enough.", "username": "Mr. Roboto", "products": 2488, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-13", "text": "I really enjoyed the story, ideas  and initial gameplay of assassins creed but became frustrated at the repitition of the gameplay. I did find the game compelling enough for me to want to complete but the repitition did start to make this game feel like a chore.", "hours": 24.7, "username": "Invisible Man", "products": 514, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-09", "text": "The first entry in the Assassin's Creed series is, at best, an okay game. The visuals were great when the game was new and the gameplay was pretty solid--it's just that once you got an hour or two in, you saw pretty much all the gameplay there was! Exploring the Holy Land as a bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665Assassin in a mind-trippingly weird story is pretty gratifying, but the city guards seem to suffer form Criminal Scum disorder at times.\nIf you like your games with weird stories, this is definitely for you; if you can't stand repetition, then you might steer clear of it.", "hours": 9.4, "username": "Adamaeus", "products": 236, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-09", "text": "Gameplay is a bit repetitive, but the setting and the story of Desmond and Altair will keep you interested. 3/5*", "hours": 29.2, "username": "Riquerico", "products": 308, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-04", "text": "Assassin's Creed is a game that got so much right, it paved a golden path for its awesome sequels\u2026 but it\u2019s one big flaw marred it enough that it falls short of gaming perfection and many have chided it for this.  That flaw was repetition\u2026 for such a vast and beautiful recreation of the Holy Land\u2026 and for the total awesomeness it is to be an Assassin, the variety of things to do available is meager in comparison.\nOverall, I highly recommend this game\u2026 but more for the story than for the gameplay.  Finish the story all the way and then go play Assassin's Creed II for both the story and the far superior gameplay and variety.  The production value on these games is so high, it\u2019s worth it.", "hours": 28.1, "username": "Vaulcul", "products": 755, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-02", "text": "What can I say, Its Assassin's Creed man!", "hours": 47.5, "username": "FoReVeR", "products": 393, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-01", "text": "Incredible game! Very fanny, good story. I recomment this game for all gamers that like of adventure in middle age! But this game is  repetitive.", "hours": 36.0, "username": "oseiascs", "products": 95, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-08-01", "text": "Visually stunning game that suffers from crude story and repetitive gameplay. The game basically consists of killing nine victim's in three beautifully designed cities. To find their whereabouts you climb up all the city towers to reveal informers. Those ask for one of four quest types (time challenges, pick pocket, eavesdropping or interrogation) to be completed to share information with you. You can also help various citizen harrassed by guards (by slaying the guards). Doing all that takes about 90 minutes until you finally get to the victim (which means you can easily beat the game at a weekend). Combat is mainly clicking at the right moment to initiate a combo or counter attack and looks pretty cool, like really all character movement in the game. The game could have been much more though if it had a more compelling story and more mission variation. Still, entertaining.", "hours": 27.3, "username": "go_oh", "products": 103, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-31", "text": "This is one of the worst games I've ever played.\nThe movement and combat are frustrating due to inconsistant response. Not to mention the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 fixed-angle camera that you are forced into using at key events and missions. This retard camera, combined with a lock on all movement during \"story events\", has caused me to get stuck on\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665like walls and headstones, making it impossible to move, and forcing a restart of the mission since I can't move to the next trigger zone because I'm stuck on a wall. This is pretty \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665ing \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665, but cannot beat the aggravating, \"now I'm yelling and everyone in the house thinks I have a problem\", targeting system, that, I can't quite tell if it locks or not, but will switch targets, and when you are attacked, will lock on, prevent you from fleeing if health is low. Of course this might all be bearable if the story didn't the depth of Dan Brown's 3rd grade picture book written in retardese. (-20/100)", "hours": 24.9, "user_id": "76561198004008090", "username": "BAT SONAR TECHNICIAN 1ST CLASS", "products": 76, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 246, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-31", "text": "It's fun to go running the rooftops and killin' nazzies.  What?  There aren't Nazis in this?  Whatever.  It's still fun.", "hours": 24.6, "username": "Boxcar", "products": 431, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-31", "text": "It gets a little repetitive towards the end, but if you're complaining about how often you have to assassinate people with a hidden blade for a finger, watch out - I'm coming to stab you.", "hours": 10.4, "username": "Yer a wizard harry", "products": 413, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-30", "text": "Was amasing for it's time, even though the newer ones have taken a big step forward, you should play through this one to get plot.", "hours": 1.8, "user_id": "76561197999030938", "username": "Malsyste", "products": 361, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-26", "text": "Addicting as heck. I love to stab people with the hidden blade.", "hours": 22.6, "username": "HusKee", "products": 145, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-23", "text": "", "hours": 33.1, "username": "esoel_", "products": 441, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-07-16", "text": "Only the second most terrible thing named Creed.", "hours": 1.2, "username": "mesmermized", "products": 2054, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-14", "text": "Great game. Great way to open up a completely new series. The game looks good for its time, free running plays fluidly, and the story is very good. One complaint that most people seem to share, although this wasnt an issue for me, was that the missions became too repetitive. I can see how people found that to be the case but if you stick to doing the bare minimum required to move on, you literally cut the busy work in half and shorten the games lifespan to the perfect length. The combat is very easy and its almost impossible to die from combat once you learn how to counter attack but that doesnt take away from the games experience because you still end up running and sneaking from guards for the sake of saving time. The long horse rides from city to city can be a bit of a pain and the games ending is a TERRIBLE cliffhanger that leaves much to be desired but by the time youre reading this, AC2 is already out anyways so what does it matter? This game is a great buy and its a MUST play.", "hours": 0.4, "username": "Jugs", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "Great 2006-7 action game,although not a RPG,it really has many features that make it look like it is.\nStory: is very interesting although it's a bit linear but it gives the player the chance to take his time to find out details about his/her missions.\nGraphics: very good,there are vast environments with huge cities and castles.\nAlso the game includes a very good illustration of how Jerusalem looked like.On some interviews developers stated that they tried their best to create the maps to look exactly like how it was back then.\nNo special effects of explotions or casting magic,its more the realistic kind of gaming.\nMusic: fine,although they could have done something more epic than they did.\nGameplay: simple fight system,gets boring after realizing you are repeating yourself over and over and over again.\nHowever there is a super awesome feature,building-climbing and freerunning.This will keep up your interest and help you enjoy yourself through the game for sure!", "hours": 35.9, "username": "Zweis\u2020ein ( \u0ca0_\u0ca0)", "products": 261, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-11", "text": "Great Graphics, Excellent Storyline. As for Gameplay Value: The repetitiveness makes the game a bit of a go nowhere time-suck.  7/10", "hours": 43.4, "username": "Vel", "products": 532, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "From beginning to end, Assassin's Creed succeeds in making you feel like a Medieval badass.", "hours": 27.1, "username": "Alecthar", "products": 344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 247, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-09", "text": "An all around joy to play.  The ease with which you control your character feels soft and natural.  The detail in the maps including architecture and the cast are very beautiful.", "hours": 5.3, "username": "$MKR_Indica", "products": 1178, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 248, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-08", "text": "This is my favorite of the series I think because of the time it takes place. And its in an area of the world I have always wanted to visit. This game as are the sequels, very detailed and gorgeous graphically. The Story is something that other developers could take a few lessons from in its consistency and scope while maintaining a huge level of open ended game play. Take the time to sit back and become a master swordsman as you travel from city to city. You will become so good that you will never be touched by a sword again regardless of the number of  foes (timing is everything). Buy this game at any price but it is a steal when on sale.", "hours": 49.9, "user_id": "76561197965463427", "username": "Metatron", "products": 536, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 248, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "O jogo \u00e9 bom e bem bacana", "hours": 5.5, "username": "Half Life", "products": 248, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 248, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "In the first Assassin's Creed game you're the boring dude (Desmond) who's been kidnapped and is forced to lie the hell down and run around in a virtual reality as his assassin ancestor Altair, because the modern day moe'suckra Templars want information from your tiny baby brain memory.\nThis game is as good as the second game but in it's own way. I feel a bit more like an assassin in this one (though he still looks a bit out of place), the combat is more of a challenge and assassinating people is generally harder. There isn't as much side stuff to do just the flag collecting thing, and those other 3 optional missions you can do when you're finding information for each assassination memory.\nYou can't change your clothes and armour and you are given weapons when the game says so. You also have alot less weapons than Ezio and you don't get as much help. Overall it's just more challenging but it feels like a bigger achievement when you kill them dudes good.", "hours": 83.2, "username": "Schnee", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 248, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-07", "text": "Incredible game. One of my all time favorites!\n9/10", "username": "Skurmes", "products": 140, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 248, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-06", "text": "F\u3067\u30bf\u30fc\u30b2\u30c3\u30c8\u30ed\u30c3\u30af\u3057\u3066\u304b\u3089\u6226\u95d8\u3001\u3084\u308a\u306b\u304f\u3059\u304e\u308b\u3000AC2 AC:BH\u304b\u3089\u306f\u3044\u3063\u305f\u4eba\u306f\u304a\u52e7\u3081\u3067\u304d\u306a\u3044\u3002\n\u30b9\u30c8\u30fc\u30ea\u30fc\u3092\u7406\u89e3\u3057\u305f\u3044\u4eba\u306b\u306f\u304a\u52e7\u3081\u3059\u308b", "hours": 2.0, "username": "EDILTE", "products": 343, "early_access": false}
