{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "This Adventure Game is super cool and nice story.", "hours": 50.9, "username": "\ue013Mathroy", "products": 1392, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "The landscape is breath-taking.  Even when I've scaled the same building countless times, I still marvel at its detail and texture.  The main missions feel repetitive after a while and the sword fighting is archaic.  However, the actions associated with the hidden blade are thrilling.  The story keeps you interested all the way to the end and will make you a life-long franchise devotee after the credits.  A must buy for any gamer who enjoys historical detail.", "hours": 29.2, "username": "JediPeaceWalker", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "You are an assassin and you go into like, cyber space which leads to time travel and then you act like a sneaky ninja and kill people and then hde in hay and climb buildings in ridiculous  ways while people point and laugh at you. But what the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 do they know? You're just going to kill them. You also get to play with birds as in you go and stalk them and then look around and then fly off buildings. Awww yeah.", "hours": 8.2, "username": "\u02b2\u1d58\u02e2\u1d57 Phreak Attack", "products": 530, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "A decent port of a great 360 game, one of the last untainted by Uplay.", "hours": 6.6, "username": "Jackal Frost", "products": 1634, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "DO YOU WANNA STAB CRUSADERS AND TEMPLARS IN THE\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665?!? DO YOU WANT TO HAVE CUTSCENES WHERE THE MOUTHS DONT ALWAYS SYNCH WITH THE VOICES?!!? DO YOU WANNA FEEL LIKE A GOD!?!?!? THEN STOP BEING SUCH A GODDAMNED \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 AND BUY THIS GAME ALREADY!!!", "hours": 45.7, "username": "Magical Jollyfish", "products": 437, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Great game and series. You have the option of going stealth or run and gun. The mechanics are amazing. You can jump and climb on virtually anything. Using combinations is very rewarding.", "hours": 35.4, "username": "The House...", "products": 305, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Amazing game with amazing views easy controls and compelling story.\nNothing like stalking through the roofs to jump down and plunge a dagger through an enemies heart.", "hours": 19.1, "user_id": "76561197997047205", "username": "JCare", "products": 116, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 249, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-03", "text": "Pretty fun", "hours": 0.7, "username": "Terro", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-02", "text": "Despite this game having many many many many many flaws, the core assassination gameplay is stellar, and the game establishes the key story foundation that the proceeding (and greatly improved) games in the series have built upon. Avoid the non-mandatory side quests, and this game should be fun enough to play to the end.", "hours": 10.3, "username": "TheHeeyyy", "products": 261, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-07-01", "text": "Awesome wrapped in win, this game is the bee's knees, hips, and every other conceivable part. Particularly for history nuts, this game will thrill all those who love a well told story.", "hours": 49.4, "user_id": "76561198022080369", "username": "Daemonkin", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-25", "text": "This is a great game.", "hours": 28.8, "username": "Hwarang", "products": 815, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-23", "text": "The story is a bit hard to swallow, but the gameplay is fantastic! Nothing like skulking through the shadows and slitting the throats of traitors.", "hours": 2.5, "username": "Hardcore Innards", "products": 234, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-21", "text": "NOTE: Only worth it if it is on sale, game play is repetitive but fun for awhile.\nThe graphics are okay and the plot is decent, but where this game really shines is the world size and freedom. You run around huge cities however you like, climbing up walls jumping from roof to roof and assassinating key targets... or anyone you please really. You'll die quite a bit until you figure out your specific fighting style but after that you can hack and slash all you please without any major issues. The one drawback is this game is repetitive as hell, the quests are always the same and the story line just isn't strong enough for me to bother with it. I play to kill some people and run around the tops of buildings pretending like I'm some bad\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665form of Aladdin for a few minutes but that is about it. Overall worth it if you can get it on sale, otherwise don't bother.", "hours": 9.6, "username": "HiddenLifeGaming", "products": 429, "early_access": false}
