{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-16", "text": "tem que subir nas casa", "hours": 15.4, "username": "Sentafria", "products": 736, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-14", "text": "After trying this one out a couple years ago, I came to it slightly more mature and with an xbox 360 controller. What a treat it was. Although some really didn't like the modern but virtual-assassin setting, I didn't find it too annoying and actually thought it somewhat intriguing. To me, the highlights of this game are its' graphics, combat, and historical atmosphere and setting. The world is bright and the animations extremely fluid. Speaking of fluid, so is the combat as you assassinate one enemy after another executing counters and sweet but brutal combos. If you're a history fan, this game also has a rich historical atmosphere and storyline to follow, although it's basically completely fictional. I picked this game up for $3 and got 20 very enjoyable hours out of it. Not too bad at all. 8.6/10.", "hours": 19.1, "user_id": "76561197972140596", "username": "Kelso", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-13", "text": "The Assassin's Creed series are my favourite games of all time, what more recommendation do you need?", "hours": 27.5, "username": "dpi.erico [TF2 Odds Collector]", "products": 166, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 250, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-12", "text": "You can definitely tell that this is the original, but don't let that stop you from buying it. The controls at first seem very unwieldly, but after an hour of play, they become second nature and allow one to do numerous actions at once which you couldn't do otherwise. The storyline's nice and it keeps you asking why. I will forewarn you that they do screw with Christianity and religion in general, but as the Assassin's Creed is \"Nothing is true. Everything is permitted\", it calls for wisdom in discerning between what is and what isn't. Assassin's Creed asks us to question what really happened and to defend our answer, while still taking on the guise as a game. Also, assassinating people that have no idea their life is going to end is just kind of fun, in a sort of morbid way.", "hours": 72.3, "username": "\u300eEvanescence\u300f", "products": 99, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-12", "text": "For all it's flaws it's a masterpiece. While it was repetitive, the story was captivating. The side quests were virtually useless, however (the flags...). There was no real customization, but it was cool to explore regardless. While a lot of players did not finish the game due to it's repitition, I encourage everyone to play it for the story alone.", "hours": 16.0, "username": "Skud", "products": 280, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-10", "text": "Assassin's Creed is essentially the platforming from Prince of Persia turned into a full game. Altair's climbing is nothing short of revolutionary platforming. It's far less in-depth than Mirror's Edge, but it's much simpler, quicker and easier to relive your childhood Spiderman fantasies. The graphics are beautiful, especially for a game so old, and the art style is superb. The streets of Acre are rife with sickness and King Richard is scruff, fat and ugly as sin. The plot is like a cross between a Robert Ludlum book and The Matrix, only if you add a whole lot more suck into the mix. I bet you the writer read the wikipedia article on cyber punk after they had just made a rad game set during the crusades and jammed in the Desmond sections as an afterthought. I normally don't care about immersion, but it's at record lows here. I bought this game to feel like an assassin, but after the 20th bench The Lone Klansman sits on to evade the guards, this is a damn problem.", "hours": 14.9, "user_id": "76561197980910801", "username": "Haute DIO", "products": 678, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-08", "text": "In this game you play as lead vocalist of Creed, Scott Stapp. He is also an assassin and must take out several members of boy bands including N-Sync, New Kids on the Block and the Backstreet Boys.", "hours": 17.8, "username": "Dire Miralis", "products": 318, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-07", "text": "Repetitive, but tells the story that starts it all. Worth a buy for less than $10.", "hours": 4.0, "username": "Roni", "products": 308, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-06-02", "text": "Nothing beats the thrill of stalking your prey, going in for the kill and then running throughout the city to escape after an assassination. Tight controls give you excellent control over Alta\u00efr.\nMain story is kinda lack-luster, but it makes up for it at the end.", "hours": 17.3, "user_id": "76561197985160995", "username": "J-Dub", "products": 71, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 5, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-05-28", "text": "CRAP CRAP CRAP!\nDON'T BUY.", "hours": 1.7, "username": "Mr. Krabs", "products": 465, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-28", "text": "\"Nothing is true. Everything is permited.\"\nDefintly, this is a game everyone should play till the end. The beginning may be a bit slow and even descouraging, but the overall game experience is fantastic, if given a chance.", "hours": 0.5, "username": "Jef", "products": 838, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-24", "text": "One of those franchises that everyone must play.", "hours": 25.7, "username": "hobnob", "products": 357, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-22", "text": "Wow this game ios one of the top games that I ever played. It has a lot of fun, challenging and even funny parts. It does start as a boring game because of the controllers, but after you will have a blasdt on killing guards, and jumping from cellings", "hours": 37.0, "user_id": "76561198019973923", "username": "=7Cav=CPL.Vel\u00e1squez.J", "products": 217, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 251, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-05-21", "text": "Looks nice, and the first hour or so is fun, but it fails to evolve or change in any way after that, so you may as well play the demo 10 times and watch the cinematics on Youtube. As a barely touched console port, the Exit to Windows button is about 8 menus and 2 minutes away from the game world.", "hours": 8.3, "username": "Spoilers", "products": 286, "found_funny": 2, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-20", "text": "Excellent game. Don't let the usual reviews talking about how the game is 'repetitive' and 'boring' dissuade you from buying the game - it's absolutely fantastic. Gorgeous visuals (Wide open spaces, massive detailed cities, lots of NPCs in one city at the same time, ...), excellent gameplay, and an intuitive and extremely interesting set of control schemes.", "hours": 22.2, "username": "Regime", "products": 1157, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-05-16", "text": "Bad combat and repetitive sidequests keep it from being great.  The main missions and the storyline are really good though, its worth about $5", "hours": 44.9, "username": "418", "products": 321, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-20", "text": "One of the classics from the early 360/PS3 era. You play as Desmond, a test subject for a mysterious project which involves the use of a machine called \"The Animus\". The Animus transports the subject into the body of any ancestor from the subject's bloodline, via genetic memory. Altair is the ancestor of choice in this game. There's so much running and jumping it'll make you want to take up parkour. The animation is beautiful as well as the worlds. The worlds are so impressive, visiting places like Jerusalem, Damascus and Acre, each having it's own distinct feel and design. Certainly a work of art. Buy it, play it, love it.", "hours": 22.9, "username": "ManyNekoZ", "products": 1241, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-04-17", "text": "This was a hell of a lot of fun, no joke! The combat and climbing is alot of fun on the PC, I doubt that it would be on a console like xbox. I played it through twice, but it wasn't addicting more than that so it is now uninstalled. Was great for the sale price.", "hours": 76.8, "username": "DiGiTaL CLeaNeR", "products": 137, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-31", "text": "I am personally loving this game. I've played it for 30+ hours, and it is really fun. Assassinations are really tricky though, so don't be surprised if most of your attempts end in you fighting all the guards one by one until you kill your target, instead of a nice slick knife in the back.\nThe cities are amazing in their scope and detail. However, the fact that they're so large means you spend a lot of time in the game just getting from place to place.\nAll in all, I very much recommend it. Oh, and one last note: killing people with counter moves looks awesome.", "hours": 40.0, "username": "Exon9", "products": 306, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-26", "text": "It looks like Assassins Creed is becoming one of the best games I've played, at least, in a long time. A clich\u00e9 filled epic that blends history and real locations with a fictional, yet suspenseful storyline. Immersion is the key, and Assassins Creed provides, even (without spoiling too much) in two realms.\nGraphics wise I didn't expect as much as I got. Even with Antialiasing disabled the game looks vibrant and alive (you can force it on through a text file, default with higher resolutions is 0).\nAs for the controls, I'm guessing it's smoother when played with a pad. Although the pc configuration works, at times it can feel a little sticky.\nThe game has also some informational value; I for one had no idea how huge the city of Jerusalem really was, before I rode to the walls myself.\nI would suggest this game to anyone who likes open world/action/sneaking games or just medieval themes in general.", "hours": 15.2, "username": "\\CCC\\ Procyon", "products": 331, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 6, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-03-26", "text": "This game really sucks.", "hours": 6.7, "user_id": "76561197971682417", "username": "Bradwick Chaddington", "products": 143, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-26", "text": "Eines der geilsten Actionspiele der Welt!!!Muss man wenigstens mal gespielt haben.Wer AC nicht mag geh\u00f6rt verpr\u00fcgelt!!!", "hours": 24.9, "user_id": "76561198038822431", "username": "Hauptmann", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-25", "text": "Klasse Spiel, allerdings werden diese 7 Minispiele, die man l\u00f6sen muss, um sein Ziel zu finden und zu t\u00f6ten auf dauer langweilig. Belauschen, Verpr\u00fcgeln, Flaggen sammeln, Bodenziel meucheln, Bogensch\u00fctze meucheln, Dachrennen, H\u00e4ndlerstand zerst\u00f6ren. Minigames dauer im Schnitt 3 minuten. Story ist ok, Spa\u00df auch. Ist empfehlenswert wenn man resistent gegen sich st\u00e4ndig wiederholende Aufgaben ist.", "hours": 44.3, "username": "illostos", "products": 409, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 252, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-24", "text": "Wasn't expecting such a well crafted game when I had only paid five dollars (on sale). Controls work surprisingly well for a port and it's very pretty. Directx11 effects weren't anything to call home about but it would be hard to find an excuse not to miss this modern classic.", "hours": 17.9, "username": "Prvt. Donut", "products": 1397, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-24", "text": "Amazing Game!", "hours": 56.8, "username": "MASTER EXPLODER{T.L.}", "products": 285, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-22", "text": "If you like slipping off of a balcony and falling into\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665then this is the game for you. I myself dont roll that way.", "hours": 3.4, "username": "Diazepanda", "products": 251, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-22", "text": "Has to be renamed to Assassins Creed 16:9\n:(", "hours": 0.2, "username": "robert | CSP", "products": 385, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-14", "text": "Incredibly enjoyable!\nIf you're not much for sneaking around and making stealthy kills the game more than welcomes you to charge in sword swinging. You can assassinate your own way!", "hours": 25.1, "username": "Doctor Fox", "products": 344, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-14", "text": "A wonderful game! It was really addicting as i beat it in 3 sittings. The story was great. The cities that you climb around are amazing. The characters are intriguing. The sounds are fun. The Ai can be stupid at times and jump off buildings when they are chasing you. The graphics are great! The gameplay is alot of fun. The sword fighting could be improved but it is still fun. It is a great adventure game that keeps you wanting more in the end. There is alot of things to do in the game. It is a great game if you can get your hands on it. If you ever see this in the price range that is great for you then don't hesitate to get it because you wont regret it. Its a great game!", "hours": 21.8, "username": "NorkDorf On Twitch {Live}", "products": 8235, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-12", "text": "Great game. However, support for Xbox 360 wireless controller is broken. Fortunately, there is a community patch that you can download to get proper support.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Raistlin Majere", "products": 315, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-11", "text": "Exploration & platforming. AC is designed for me!", "hours": 51.4, "username": "Rainsing", "products": 304, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-10", "text": "Looking at this game at first I thought it was a normal Hitman assasin type game. I bought it with a bundle so I thought I would give it a try. It has a really great storyline and is more sci fi than I thought, in fact it revolves around a sci fi type theme.\nIf you get a chance play it", "hours": 6.5, "username": "Jyncs", "products": 119, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-08", "text": "A Pretty game, reels you in after a while gets you blood pumping when the heat is on", "hours": 24.5, "username": "8ace69", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 253, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-03", "text": "Patrick Byrn eats\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665", "username": "Secret Asshole", "products": 204, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-02", "text": "This game is beautiful. There's a lot to do init, so much to explore... Just fantasic. Only thing is that you really need a controller, but that's just me. Without a controller it felt really weird, but then my 360 controller saved the day.", "hours": 31.6, "username": "Displeased Duck", "products": 525, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-03-01", "text": "This game is worth playing through just for the story. The gameplay is good, but it is also repetitive!\nForget getting all the collectibles, and forget doing all the side missions. Just play through it for the story. Why? Because Assassin's Creed 2 and Brotherhood is so good (and improves so much over this game) that it's worth playing through to get the full experience.", "hours": 15.9, "username": "the Sliver", "products": 941, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2011-02-20", "text": "I like 3rd person games and found this one to be weak.  Not sure why, but halfway through I stopped wanting to play it.", "hours": 0.0, "username": "McMillanFixXxeR", "products": 414, "found_funny": 1, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-02-17", "text": "Awful. I tried so hard to finish it but it's just so...flaccid. There's not heart at all in it.", "hours": 8.0, "username": "Dan", "products": 517, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-02-12", "text": "A very good game, though repetitive. It was much improved in the sequel.", "hours": 27.1, "username": "facls", "products": 663, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-02-01", "text": "Even after several centuries, the Middle East still looks the same today as it does in this game.", "hours": 12.4, "username": "schpeltiger", "products": 285, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-28", "text": "It's not a bad game by any means, but the gameplay gets incredibly repetitive. The stor is very good, though, and the series only gets better from here.\nSCORE: 7.75/10", "hours": 12.1, "username": "StonedMagician", "products": 506, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-11", "text": "Forwarning: It gets betters once you figure out how the AC Engine works.  Very beautiful game when it's not acting up, but with all the gripes I have with it, the story is very interesting and the assassination missions are so satisfiying to acomplish.  Walking away like a boss after a high profile target kill makes it worth the annoyances.", "hours": 24.8, "username": "CAT PLANET; CAT PLANET! :3", "products": 559, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2011-01-08", "text": "Because I did a review of Assasin's Creed 2, I thought it only fair to review it's predecessor. Assassin's Creed (if I say \"2\", it implies the sequel. Other wise, I'm referring to the first game) initially feels like a breath of fresh air amidst all wildly rampant action games at its time. And it was unique (\"was\" being the key word). The graphics are stunning and it helped buff the slim pickings of the stealth genre. However, as the game dragged on, you'll come to realize that all your quests are the same and at its core, you're simply repeating what you've been doing since the first hour of the game for about a dozen more hours. Only play this game if you care about the series' plot. Otherwise, skip it.\nGrade: C-", "hours": 28.4, "username": "DaNCeSWiTHBuLLeTS", "products": 1967, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 254, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-29", "text": "Awesome game. I beat it on ps3. On PC its tad more complicated with the mouse and keyboard. I cant explain why but the graphics are way better. Its amazing looking game. Definitelly recommend. But only this. First Game.", "hours": 2.3, "username": "R3V3NG3R", "products": 206, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-25", "text": "Assassin's Creed is a great sandbox game and is currently on of my favorite ongoing game series. Great story, combat system, graphics and level design.", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Fragems", "products": 722, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-22", "text": "Solid graphics, but mediocre gameplay. Expect extreme repetition. $5 bucket.", "hours": 33.0, "username": "JonesR", "products": 1346, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-22", "text": "This game was just flat out FUN.\nWhile I don't have the sequels... i sure wish I did. They just don't like to drop their prices much at all... \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665s.", "user_id": "76561197970634020", "username": "Mork d'Ork", "products": 146, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-18", "text": "Reading many reviews of this game, I understand how fortunate I was to have played, or better said, lived through the original Assassin's Creed without reading any reviews beforehand. I enjoyed the game totally oblivious to the \"well known facts\" that it is redundant, buggy, too easy, and has a confusing ending. I just bought it, started playing and fell out of reality for a week, and loved every minute of it, except the ending - it was really sad to realise that it was finished and I couldn't play any more.\nI must admit I'm not a \"gamer\", I enjoy games since my childhood, but I do not play them professionally, and I'm more on the intellectual side. I get bored with shallow keyboard-smashing action titles, and more appreciate a solid story and an adventure that allows me to use logic to solve the problem. I've never played games like Assassin's Creed before (were there any?), so I was totally blown away. I found it very similar to the original Prince of Persia from 1990, the same cinematic movement animations, same classic approach to a level-based story progression. One fight was a bit too hard for me, but I generally loved the idea of not dying. Since it was a memory, I could not really die - desynchronisation merely meant I was not doing it right. Psychologically it's somehow easier for me than getting actually killed. This game is much more logical than its sequels - here you live through a genetic memory of an ancestor, and you have to follow it very closely. In the sequels you had much more freedom, you could buy property, get various weapons, heal yourself, dress in fancy clothes through uPlay rewards (sometimes losing a finger), visit same place during a day or night - that really broke the concept of a DNA memory and moved the franchise from a science fiction into a non-science... better said: nonsense-fiction genre.\nI have found the multi-layer matryoshka-like plot, the graphics and Altair so realistic, I was saying sorry to him each time I was clumsy enough to make him fall off a wall :) I don't understand what \"redundancy\" people are talking about. I guess I'm not blessed with a consumer's mind, and to me consistency, integrity of a story is more important than the \"fun value\".\nSo, if anyone hasn't yet played the original Assassin's Creed and makes up his mind by reading my review, I'd say that if you're jumping through the games while chatting to your friends, and you pay no attention to dialogues and story, this one is not for you, and you will be disappointed with it. However, if you immerse into games and live through them, this is something you'll most likely appreciate.", "hours": 2.8, "username": "michael", "products": 459, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-18", "text": "Assassin's Creed is one of those games that goes out of its way to make you feel badass. For example, when running along rooftops, so long as you're within step or reach of something to jump on, run across, or grab onto (depending on your skills obtained), Altair is going to look badass as hell running around and stabbing people.\nThe game is not super difficult, but it's fun to play an assassin. Don't miss the super conspiracy theme in this game, either!", "hours": 19.9, "username": "Buns of Aluminum", "products": 1757, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-13", "text": "An absolutely fascinating premise, a 'game within a game' dynamic that hasn't been exploited before. It's a stunningly realised Medieval world, and the first few missions are breathtaking. Hearing the characters speak, negotiating crowds, and running up walls and climbing is just pure joy. The draw distance is great also.", "hours": 31.3, "username": "D\u00fcsti\u00f1_ds3000", "products": 334, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-09", "text": "I bought this when it was uber cheap because I wanted a good adventure type game to play. Over all, it was very repetitive, the story was kind of terrible imho, and the gameplay wasn't very hard. I enjoy running from rooftop to rooftop, and being one stealthy mother \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665er, but I'd probably recommend it on a $4.99 - $9.99 price range basis.", "hours": 14.8, "username": "Control", "products": 359, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-08", "text": "One of my most favorite games of 2005-2010. The story and execution are extremely compelling.", "username": "shurcooL`", "products": 113, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-12-03", "text": "If you like medieval times, hitman, and some platforming added on, you will like AC. The only problem, after a while, it can get a little boring, and you end up just running through it to finish the story,which is not bad either, this game will keep you entertained to the end.", "hours": 24.8, "username": "defiance5050", "products": 607, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 255, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-28", "text": "Though it's not without it's problems, the original Assassin's Creed is a nice game that splices the traditions of adventure and platform games!  The sci-fi element seems slightly contrived but at least offers something different in the way of gaming narrative.", "hours": 10.4, "username": "Nemesis", "products": 339, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-26", "text": "PC Version blows away both console games!", "hours": 55.8, "user_id": "76561197969366898", "username": "RubberDuckyWithaKnife", "products": 1124, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-25", "text": "Okay. Here's the deal with Assassin's Creed. It's a really great jigsaw puzzle that somebody put together all wrong. It's a little bit like God of War, but don't think you'll like it because you liked God of War.\nI don't know. I don't want to hate on it, because I really do like it. It's a fun game. There are just things about it that don't make sense. For example: riding your horse past soldiers at high speed makes them chase you.\nAnd it's not like they chase you, catch you, then you have a conversation like \"you shouldn't ride so fast on the highway.\" They chase you, they catch you, they kill you. because you were galloping down the goddamn highway.\nThe idea of the game and the story of it are really, really cool. But the game itself is a little bit hard to play because of things like that. But I maintain my former opinion: try it and you might like it, because this is actually a good game. It's just got it's little quirks.\nGet the demo and see if you like it.", "hours": 3.6, "username": "thorvindr", "products": 410, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-22", "text": "This game was like a dream come true for me. A lot of people complain about it being repetitive, shallow, boring, etc. and I can understand how they can say that. However I really enjoyed the freedom of movement and beautiful scenery. It's like you're a Middle Ages Batman! With time travel! I would've picked up the sequel on launch day if it wasn't for the overbearing DRM.", "hours": 22.1, "username": "\u300clandwhale\u300d", "products": 967, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2010-11-22", "text": "probably the worst game I am ashamed to have listed on my owned games list", "username": "func_door", "products": 438, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 4, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "Who doesn't want  to be an assassin and go around running on rooftops and secretly killing people? Very fun to play with an interesting story line both in and out of the Aminus.", "hours": 21.5, "username": "Jaykoni", "products": 87, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "In the epic war between Saladin and Richard, Christianity and Islam, This Warrior of a  Extremist\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665sect rises to Save the land holy to Christian Jew and Muslim alike from a threat to all man-kind!\nIncluded with possibly the best swordsmanship in any game ever!!!!", "hours": 183.5, "username": "The Pasha [\u262a\u26051453rd\u262a\u2605]", "products": 298, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "A unique game of its' time, with open world parkour, an intruiging story with interesting characters, as well as bonuses that aren't available on the console editions, any fan of Prince of Persia games, stealth/action games, as well as fans of any new type of concept should experience this game, despite it's few shortcomings.", "hours": 11.1, "username": "M1SF0RTUNE [Work]", "products": 738, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-11-19", "text": "What a beautiful work of art this game is. The platforming is fantastic, with a free running so you can jump, grab, climb, almost anywhere. Social stealth is valued, and strategi to use. Running across rooftops is incredibly fun. The storyline is immersive, compelling, and makes good sense, with alot of intruige and mystery mixed in. Learn the skills of an asassin, find your target, study the situation, learn information out on the streets, and let your blade find their throat. While you are mostly invincible if you play it right, you can end up needing to re synch with the genetic memories if you do anything too foolish. Be alert and observant, and don't forget your creed.", "hours": 79.4, "username": "Shalmendo", "products": 463, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "15100", "page": 256, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2010-10-19", "text": "Cool game. Not perfect, a little repetitve, but fun. Wait for a sale.", "hours": 24.1, "username": "Lyra", "products": 370, "early_access": false}
